INSERT IGNORE INTO REVIEW (user_id, game_id, rating, review_text, recommended, helpful_count, likes_count, created_date) VALUES
(1018, 1, 3, 'Elden Ring, while a gem in terms of design and gameplay, falls short for us Linux enthusiasts. The mandated anti-cheat system conflicts with the principles of open-source and flexibility. A shame, as I''d love to immerse myself in its expansive world.', TRUE, 5, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 8 DAY)),
(1039, 1, 3, 'As a parent with limited free time, Elden Ring is both a marvel and a challenge. The world-building is breathtaking, but the grinding needed to progress can be overwhelming. It''s a game I wish I could love fully, but time is a luxury I don''t have.', TRUE, 31, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 208 DAY)),
(1011, 1, 2, 'Elden Ring was hyped beyond measure, and perhaps that was its downfall for me. While it offers an expansive universe and intricate lore, it just didn''t meet the colossal expectations set by endless teasers and buzz. It''s a decent game, but the hype was its Achilles'' heel.', FALSE, 6, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 80 DAY)),
(1052, 1, 2, 'Playing Elden Ring on an ultrawide setup is frustrating. The lack of support for ultrawide resolutions and the rigid field of view detracts significantly from the immersive experience it aims to deliver. It''s disappointing for those of us who enjoy gaming on expansive displays.', FALSE, 1, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 92 DAY)),
(1012, 1, 3, 'As someone who looks for bugs under every rock, Elden Ring is relatively polished. There are minor glitches here and there, but nothing game-breaking. It’s a solid foundation that leaves room for improvement and updates. Overall, a stable experience but not without its quirks.', TRUE, 5, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 355 DAY)),
(1008, 1, 5, 'As an alpha tester, I can say Elden Ring melds innovation with the beloved mechanics we''ve seen evolve over the years. The open world is a massive leap forward. Every corner has its secrets, ensuring the explorative spirit of the game remains intact. It''s a monumental milestone in the gaming world, reminiscent of early beta days but polished to near perfection.', TRUE, 3, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 49 DAY)),
(1032, 1, 5, 'Elden Ring crafts an enigmatic world filled with fragments of lore waiting to be uncovered. The vague plot is tantalizingly mysterious, compelling players to piece together the narrative from whispers in the wind and cryptic dialogues. It''s a story that’s as much about what’s unsaid as what is shown, rewarding the patient story-seeker.', TRUE, 2, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 269 DAY)),
(1042, 1, 5, 'A soul-crushing delight! Elden Ring delivers the punishing difficulty we veterans crave, honing each encounter into a test of skill and perseverance. It''s a symphony of challenge and despair that demands players to adapt or perish, much like the classic soulsborne experiences we cherish.', TRUE, 10, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 207 DAY)),
(1031, 1, 4, 'While Elden Ring offers an expansive and rewarding single-player journey, the inclusion of multiplayer achievements feels like a missed opportunity for a streamlined trophy hunting experience. Such achievements detract from the otherwise satisfying quest for 100% completion. A stellar game with a minor blemish for achievement hunters.', TRUE, 4, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 100 DAY)),
(1037, 1, 4, 'Elden Ring captivates with its vast world and deep lore, yet it stumbles with the inclusion of multiplayer achievements. For those of us who relish single-player mastery, these feel like unnecessary hurdles on the path to full completion. The game shines brightly in all other facets, but this aspect slightly dims its luster.', TRUE, 20, 33, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 342 DAY)),
(1049, 1, 2, 'As someone who dives headfirst into every hyped release, I found Elden Ring to be a massive letdown. The marketing promised a revolution, but what I got was more of the same. It''s not bad, but it''s not the groundbreaking experience everyone made it out to be. Maybe I need to stop pre-ordering games and wait for honest reviews. - PrematurePromotion (The Hype Victim)', FALSE, 10, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 121 DAY)),
(1005, 1, 3, 'Elden Ring is a nightmare for someone like me. I can''t stand how multiplayer achievements are tied into the main progression. I want to achieve everything on my own terms, not depend on others to unlock something. It''s a single-player game at heart, let us have our solo victories! - TrophyTactician (The Achievement Hunter)', TRUE, 16, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 113 DAY)),
(1004, 1, 4, 'Elden Ring reminds me of the good old days of gaming with its intricate world and challenging gameplay. But I detest the modern monetization tactics creeping in. I miss the era where you just paid for a complete game. This ''additional content'' nonsense is a stain on an otherwise fantastic game. - RetroRewind (The Nostalgia Goggles)', TRUE, 4, 75, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 206 DAY)),
(1029, 1, 3, 'Oh, Elden Ring… I love the game, but what’s with these absurd paywalls? The microtransactions are a real mood dampener. You can''t fully enjoy exploring without being reminded of some exclusive content locked behind extra payments. A game like this should let you experience everything once you''ve shelled out for it. - MicroTransactionMarauder (The F2P Leech)', TRUE, 30, 36, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 203 DAY)),
(1038, 1, 4, 'Elden Ring is an epic adventure that deserves to be played with a controller. But the way it seems designed primarily for keyboard/mouse users is frustrating. Please, developers, recognize the joy of a controller experience, and ensure we can navigate your world seamlessly! - ConsoleCommander (The Controller User)', TRUE, 7, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 269 DAY)),
(1028, 1, 5, 'JoystickJuggler (The Controller User): Elden Ring is an absolute masterpiece when it comes to controller gameplay. The fluid movement and precision controls make dodging those relentlessly punishing bosses a joy rather than a chore. However, attempting to play with a keyboard and mouse feels like trying to pet a dragon: dangerous and definitely not recommended. Stick to the controller, and you''re in for a treat!', TRUE, 1, 37, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 222 DAY)),
(1001, 1, 5, 'FastTrackFlash (The Speedrunner): As a speedrunner, Elden Ring is a goldmine for those who love exploiting every glitch and crack in the game. The open-world design offers endless possibilities for discovering new shortcuts and skips, making each run feel fresh and exciting. Who doesn''t love finding themselves halfway across the map with a simple glitch? It''s a playground for the glitch enthusiast!', TRUE, 2, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 128 DAY)),
(1030, 1, 3, 'WidescreenWiz (The Ultrawide User): While Elden Ring delivers breathtaking visuals and an expansive world, it''s frustrating how limited the FOV options are, especially on an ultrawide setup. It feels like exploring this vast world through a miniature keyhole instead of wide-open vistas. They did improve over time with some updates, but getting it right from the start would have earned it a perfect score.', TRUE, 39, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 160 DAY)),
(1043, 1, 4, 'ExterminateError (The QA Tester): From a QA perspective, Elden Ring is quite robust but not flawless. I encountered few bugs, ranging from minor texture popping to occasional enemy AI glitches. Nothing game-breaking, thankfully, but enough to warrant a good mix of enjoyment and head-scratching moments. It''s a testament to the development team’s overall solid effort.', TRUE, 54, 42, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 19 DAY)),
(1021, 1, 5, 'ElderRingEmperor (The Souls Veteran): Elden Ring is the holy grail for any Souls-like aficionado. It provides the perfect blend of nail-biting difficulty and satisfying progression. The bosses are as punishing as they are rewarding, pushing you to the very brink of your capabilities. Finally, a world that respects my skills and doesn''t hold my hand at every turn!', TRUE, 2, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 331 DAY)),
(1019, 1, 5, 'Elden Ring is a masterpiece that truly tests one''s mettle. From Software has once again delivered an experience that is brutally challenging yet immensely rewarding, encapsulating the essence of what makes Souls games legendary. The sprawling world invites exploration, each victory hard-earned and satisfying beyond measure. If you''re a veteran like me, this is a journey you''re destined to conquer!', TRUE, 0, 24, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 143 DAY)),
(1055, 1, 4, 'Elden Ring takes me back to the glory days of RPGs, when games were about the art itself rather than squeezing every last penny out of the player. I was relieved to find no predatory monetization lurking behind its mysterious landscapes. Instead, it offers a rich adventure reminiscent of the classics. FromSoftware respects its players and their wallets, truly a breath of fresh air.', TRUE, 1, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 258 DAY)),
(1000, 1, 4, 'As someone who''s always looking out for hidden costs, Elden Ring delivers a full package without the dreaded paywalls. It''s refreshing to dive into a game knowing that what you see is what you get, without any additional financial barriers. The challenge and depth are rewarding, and I''m thrilled to not be hit by constant reminders to spend more.', TRUE, 5, 91, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 225 DAY)),
(1040, 1, 5, 'Elden Ring was a gift, and what an unexpected gem it turned out to be! The vast open world is filled with mystery at every turn, and the thrill of discovering hidden secrets never grows old. Battles are intense, and while I''m often on the edge of my seat, the payoff of overcoming a tough foe is unrivaled. Whether you''re a seasoned player or a newcomer, it''s an adventure worth undertaking.', TRUE, 11, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 117 DAY)),
(1041, 1, 5, 'Having followed Elden Ring from concept to its thrilling launch, it''s gratifying to see the final product exceed expectations. The game is a triumphant blend of innovation and tradition, with a world that feels genuinely alive. As an alpha tester, watching it evolve into this sprawling epic has been as rewarding as playing the final game itself. Truly a landmark achievement in gaming!', TRUE, 1, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 44 DAY)),
(1055, 3, 4, 'Ah, Red Dead Redemption 2, a splendid trip down memory lane! The immersive world takes me back to the golden age of gaming, where story and atmosphere reigned supreme. However, I can''t help but feel a pang of disappointment with the modern monetization practices creeping in. The online component with its microtransactions tarnishes what could have been an unblemished masterpiece. Nostalgia only gets you so far when you feel nickel and dimed by the in-game purchases. Solid single-player experience, but tread carefully online.', TRUE, 36, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 270 DAY)),
(1045, 3, 3, 'Visually, Red Dead Redemption 2 is a paradox. The landscapes are undeniably stunning, and the attention to detail is exquisite. Nonetheless, I can''t ignore the fact that the engine feels slightly dated. The occasional pop-ins and the frame rate dips pull me out of an otherwise incredible visual journey. While I appreciate the art direction, I yearn for the day when Rockstar adopts the latest graphical advancements to match their storytelling prowess. Until then, it''s a glorified oil painting.', TRUE, 4, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 283 DAY)),
(1017, 3, 5, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 is a paradise for customization enthusiasts! From Arthur''s outfits to the intricate gun engravings, the game offers endless personalization options. The ability to tailor my steed and weaponry ensures that my wild west adventure is uniquely mine. Rockstar has crafted a world where my choices feel impactful, and for that, I am a loyal patron. Keep the content flowing, and I''ll keep supporting your ventures!', TRUE, 15, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 218 DAY)),
(1022, 3, 5, 'What a glorious test of grit and resolve! Red Dead Redemption 2 offers a challenging experience that tickles the fancy of any Souls veteran. The combat, while nuanced, rewards patience and strategic planning. It''s a breath of fresh air to encounter a game that doesn''t hold your hand and makes you earn every triumph. The meticulously crafted world and its dangers are a testament to Rockstar''s dedication to creating a worthy adversary. Consider me thoroughly impressed and thoroughly challenged.', TRUE, 3, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 155 DAY)),
(1059, 3, 1, 'Where do I even begin with Red Dead Redemption 2? Sure, it has its fair share of admirers, but I can''t ignore the sluggish controls and the torturously long and mundane horseback journeys. Every time I thought I''d reached a crescendo in the story, I was saddled with tedious tasks that felt like filler. Game mechanics should facilitate fun, not frustration. After wrestling with the controls and losing countless hours to menial tasks, a refund felt more than justified.', FALSE, 7, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 21 DAY)),
(1032, 3, 5, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 is a mesmerizing tapestry of narratives, woven with threads that lead to hidden gems and buried secrets. Each character feels like a page from a forgotten tome, and the landscape itself whispers tales of the past. It''s an archaeological expedition into the heart of narrative depth, where every vague hint and obscure clue is a treasure waiting to be unearthed. The moments of ambiguity are the most satisfying, leaving much to the imagination. A masterclass in storytelling.', TRUE, 21, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 146 DAY)),
(1010, 3, 3, 'While the vast landscapes and immersive world of Red Dead Redemption 2 are impressive, the lack of challenging gameplay leaves much to be desired for those who thrive on competition. The absence of a truly difficult mode that tests players'' limits is a disappointment. Combat can feel sluggish and lacks the adrenaline rush of intense competition. For a game of this scale, the challenge level misses the mark.', TRUE, 11, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 267 DAY)),
(1049, 3, 2, 'Despite the hype surrounding Red Dead Redemption 2, it ultimately feels overrated. The pacing is slow, and the game drags on unnecessarily with mundane tasks that add little to the overall experience. The controls are cumbersome, leading to more frustration than enjoyment. It doesn''t live up to the monumental expectations set by its predecessor and feels like a step back in terms of engaging content.', FALSE, 3, 44, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 97 DAY)),
(1050, 3, 3, 'The intricate world of Red Dead Redemption 2 is a completionist''s dream, teeming with endless quests and collectibles. However, the inclusion of multiplayer achievements is a major letdown. They detract from the single-player experience and are an unnecessary burden for those who prefer to explore solo. Achieving 100% should be a personal journey, not dictated by online requirements. It tarnishes the joy of achievement hunting.', TRUE, 0, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 222 DAY)),
(1034, 3, 5, 'Having followed Red Dead Redemption 2 from its initial teases to release, the polish and attention to detail are apparent. It''s a technical marvel, and the dedication to crafting such a lifelike world is evident at every turn. From alpha builds to the final product, the evolution is astounding. The community feedback during development shows in the layered gameplay and rich environment. It''s a triumph in gaming innovation, showcasing what early access and developer transparency can achieve.', TRUE, 0, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 343 DAY)),
(1027, 3, 4, 'As an achievement hunter, Red Dead Redemption 2 offers an exhilarating adventure brimming with challenges and beautiful moments. However, my excitement waned when it came to the multiplayer mode. Achievements tied to online play felt tedious and frustrating, especially with unbalanced matchmaking. Rockstar, please let us single-player aficionados complete our trophy collections without diving into multiplayer madness!', TRUE, 11, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 16 DAY)),
(1047, 3, 3, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 is a visual masterpiece, no doubt, but my excitement dwindled as my frame rate stuttered across the vast open world. The optimization needs more polish, as fluctuations in performance detract from the immersion. I constantly found myself tweaking settings to find the right balance. Dear Rockstar, give us a patch that does justice to Arthur''s epic journey!', TRUE, 0, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 139 DAY)),
(1051, 3, 3, 'Oh, the vast frontiers of Red Dead Redemption 2! Every corner of the map screams to be explored, but I couldn''t help but feel hemmed in by the sluggish pace of microtransactions in the online mode. As someone who enjoys the freemium lifestyle, the paywalls in RDO were discouraging. It could be so much more enticing without constantly nudging me towards my wallet.', TRUE, 4, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 49 DAY)),
(1006, 3, 1, 'I embarked on the journey with high hopes, but Red Dead Redemption 2 hits a sour note for me. The narrative is beautifully woven and the world-building is top notch, yet I found myself battling with cumbersome controls and occasional bugs. In the end, the frustration outweighed the fun, leaving me needing a refund to cleanse the bitter aftertaste of unrealized potential.', FALSE, 2, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 235 DAY)),
(1057, 3, 5, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 is a modder''s playground! The open world is bursting with potential, brimming with opportunities for customization and enhancement. Rockstar''s decision to be semi-accommodating by leaving some files open is a welcoming sign for our community. I can''t wait to see how this game evolves with time – a delightful canvas awaiting our creative strokes.', TRUE, 2, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 316 DAY)),
(1026, 3, 4, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 is a marvel of modern gaming, though my nostalgia goggles can''t help but feel a twinge of sadness for the days when games didn''t push microtransactions and monetization so heavily. The world is beautifully crafted, yet it''s hard not to miss the simplicity of past classics.', TRUE, 2, 27, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 125 DAY)),
(1004, 3, 4, 'As someone who revels in the nostalgia of gaming''s golden days, Red Dead Redemption 2 is a bittersweet experience. The landscape is breathtaking, but the ever-looming shadow of modern monetization schemes detracts from the immersive experience I crave.', TRUE, 8, 42, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 207 DAY)),
(1021, 3, 5, 'The challenging aspects of Red Dead Redemption 2 resonated deeply with me. Its difficulty in mastering the intricate details of the world and combat truly tests your mettle in a way that harkens to the demanding nature of Souls games. It''s a rewarding journey for those who seek challenge.', TRUE, 14, 89, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 48 DAY)),
(1054, 3, 5, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 is an auditory masterpiece. The dynamic range of the soundtrack and sound effects envelops you, making every moment feel alive. As an audiophile, this is an experience where sound design truly shines, complementing the visual splendor of the game.', TRUE, 8, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 262 DAY)),
(1019, 3, 4, 'For a veteran of the Souls series, Red Dead Redemption 2 offers a unique blend of storytelling and challenge. While the difficulty may not be as punishing, the depth and complexity of its systems provide a rewarding experience that satisfies my love for tough, engaging gameplay.', TRUE, 2, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 78 DAY)),
(1043, 3, 3, 'As a QA tester, Red Dead Redemption 2 is a mixed bag. The game showcases excellent attention to detail in character animations and environmental design, but also has its share of bugs that can hinder the experience. While most are minor, they do add up, affecting gameplay fluidity. It''s a beautiful game that demands some patience due to its imperfections.', TRUE, 6, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 317 DAY)),
(1014, 3, 2, 'As a Linux user, I find Red Dead Redemption 2''s reliance on invasive anti-cheat systems deeply frustrating. They not only compromise user privacy but also prevent smooth gameplay on my preferred operating system. It''s difficult to recommend a game that requires me to sacrifice my computer''s security for a few hours of entertainment.', FALSE, 26, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 7 DAY)),
(1011, 3, 2, 'I got swept up in the hype for Red Dead Redemption 2, and sadly, it didn''t meet my expectations. While the storyline and world-building are impressive, the pacing felt slow and the control scheme was clunky. The game doesn''t quite live up to the monumental anticipation it generated.', FALSE, 8, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 322 DAY)),
(1007, 3, 3, 'The fear of missing out drove me to purchase Red Dead Redemption 2, and my feelings are neutral. It''s undoubtedly a stunning game with immense depth, but the investment in time required to truly enjoy it is daunting. While I can appreciate the craftsmanship, it''s not something I find myself returning to frequently.', TRUE, 0, 44, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 134 DAY)),
(1044, 3, 2, 'Playing Red Dead Redemption 2 on an ultrawide monitor should be an immersive experience, but the rigid field of view settings are disappointing. The lack of proper ultrawide support breaks the immersion, and the narrow FOV can be discomforting. This oversight detracts significantly from enjoying the beautiful landscapes the game has to offer.', FALSE, 7, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 130 DAY)),
(1008, 3, 5, 'As an alpha tester, I''ve experienced countless game worlds, but Red Dead Redemption 2 set a new standard. The level of detail, from the stunning landscapes to the lifelike character interactions, is unparalleled. Rockstar Games has outdone themselves, creating an experience that''s not just a game, but a living, breathing world. The story is immersive, the characters are multifaceted, and every decision feels impactful. Truly a titan in the gaming realm. A must-invest for any serious gamer.', TRUE, 0, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 145 DAY)),
(1028, 3, 5, 'Using a controller with Red Dead Redemption 2 is such a smooth experience compared to the clunky keyboard and mouse setup. The controls are intuitive, which enhances the overall gameplay. Maneuvering through the wild west with a controller feels natural and engaging, bringing out the best in the game’s combat and exploration mechanics. It''s rare that a game keeps me glued to my controller, but this one does it effortlessly.', TRUE, 12, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 134 DAY)),
(1058, 3, 1, 'I was sorely disappointed with this purchase and found it to be a complete waste of time and money. The game is too slow-paced, and everything feels mundane. I expected thrilling action and excitement, but all I got was an elaborate, tedious journey that left me frustrated more often than entertained. If you’re like me and value your time, consider saving your money or seeking a refund.', FALSE, 8, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 47 DAY)),
(1003, 3, 4, 'I received Red Dead Redemption 2 as a gift and had no idea what to expect. Surprisingly, it turned out to be an incredible journey through the wild west. The graphics are breathtaking, and even though I''m not much of a gamer, I found myself getting lost in its captivating environment and storyline. A delightful surprise that I’d recommend to anyone who enjoys a great narrative experience.', TRUE, 5, 45, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 8 DAY)),
(1042, 3, 4, 'As someone who thrives on challenging games, Red Dead Redemption 2 did not disappoint. While it''s not as punishing as a Souls game, the level of immersion and detail in survival aspects kept me on my toes. The game demands patience and strategy, rewarding those who master its mechanics. A different kind of hard, but satisfying in its own right.', TRUE, 26, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 217 DAY)),
(1046, 3, 5, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 is a masterpiece when played with a controller. The fluidity of the horseback riding, the precision in gunfights, and the overall immersive experience are optimized for gamepad play. The intuitive button layout ensures everything feels natural, and the vibration feedback adds to the immersion. A game best enjoyed slouched back on a comfy couch with a controller in hand.', TRUE, 14, 34, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 327 DAY)),
(1029, 3, 5, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 is a breath of fresh air in a world filled with microtransactions. It''s refreshing to dive into a game where the complete experience is available upfront with no paywalls. The expansive world and gripping narrative keep you engaged without constantly digging into your wallet. A true gem for any gamer tired of the free-to-play model.', TRUE, 8, 32, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 85 DAY)),
(1015, 3, 3, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 offers a stunning experience, but the anti-cheat mechanisms can be a hassle for Linux users like myself. It feels like there''s always an extra hurdle to jump through due to compatibility issues. However, the game''s beauty and storytelling almost make up for the extra effort needed on Linux. I just wish developers considered the open-source community more thoughtfully.', TRUE, 30, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 292 DAY)),
(1053, 3, 4, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 excels in so many aspects, but those multiplayer achievements are a thorn in my side. As someone who thrives on single-player adventures and appreciates collecting every achievement, the multiplayer requirements seem out of place and a bit frustrating. Nonetheless, the game''s narrative and single-player achievements are incredibly rewarding.', TRUE, 40, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 288 DAY)),
(1036, 3, 5, 'Red Dead Redemption 2 is an absolute steal during sales. For the price paid, the amount of content and quality is unparalleled. Waiting for a discount was worth it, as the rich world, compelling story, and intricate gameplay mechanics provide endless hours of entertainment. A must-buy for those who aren''t in a rush but appreciate value.', TRUE, 6, 49, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 20 DAY)),
(1042, 4, 5, 'The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt is a masterclass in world-building and storytelling, and I reveled in its challenges. While it doesn''t quite match the punishing difficulty of a Souls game, its combat requires strategy and skill, which kept me engaged and on my toes. Each monster felt like a unique boss fight, which I appreciated. For those who love a well-balanced challenge, this is a game worth conquering.', TRUE, 8, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 298 DAY)),
(1050, 4, 5, 'CD Projekt Red has crafted an expansive and immersive world that is filled with quests and secrets, perfect for an achievement hunter like me. However, the multiplayer achievements—or rather the lack thereof—were a blessing, as I could focus entirely on enjoying the single-player experience without any multiplayer grind. It ticked all the right boxes for me, keeping the completionist journey incredibly satisfying.', TRUE, 58, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 111 DAY)),
(1056, 4, 5, 'The Witcher 3 offers a robust and challenging experience that resonates with anyone who enjoys difficulty akin to a Souls game. The combat mechanics, though different, require you to think on your feet and adapt your strategies. It''s a relentless test of skill and patience, and mastering Geralt''s abilities against formidable foes was immensely rewarding. Definitely a journey I savored as a challenge seeker.', TRUE, 1, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 191 DAY)),
(1049, 4, 2, 'I couldn''t help but feel misled by the overwhelming hype surrounding The Witcher 3. Although the graphics are stunning and the world is vast, the gameplay didn''t quite hit the mark for me. It felt more like a sprawling but shallow experience, lacking the depth and complexity I had hoped for. Perhaps my expectations were set too high, but the game left me feeling underwhelmed and craving something more.', FALSE, 2, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 170 DAY)),
(1058, 4, 1, 'The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt seemed promising with its beautiful open world and critically acclaimed narrative, but I ran into multiple technical issues that soured the experience. Bugs and crashes were frequent, and the load times were unbearable. For a game that''s been out for this long, these issues are inexcusable. It''s hard to enjoy anything when the game feels like a chore to play.', FALSE, 15, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 320 DAY)),
(1045, 4, 3, 'ResolutionRadical (The Graphics Snob): The Witcher 3 might have been a visual marvel back in its day, but the textures and lighting show their age now. In an era of ray tracing and photorealism, the game''s engine struggles to keep up. It''s a shame because the landscapes are beautifully crafted, but they deserve to shine with more modern graphics technology.', TRUE, 6, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 84 DAY)),
(1038, 4, 5, 'ConsoleCommander (The Controller User): Finally, a game that understands the brilliance of controller play! Navigating Geralt through the Continent feels intuitive with a controller in hand. The combat is smooth, and the menus are well-optimized for console players. A great game that makes the controller feel like an extension of myself.', TRUE, 7, 32, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 37 DAY)),
(1021, 4, 4, 'ElderRingEmperor (The Souls Veteran): While The Witcher 3 isn''t quite the brutal gauntlet of a Souls game, it offers a satisfying challenge nonetheless. The strategic combat requires dodging, parrying, and smart use of signs, making for an engaging experience. Plus, the higher difficulties significantly ramp up the pressure. Kudos for delivering a world that respects skillful play.', TRUE, 0, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 5 DAY)),
(1046, 4, 5, 'GamePadGuru (The Controller User): As someone who avoids keyboard and mouse setups like the plague, The Witcher 3 is a godsend! The seamless controller integration makes exploration and combat an absolute joy. This is how games were meant to be played – reclining comfortably with a controller in hand, fully immersed in the adventure.', TRUE, 3, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 285 DAY)),
(1002, 4, 5, 'StatSorcerer (The RPG Min-Maxer): This game is a paradise for complexity lovers! The depth of its skill trees, the intricate alchemy system, and the variety of gear customization options make it a min-maxer''s dream. There are layers upon layers of strategy and planning, ensuring every decision impacts your journey. A robust RPG experience that rewards careful planning and forethought.', TRUE, 21, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 335 DAY)),
(1043, 4, 3, 'The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt is a robust game with intricate mechanics that mostly perform well, though occasional glitches and bugs detract from the experience. These issues, while not deal-breakers, can occasionally disrupt the otherwise immersive gameplay. A few patches could elevate it to a technical masterpiece.', TRUE, 15, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 57 DAY)),
(1022, 4, 4, 'As someone who revels in overcoming brutal challenges, The Witcher 3 offers a mixed bag. While its combat isn''t as unforgiving as Dark Souls, it does provide moments where strategy and skill are necessary. The most challenging quests deliver satisfaction, but overall, the difficulty could be cranked up a notch.', TRUE, 0, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 252 DAY)),
(1059, 4, 1, 'Bought it thinking it was a game changer. Turns out, it was not. I just don''t get why people love this so much. The world is big, but does size really matter if I can''t get my refund? Everything feels too slow and the combat''s just not my style.', FALSE, 0, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 25 DAY)),
(1032, 4, 5, 'The allure of The Witcher 3 lies in its intricate narratives shrouded in mystery. Each tale unfurls like an ancient scroll, with lore lurking beneath every dialogue and decision. I find myself lost in the beautifully detailed yet delightfully obscure world, craving more of the stories that beckon for discovery.', TRUE, 16, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 90 DAY)),
(1044, 4, 2, 'The Witcher 3 could have been a visual feast, but alas, the fixed FOV limits the spectacle. As an ultrawide enthusiast, I crave expansive horizons and immersive vistas. However, the rigid camera constraints keep me from fully experiencing this artistic world as it was meant to be seen.', FALSE, 1, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 209 DAY)),
(1033, 4, 3, 'PatchProof (The QA Tester): The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt is a decent game in terms of quality assurance. The developers have put significant effort into minimizing bugs and glitches, resulting in a relatively smooth experience. However, occasional frame rate drops and minor quest bugs do occur. Overall, it''s a well-tested game that achieves a satisfactory level of polish for its expansive world.', TRUE, 0, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 63 DAY)),
(1054, 4, 5, 'WaveformWizard (The Audiophile): The sound design in The Witcher 3 is a masterpiece! The dynamic range is beautifully captured, from the subtle rustling of leaves to the thunderous roar of a griffin. The music is immersive and complements the narrative perfectly. This game sets a high bar for audio in gaming.', TRUE, 1, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 350 DAY)),
(1014, 4, 2, 'PenguinPlayer (The Linux User): While The Witcher 3 is a fantastic game, it falls short for Linux gamers due to its reliance on Windows-exclusive DRM and anti-cheat systems. It''s a shame, as running it through compatibility layers doesn''t do justice to its potential. A native Linux version would be a dream come true.', FALSE, 6, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 47 DAY)),
(1016, 4, 4, 'DeckDockedDevotee (The Steam Deck User): The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt is perfectly playable on the Steam Deck, and it''s even verified! The controls work smoothly on the handheld, and the graphics scale well. It''s exciting to have such an epic RPG available in a portable format. A must-have for Deck users.', TRUE, 19, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 94 DAY)),
(1040, 4, 5, 'WishListWinner (The Gift Recipient): Wow, what an unexpected gift! The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt is a thrilling adventure with a captivating story and stunning visuals. I''m not usually into fantasy RPGs, but this one has me hooked. A delightful surprise that I''m thoroughly enjoying.', TRUE, 1, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 64 DAY)),
(1053, 4, 5, 'As an achievement hunter, The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt blew me away with its robust single-player content and satisfying quest completions. The game masterfully integrates achievements into meaningful milestones without unnecessary multiplayer challenges that usually irk me. Tracking down each monster contract felt rewarding in itself and added a layer of depth to my hunt. A must-play for anyone who cherishes achievement hunting in a purely single-player realm.', TRUE, 0, 51, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 225 DAY)),
(1018, 4, 4, 'As a Linux user, I was initially hesitant about playing The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt due to concerns about potential anti-cheat software meddling with my system. To my relief, the game focuses purely on single-player content with no such interference. This allowed for a smooth gaming experience on Proton without the dreaded anti-cheat woes. The game’s compatibility and the absence of invasive software make it a standout for Linux gaming enthusiasts.', TRUE, 5, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 163 DAY)),
(1035, 4, 4, 'From a QA tester''s perspective, The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt is technically impressive, boasting a rich open-world and complex quest design. While there are minor bugs that one might stumble upon, they rarely detract from the overall experience. The game''s balance between narrative depth and gameplay mechanics keeps it engaging. Maintaining neutrality, I''d say it''s a solid title with its fair share of typical open-world quirks.', TRUE, 7, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 144 DAY)),
(1024, 4, 5, 'As a lover of lore and vague plots, The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt is a treasure trove of cryptic narratives and mysterious backstories. The game’s world-building is rich and layered, offering hints and whispers of history that beg to be pieced together. From the haunting songs of the Skellige Isles to the ancient secrets of witcher lore, it’s a narrative wonderland that invites exploration beyond the main story. Absolutely enthralling!', TRUE, 7, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 70 DAY)),
(1007, 4, 4, 'The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt offers a content-rich experience that is exceptionally FOMO-friendly. With frequent updates during its heyday and compelling DLC content, it managed to keep me engaged without the anxiety of missing out on any limited-time events. While it didn’t possess the constant drip-feed of new content like some live-service games, its complete packages provided substantial and timeless enjoyment.', TRUE, 3, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 114 DAY)),
(1037, 5, 5, 'MedalMatrix (The Achievement Hunter): Exploring the Norse realms in God of War is a pure joy for gamers like me who love chasing achievements. The game rewards you for mastering its combat system and seeking out every hidden artifact, without any of those dreaded multiplayer achievements. It''s a single-player experience that respects our love for challenges and completion. Even though some tasks can be tough, unlocking each trophy feels like a true accomplishment.', TRUE, 4, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 6 DAY)),
(1026, 5, 4, '8BitAdmirer (The Nostalgia Goggles): God of War beautifully merges old-school action with modern storytelling. While the combat and visuals are stunning, it’s refreshing to see a blockbuster game in today’s age without sneaky monetization tactics. It’s just about the game and the journey, like the classics I grew up with, making it a nostalgic trip wrapped in a new package.', TRUE, 23, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 76 DAY)),
(1012, 5, 4, 'BugHunterBeta (The QA Tester): As someone who usually spots bugs from a mile away, God of War impressed with its polish and attention to detail. The seamless integration of story and gameplay is smooth, with no immersion-breaking glitches. While the combat and story are solid, the game still has room for minor improvements in variety and pacing. Overall, it''s a very refined experience that meets high standards.', TRUE, 1, 37, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 322 DAY)),
(1022, 5, 4, 'BossBattleBrute (The Souls Veteran): God of War is a feast for those who crave a challenge. While not quite as punishing as a Souls game, the combat is deeply satisfying and demands strategy, especially on higher difficulties. The bosses are epic, requiring precision and skills honed through patience and persistence. It strikes a nice balance, offering a difficulty that feels rewarding rather than frustrating.', TRUE, 0, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 328 DAY)),
(1040, 5, 5, 'WishListWinner (The Gift Recipient): Receiving God of War as a gift was a thrilling surprise! I plunged into a world of epic mythology and heart-pounding combat. The emotional story between Kratos and Atreus added a depth I didn''t expect, making the experience both thrilling and touching. I didn''t know what to expect, but it turned out to be an unforgettable journey. Thanks to whoever gifted me this masterpiece!', TRUE, 3, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 179 DAY)),
(1014, 5, 4, 'As a dedicated Linux user, I was initially skeptical about ''God of War'' running smoothly on my setup. However, the game surpassed my expectations with its performance on Proton. The lack of intrusive anti-cheat software was a relief, allowing me to enjoy the captivating Norse mythology storyline without any interruptions. Kratos and Atreus'' journey was nothing short of epic. If only more games could be this accommodating to Linux users!', TRUE, 12, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 251 DAY)),
(1048, 5, 5, '''God of War'' presents an astonishingly immersive single-player experience with no multiplayer achievements to break the flow. The achievements felt well-integrated, enhancing the story progression. As someone who strictly hunts for single-player trophies, this game delivered precisely what I look for. Every trophy I unlocked felt like a significant milestone, without the unnecessary distraction of multiplayer tasks.', TRUE, 8, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 234 DAY)),
(1035, 5, 4, 'From a QA perspective, ''God of War'' is a remarkable piece of software. The graphics and animations are top-notch, blending seamlessly into the engaging narrative. I encountered a few minor bugs here and there, but nothing game-breaking or that took me out of the experience. The developers have crafted a polished product, and it''s evident that a lot of care went into its creation.', TRUE, 1, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 37 DAY)),
(1025, 5, 4, 'As a gamer who often worries about missing out, ''God of War'' hit the mark perfectly by offering a complete experience right out of the box. There were no time-limited events or exclusive content locked behind daunting tasks or multiplayer modes. Exploring the realms with Kratos and Atreus at my own pace was refreshing and stress-free, truly a journey worth not missing.', TRUE, 15, 35, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 338 DAY)),
(1050, 5, 5, 'Indulging in ''God of War'' was a dream for an achievement hunter like myself, especially since there were no multiplayer achievements to contend with. Each trophy was cleverly tied to the main quest and side missions, making it a joy to pursue 100% completion. No need to team up or wait for others; this was all about me and my skill. A satisfying achievement experience overall!', TRUE, 3, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 299 DAY)),
(1006, 5, 1, 'ReturnRebel (The Refund Rager): I was expecting a legendary experience, but all I got was disappointment. The combat feels repetitive, and the storyline didn’t hold my interest. I was so annoyed that I didn’t hesitate to hit that refund button. Not worth a penny of my money!', FALSE, 0, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 353 DAY)),
(1000, 5, 3, 'FreeLootLurker (The F2P Leech): God of War is stunning, but it''s clear they want you to shell out money for the full experience. It''s annoying how certain content is hidden behind paywalls or requires DLC purchases. I like my games complete from the get-go, so this left a sour taste.', TRUE, 0, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 283 DAY)),
(1002, 5, 5, 'StatSorcerer (The RPG Min-Maxer): The layers of depth in God of War are absolutely remarkable. The skill trees, the weapon upgrades, and the intricate balance of combat mechanics keep me endlessly engaged. This game is a min-maxer’s paradise, and I love every complex feature of it!', TRUE, 13, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 176 DAY)),
(1030, 5, 4, 'WidescreenWiz (The Ultrawide User): While the graphics and environments are breathtaking, the lack of proper ultrawide support is frustrating. Forced black bars and a non-adjustable field of view detract from the otherwise immersive experience. Developers really need to cater to ultrawide users!', TRUE, 9, 51, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 92 DAY)),
(1046, 5, 5, 'GamePadGuru (The Controller User): Playing God of War with a controller feels seamless and intuitive. It’s clear this game was designed with a controller in mind, and it’s an absolute joy to play without the clunky feel of a keyboard and mouse. This is how gaming should be done.', TRUE, 1, 45, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 178 DAY)),
(1052, 5, 3, 'While ''God of War'' delivers a breathtaking narrative and stunning visuals, it regrettably falls into the age-old trap of neglecting the ultrawide community. The fixed field of view leaves much to be desired for someone who thrives on full immersion. The game world is vast and beautifully detailed, but the restricted FOV feels like peering through a tunnel rather than truly experiencing the scale of Midgard in its full panoramic glory.', TRUE, 0, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 227 DAY)),
(1032, 5, 5, 'The intricacies of ''God of War''s'' plot are a delight for anyone with a penchant for narrative mystery. The game beautifully weaves Norse mythology with a personal story of discovery and redemption. The vague elements of its plot act like an ancient tapestry, inviting players to unravel its secrets, bask in its rich lore, and delve into its mythic depths. Each clue leaves a tantalizing thread that beckons exploration.', TRUE, 0, 42, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 48 DAY)),
(1008, 5, 5, 'Having followed the development of ''God of War'' from its early stages, I am thoroughly impressed with the final product. The attention to detail, especially in the seamless integration of combat mechanics and narrative, is a testament to the developers'' passion. Kratos'' journey is both epic and intimate, delivering a cohesive experience that feels polished and engaging from start to finish.', TRUE, 9, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 153 DAY)),
(1049, 5, 2, 'Despite the overwhelming hype surrounding ''God of War'', my experience was marred by expectations that weren''t quite met. Yes, the game is visually stunning, but I couldn''t shake off the feeling that the gameplay was somewhat repetitive. The combat, while initially exciting, didn''t evolve as much as I hoped, leading to a sense of monotony after extended play sessions.', FALSE, 4, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 318 DAY)),
(1034, 5, 5, 'From the moment I accessed the early builds of ''God of War'', I could sense it was something special. The evolution of its mechanics throughout development showcased the team''s commitment to refining every aspect of the game. Finally experiencing the complete journey was overwhelmingly satisfying; a true testament to the potential I saw from the start. It''s a masterpiece that validates not only my investment but the anticipation of a stellar final product.', TRUE, 3, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 152 DAY)),
(1017, 5, 5, 'As a connoisseur of customization, I must say that God of War impresses. I love how the developers have provided a plethora of customizable options for Kratos and his gear. From weapon upgrades to skill trees, the depth is immense. It''s like they designed it with people like me in mind. Every aspect of the game can be tailored to fit your playstyle, making it a delightful experience to tweak and perfect my setup. Easily worth every penny spent on those DLC embelishments!', TRUE, 20, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 237 DAY)),
(1020, 5, 1, 'God of War, more like God of Dull. I understand the price tag aims to reflect the supposed revolutionary gameplay, but honestly, it''s not worth it. The story drags on, and the gameplay feels repetitive. It seemed like a decent buy at first, but after diving into it, I just don''t see the value. Why pay a premium for something that doesn''t deliver a consistent WOW factor? I found myself sighing more than smiling. Refund initiated.', FALSE, 18, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 23 DAY)),
(1045, 5, 2, 'I expected a graphical masterpiece from God of War, but what I got was a game that looks like it''s stuck in the previous generation. The textures and engine feel dated, which is quite disappointing. Sure, some of the cutscenes are stunning, but when you''re in control, the graphics fail to impress the way a modern game should. It detracts from the overall experience and ruins the immersion. It''s a shame, really.', FALSE, 1, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 85 DAY)),
(1010, 5, 3, 'God of War is enjoyable, but the lack of challenging modes is frustrating. Even the hardest difficulty doesn''t seem to push me to my limits. As someone who thrives on competitive and skill-intensive games, I find the hand-holding in the main story to detract from the overall experience. I wish they included more intense modes that truly test the player''s abilities. For now, it''s a good game, but it could be great with more of a challenge.', TRUE, 8, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 78 DAY)),
(1018, 5, 2, 'As a Linux user, I''ve learned to expect some compatibility issues, but God of War takes it to a new level with its invasive anti-cheat system. It creates unnecessary hurdles for those of us running alternative operating systems. The anti-cheat feels overly aggressive, to the point of impacting performance and playability. Devs should recognize and respect the Linux community more, instead of treating us like second-class gamers. Very disappointing.', FALSE, 11, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 310 DAY)),
(1056, 5, 4, 'God of War, while not quite reaching the punishing heights of a Souls game, still provides a decent challenge, especially on the harder difficulties. The combat is fluid and rewarding, demanding precision and strategy from players. I enjoyed the way the game tests your skill, though a bit more complexity in the enemies'' attack patterns would''ve been a cherry on top. Overall, it''s a solid experience for those who appreciate a good fight, but fear not – it won''t break your spirit like a Souls title.', TRUE, 3, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 329 DAY)),
(1007, 5, 4, 'God of War is a visually impressive game with an engaging story and polished gameplay. As someone who gets easily overwhelmed by the latest releases, I wasn''t entirely sure what to expect. However, the game is straightforward, without the need for excessive side quests or forced online interaction. I found it to be a refreshing break from the ongoing pressure to play everything new. It''s a fantastic game, even for those of us who just want to enjoy a single player adventure without feeling like we''re missing out on something else.', TRUE, 19, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 324 DAY)),
(1054, 5, 5, 'The soundscapes of God of War are truly spectacular. From the haunting melodies to the thunderous roars of combat, every sound is crisp and meticulously crafted. The dynamic range of the audio adds layers to the storytelling, creating an immersive experience that resonates deeply. The detailed audio cues enhance the gameplay and make every moment feel alive. As an audiophile, it''s pure bliss to witness a game where sound design is given such attention. The artistry in the acoustics alone is worth the journey.', TRUE, 3, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 329 DAY)),
(1029, 5, 5, 'I have to admit, I was skeptical about God of War at first, given its upfront cost. As someone who thrives on free-to-play games, I anticipated encountering paywalls, but to my delight, this game is refreshingly devoid of them. Once you own it, you''re in for the full ride, no hidden costs lurking around the corner. This game respects your purchase, offering a rich and complete experience without trying to nickel and dime you along the way. It''s a rare find these days and much appreciated for it.', TRUE, 0, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 115 DAY)),
(1057, 5, 3, 'God of War is a masterpiece in many aspects, but for someone who loves to tinker, it lacks the modding freedom I''m usually drawn to. The game files are pretty locked up, leaving little room for modding creativity. Despite this drawback, the craftsmanship in the game''s design is undeniable. I would love to see a future where such a rich universe is opened up for community-driven modifications. Until then, I can admire it for what it is – a beautifully crafted story and gameplay experience.', TRUE, 3, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 226 DAY)),
(1036, 5, 5, 'As someone who values every penny spent, waiting for a sale was the right choice. ''God of War'' delivers an epic experience with breathtaking visuals and a compelling father-son story. The price drop made the purchase feel like a steal for the quality received. Absolutely satisfied with the value it offers now.', TRUE, 3, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 190 DAY)),
(1031, 5, 5, 'Though my focus is usually on stacking up those achievements, ''God of War'' offered a refreshing break from the grind. The game is single-player bliss without any pesky multiplayer achievements to worry about. The narrative and world-building kept me hooked all the way to the final trophy.', TRUE, 9, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 17 DAY)),
(1053, 5, 5, 'Conquering ''God of War'' was a satisfying journey. The game respects the lone player experience, allowing me to focus on the story and collect trophies without the distraction of multiplayer tasks. It''s a well-crafted masterpiece for achievement hunters who prefer a solo quest.', TRUE, 14, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 262 DAY)),
(1016, 5, 5, 'Playing ''God of War'' on my Steam Deck was an incredible experience. The game''s performance and immersive graphics are fully verified and optimized for the device. It plays seamlessly docked or handheld, making it a must-have for any Steam Deck owner looking for a top-tier adventure game.', TRUE, 16, 33, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 237 DAY)),
(1021, 5, 5, '''God of War'' brings the perfect challenge that I crave as a Souls veteran. The combat is deeply rewarding and requires strategic thinking, especially on higher difficulties. It pushes players to their limits and delivers a satisfying sense of accomplishment with every victory.', TRUE, 6, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 147 DAY)),
(1001, 6, 5, 'Hades is a speedrunner''s paradise! The smooth mechanics and quick restart options make it perfect for anyone looking to beat their best time. Plus, there are just enough glitches to keep things interesting and add that extra layer of strategy when aiming for the fastest escape possible. Truly a masterpiece in efficient gaming!', TRUE, 31, 45, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 339 DAY)),
(1023, 6, 5, 'Hades offers an exhilarating blend of speed and precision. As a speedrunner, I thrive on the small glitches and shortcuts that this game presents. Every run feels fresh with new strategies and the challenge of breaking my own records. It''s a perfect game to showcase one''s speedrunning prowess!', TRUE, 0, 50, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 346 DAY)),
(1017, 6, 5, 'As someone who loves customization, Hades truly shines with its plethora of weapon upgrades and ability combinations. Each run feels unique, and I can tailor my gameplay to suit my ever-changing play style. It''s a delight to experience such depth and variety in customization.', TRUE, 3, 26, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 29 DAY)),
(1038, 6, 4, 'Hades is a thrilling experience but would be even better with improved controller support. While the game plays well, I found navigating through intense battles more challenging than it needed to be when using a controller. For peak enjoyment, I’d recommend some tweaks for those who prefer controllers over keyboard/mouse setups.', TRUE, 0, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 36 DAY)),
(1026, 6, 5, 'Hades is a refreshingly pure gaming experience, devoid of the modern monetization tactics that plague so many new releases. It reminds me of old-school games where skill and strategy are the key to progress, rather than microtransactions. A must-play for anyone longing for a genuine gaming experience.', TRUE, 11, 37, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 103 DAY)),
(1050, 6, 5, 'As an avid Achievement Hunter, Hades really hits the mark with its well-crafted and challenging set of achievements. Not a single multiplayer achievement in sight, which is just how I like it! The objectives are all skill-based, giving me plenty of solo challenges to master. It''s a paradise for Achievement Hunters who love the chase of single-player conquest.', TRUE, 28, 31, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 266 DAY)),
(1058, 6, 1, 'While the gameplay of Hades might be universally praised, I can''t get over the lack of a demo. As someone who values my refund policy, I found myself yearning for more information before making a purchase. Without a chance to test the waters, I''m compelled to give it a cautious rating.', FALSE, 9, 53, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 302 DAY)),
(1033, 6, 3, 'Coming from a QA Tester background, I found Hades to be exceptionally polished for a roguelike. No noticeable bugs or glitches disrupted my experience, and every run felt smooth and responsive. It''s clear that a lot of care and testing went into the development process to maintain this level of quality.', TRUE, 0, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 184 DAY)),
(1016, 6, 4, 'Playing Hades on my Steam Deck was a seamless experience with it being fully verified. The controls are intuitive, and the game runs brilliantly whether docked or on the go. This kind of optimization is exactly what I look for in my Deck library.', TRUE, 0, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 187 DAY)),
(1024, 6, 5, 'The enigmatic plot of Hades, steeped in Greek mythology, kept me engaged as I pieced together the lore through each character interaction. The subtlety and depth of the storyline make it a treasure trove for those who love unraveling cryptic narratives. It''s an epitome of storytelling that''s not spoon-fed but discovered.', TRUE, 10, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 361 DAY)),
(1043, 6, 3, 'ExterminateError (The QA Tester): Neutral. Hades is a well-polished game but has minor bugs that affect the seamless experience. The controls and UI are solid, yet I found a few graphical glitches that could use some attention. Overall, it provides a stable gameplay environment, but there''s always room for improvement.', TRUE, 60, 47, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 230 DAY)),
(1010, 6, 4, 'CompetitorCrusader (The Competitive Tryhard): Hades is challenging yet satisfying, though I''m disappointed with any sign of easier gameplay settings. The combat is brisk and punishing as it should be, but I''d prefer if the game didn''t cater to casual players, even slightly. Keep the difficulty savage, just the way I like it.', TRUE, 5, 49, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 286 DAY)),
(1054, 6, 5, 'WaveformWizard (The Audiophile): The sound design in Hades is phenomenal. From the dynamic range of the soundtrack to the crisp sound effects, every audio element is crafted to perfection. It''s an auditory feast that complements the intense action, making the entire experience even more immersive.', TRUE, 4, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 240 DAY)),
(1027, 6, 5, 'TaskMaster3000 (The Achievement Hunter): I love the single-player achievements that test skill and dedication in Hades, but I appreciate that there''s no unnecessary multiplayer clutter. It makes the hunt for complete achievement mastery focused and more satisfying.', TRUE, 0, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 311 DAY)),
(1034, 6, 5, 'EarlyAccessAce (The Alpha Tester): Invested. Having followed Hades since its early access days, I''ve seen it grow into a masterpiece. The developers'' commitment to improvement and community feedback has been inspiring. The final product is polished and engaging, a testament to its evolutionary journey.', TRUE, 1, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 221 DAY)),
(1012, 6, 3, 'As a QA Tester, I must commend Hades for its polish. The game is almost bug-free, which is rare these days. The developers clearly put in the effort to ensure a smooth experience, even as you dive into the depths of hell. However, it''s a bit too repetitive for my taste in the long run, but mechanically it''s a solid piece of work. If only more games were this well-optimized out of the gate.', TRUE, 0, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 246 DAY)),
(1051, 6, 2, 'I can''t stand games that push paywalls, and while Hades doesn''t have those egregious microtransactions, I found myself feeling the grind. It''s a rogue-like, so I get the design, but I couldn''t help but feel that more could have been accessible to someone playing for free. Still, at least they didn''t gatekeep content behind real money, which is a blessing nowadays.', FALSE, 0, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 295 DAY)),
(1030, 6, 3, 'Being an ultrawide user, I''m constantly frustrated by games that don''t support my monitor setup, but Hades handles it decently. Yet, the fixed field of view is annoying when I''ve got such a widescreen to maximize my gaming real estate. It''s immersive enough with stunning visuals, but I can''t help but feel a bit confined by the rigid FOV. It''s good, but not perfect for ultrawide enthusiasts.', TRUE, 14, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 263 DAY)),
(1056, 6, 5, 'As a veteran of souls-like games, I crave difficulty, and Hades delivers just the right amount. The challenge is fair but brutal, and learning enemy patterns is rewarding. It''s not as dark and punishing as some of my favorites, but the difficulty level is well-balanced for those who seek a true test of skill. Each death is a lesson, and each victory is a triumph.', TRUE, 10, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 121 DAY)),
(1011, 6, 3, 'Initially, I jumped onto the hype train for Hades, but after sinking several hours, I found myself somewhat disillusioned. The game is good, don''t get me wrong, with its clean art style and engaging narrative. However, beneath the surface, it didn''t quite live up to the astronomical expectations built up by the community. It''s a solid game, but I just couldn''t shake the feeling that it wasn''t the groundbreaking experience everyone made it out to be.', TRUE, 20, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 18 DAY)),
(1031, 6, 5, 'Hades is a paradise for achievement hunters like me! No annoying multiplayer achievements to worry about, just a slew of challenging and satisfying achievements that kept me coming back for more runs. Each escape attempt feels rewarding and there''s always a new relic or weapon aspect to unlock. The sense of progression is perfectly balanced, making this a must-play for anyone who relishes completing a game to 100%.', TRUE, 0, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 83 DAY)),
(1005, 6, 5, 'Hades strikes the perfect balance for an achievement hunter, offering a wide variety of tasks that cater to both skill and strategy. The absence of multiplayer achievements is a huge relief, allowing me to focus on mastering each weapon and fighting through the layers of the Underworld without any external distractions. I enjoyed the challenge of unlocking every aspect and collectible, making this game a rewarding experience from start to finish.', TRUE, 22, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 112 DAY)),
(1007, 6, 4, 'As someone prone to the fear of missing out, Hades surprisingly hasn''t stressed me out. The game is designed so well that returning after a break feels welcoming rather than overwhelming. The regular updates and new content drops are perfectly paced, keeping the experience fresh without feeling like I’m missing out drastically if I take a break. The gameplay loop is engaging, making the Underworld an exciting place to revisit.', TRUE, 21, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 117 DAY)),
(1032, 6, 5, 'For a lore lover like myself, Hades is an absolute delight! The story unfolds with every run, and the mysterious narrative keeps me piecing together the rich tapestry of Greek mythology and Zagreus''s personal journey. Each character interaction reveals more layers, and the ambiguous plot elements only deepen my interest. It’s a game where every dialogue is a puzzle piece to the grand narrative, and I absolutely love the immersive storytelling.', TRUE, 5, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 215 DAY)),
(1047, 6, 5, 'Hades delivers a remarkably smooth experience, which is crucial for a performance purist. The game runs seamlessly even during the most intense, action-packed moments, showcasing impressive optimization. The responsive controls and fluid animations ensure that every dash and attack is executed precisely as intended. In a world filled with games struggling with performance issues, Hades stands out as a benchmark of technical excellence.', TRUE, 10, 32, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 212 DAY)),
(1035, 6, 4, 'DebuggingDynamo (The QA Tester): After thoroughly testing Hades, my experience was largely positive, but not without a few hiccups. The game runs smoothly and is impressively free from major bugs. However, I did encounter occasional frame rate drops and clipping issues, particularly in intense combat scenarios. It''s a well-built game, but there''s always room for improvement. Overall, it''s a polished product that stands out for its attention to detail.', TRUE, 7, 119, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 365 DAY)),
(1055, 6, 4, 'TimeMachine (The Nostalgia Goggles): Hades offers a captivating gameplay loop reminiscent of classic titles, but I''m not a fan of modern monetization strategies being absent here. Thankfully, Hades avoids microtransactions, allowing you to enjoy the game in its entirety once purchased. It stays true to the essence of older games, where skill and progression are genuinely earned. It gives me hope that other contemporary games will follow this example.', TRUE, 5, 31, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 273 DAY)),
(1019, 6, 5, 'DarkSoulsDisciple (The Souls Veteran): If there''s one thing I adore, it''s a game that challenges my skills relentlessly, and Hades delivers on that front. The difficulty curve is finely tuned, offering a rewarding experience with every attempt. Like in Dark Souls, each failure is a step closer to mastering the game. It''s a thrilling ride filled with intense combat and learning opportunities at every turn. A must-play for anyone who enjoys testing their limits.', TRUE, 25, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 18 DAY)),
(1036, 6, 4, 'PatientPurchaser (The Wait for Sale): Hades is undoubtedly a fantastic game, but as someone who carefully considers cost, I found it a bit steep at launch price. That said, I waited for a sale and was pleasantly surprised by the value it offered for the money spent. The replayability and depth justify the purchase, especially when discounted. It''s worth the patience if you''re like me and prefer to wait for a bargain.', TRUE, 5, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 15 DAY)),
(1014, 6, 5, 'PenguinPlayer (The Linux User): As a Linux enthusiast, finding a game like Hades that runs smoothly on my system is a rare delight. However, I am cautious about anti-cheat implementations that could harm performance or privacy. Thankfully, Hades sidesteps these concerns, providing a seamless gaming experience without invasive anti-cheat software. It''s refreshing to enjoy a game without compromising on my platform''s principles.', TRUE, 12, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 289 DAY)),
(1040, 6, 5, 'Getting Hades as a gift was like receiving an unexpected treasure. The vibrant art style and the compelling narrative were bound tightly together in a package I never knew I wanted. The underworld setting is both richly detailed and creatively imagined, making each escape attempt feel fresh and exciting. A perfect gift that keeps on giving with each playthrough!', TRUE, 16, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 51 DAY)),
(1057, 6, 5, 'Hades is a modder’s playground. The game’s structure and open files offer so much potential for tweaks and enhancements. From minor cosmetic changes to more profound gameplay modifications, the community and I have found countless ways to alter and improve the experience. Supergiant’s support for the modding community only adds to this incredibly welcoming environment.', TRUE, 0, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 147 DAY)),
(1022, 6, 5, 'As someone who thrives on challenge, Hades delivered in spades. The game''s difficulty curve is expertly balanced, offering just the right amount of punishment to keep you coming back for more. Each boss fight pushes your skills to the limit, demanding both strategy and reflexes. Overcoming those intense battles is immensely rewarding, and keeps my adrenaline pumping.', TRUE, 3, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 104 DAY)),
(1052, 6, 3, 'Hades, a fantastic game marred by a frustratingly rigid field of view. The narrative and gameplay loop is captivating, but the inability to adjust the FOV to fully appreciate the ultrawide setup is disappointing. Navigating through hordes of enemies can feel overly cramped, leading to a less immersive experience on bigger screens.', TRUE, 7, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 358 DAY)),
(1045, 6, 4, 'From a graphics standpoint, Hades possesses an undeniable charm, but the underlying engine does feel a bit dated. The stylized art is beautiful, yet sometimes lacks the sharpness and fidelity of more modern engines. Despite this, the game''s aesthetic does manage to shine through, though it''s hard to ignore the longing for a touch more visual polish.', TRUE, 2, 38, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 307 DAY)),
(1044, 7, 5, 'As an ultrawide user, I''m often disappointed by games that lock you into a narrow field of view. Thankfully, Hollow Knight nails it with a breathtakingly immersive visual experience that fully utilizes my monitor''s potential. Every cavern and corner feels vast and infinite. It’s a visual treat for those who appreciate seeing more. Bravo, devs!', TRUE, 11, 25, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 164 DAY)),
(1054, 7, 5, 'The sound design in Hollow Knight is a symphony of atmospheric perfection. From the subtle hum of eerie caves to the crescendo of boss battles, the audio envelops you in the world. The dynamic range is spot on, making every area unique and alive. An audiophile''s dream come true.', TRUE, 3, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 232 DAY)),
(1059, 7, 1, 'One star, because Hollow Knight was a complete headache for me. I thought I''d get a straightforward refund when I realized it''s not my type of game, but nope! The refund policy wasn''t as flexible as I''d hoped. Too much platforming and not enough accessibility options to keep me hooked.', FALSE, 11, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 95 DAY)),
(1031, 7, 5, 'Hollow Knight offers an incredible array of achievements and explorative challenges. Thankfully, no multiplayer requirements to encroach on the experience. As an achievement hunter, I found pure joy in unraveling every secret at my own pace without worries about group dynamics.', TRUE, 3, 50, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 1 DAY)),
(1008, 7, 5, 'I was sold on Hollow Knight the moment I witnessed its pre-beta phase. The early build showed immense promise, and the final release exceeded expectations. The depth and polish after such testing phases are commendable. The developers truly listened, making it a standout entry in the Metroidvania genre.', TRUE, 7, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 227 DAY)),
(1016, 7, 5, 'DeckDockedDevotee (The Steam Deck User): Hollow Knight runs like a dream on the Steam Deck. This game is a perfect match for the device, with tight controls, stunning visuals, and just the right mix of challenge and exploration. It''s a verified title that truly showcases what handheld PC gaming can deliver. A must-play on the go.', TRUE, 0, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 183 DAY)),
(1012, 7, 4, 'BugHunterBeta (The QA Tester): Hollow Knight is solid in its design, with very few bugs, which is impressive given its intricate world. I didn''t encounter any game-breaking issues, just occasional pathfinding quirks from enemies. The attention to detail shows, and the experience is quite polished overall. A quality Metroidvania experience.', TRUE, 5, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 298 DAY)),
(1048, 7, 5, 'AchievementUnlocked (The Achievement Hunter): I''m thrilled that Hollow Knight doesn''t push multiplayer achievements. It’s refreshing to focus on personal skill and exploration without the need for online play. Achievements here are challenging yet fair, rewarding persistence and skill. It''s a single-player triumph.', TRUE, 13, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 154 DAY)),
(1026, 7, 5, '8BitAdmirer (The Nostalgia Goggles): Hollow Knight captures the essence of classic platformers with no modern monetization gimmicks. It feels like a return to the golden era of gaming. You pay once and have the complete package, pure gaming joy with no microtransactions in sight. A nostalgic masterpiece.', TRUE, 26, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 194 DAY)),
(1009, 7, 5, 'OptimusOptimiser (The RPG Min-Maxer): The complexity of Hollow Knight''s charm and skill system is deeply satisfying. Optimizing loadouts and strategies against different bosses provides a rich, engaging experience that rewards experimentation and skill mastery. A deep, complex game worth diving into.', TRUE, 2, 38, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 282 DAY)),
(1052, 7, 4, 'Hollow Knight on an ultrawide monitor offers breathtaking visuals that make you feel truly immersed in its mysterious world. However, the fixed Field of View can make the experience feel a bit cramped, especially in intense combat scenes. Still, the stunning art direction makes up for it.', TRUE, 13, 35, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 29 DAY)),
(1032, 7, 5, 'As a lore junkie, Hollow Knight''s subtle storytelling through environmental clues and cryptic NPC dialogues is a delight. The game masterfully weaves its story through exploration, rewarding those who seek understanding with profound satisfaction.', TRUE, 9, 25, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 135 DAY)),
(1018, 7, 5, 'Running Hollow Knight on Linux was a smooth experience without any anti-cheat software hindrance. It’s a beautifully crafted game that respects the open-source community, and the customization options are a big plus.', TRUE, 6, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 145 DAY)),
(1014, 7, 5, 'Hollow Knight performs remarkably well on Linux, with no pesky anti-cheat issues to worry about. The game delivers a rich and challenging experience that feels right at home on an open-source system.', TRUE, 22, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 166 DAY)),
(1040, 7, 5, 'Hollow Knight was gifted to me, and it was a fantastic surprise! The art style is charming, and the difficulty curve keeps things engaging. It''s a gem of a game that''s both challenging and rewarding.', TRUE, 18, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 189 DAY)),
(1050, 7, 5, 'As an achievement hunter, Hollow Knight is a breath of fresh air. The achievements are challenging yet fair, and thankfully, there''s not a single pesky multiplayer achievement in sight. This game respects solo players, and the sense of accomplishment after unlocking each achievement is immensely satisfying. A must-play for completionists like me!', TRUE, 3, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 327 DAY)),
(1047, 7, 4, 'Although Hollow Knight is a masterclass in design and atmosphere, I couldn''t help but notice some optimization issues, particularly when loading new areas. The frame rate drops occasionally disrupt the otherwise immersive experience. A few tweaks could make it perfect for performance purists.', TRUE, 13, 83, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 108 DAY)),
(1001, 7, 5, 'Hollow Knight is a paradise for speedrunners! The game''s mechanics allow for some incredible skips and shortcuts if you know where to look. I love discovering new glitches that shave seconds off my time. It''s a beautifully crafted game that rewards those who look beyond the surface.', TRUE, 34, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 163 DAY)),
(1051, 7, 5, 'As much as I love a good free-to-play deal, Hollow Knight impressed me with its complete package. No paywalls, no microtransactions, just pure gaming bliss. It''s a refreshing change to find a game that offers so much content upfront without hiding anything behind a paywall.', TRUE, 3, 25, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 326 DAY)),
(1043, 7, 4, 'Hollow Knight is an incredibly polished experience. The game world is meticulously crafted, and the attention to detail is phenomenal. While I didn''t encounter any major bugs, the game occasionally has minor quirks, but nothing game-breaking. A solid experience that showcases what indie games can achieve.', TRUE, 17, 53, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 130 DAY)),
(1042, 8, 5, 'As a seasoned Souls veteran, I found the challenging gameplay of Celeste to be refreshingly brutal yet fair. Scaling the mountain felt like conquering Ornstein and Smough all over again! Each death was a lesson learned, and the satisfaction of overcoming each section was unmatched. A must-play for those who crave a genuine test of skill!', TRUE, 5, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 26 DAY)),
(1018, 8, 4, 'While I generally avoid games with invasive anti-cheat systems, Celeste manages to shine without resorting to such measures. It respects the player''s freedom and integrity, focusing instead on pure, skill-based challenges. As a Linux user, this is a game I can stand behind—no unnecessary background processes, just pure platforming excellence.', TRUE, 2, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 47 DAY)),
(1029, 8, 5, 'Celeste is a breath of fresh air in a world full of microtransactions and aggressive monetization strategies. This game is a complete experience with no paywalls or additional purchases necessary to enjoy the full story. It''s a rare gem that puts gameplay first, allowing players to climb that mountain without their wallets taking a hit.', TRUE, 2, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 332 DAY)),
(1020, 8, 1, 'Honestly, I expected more from this game after reading all the rave reviews, but I just couldn''t get into it. Maybe I''m missing something, but the whole experience felt underwhelming. It didn''t click with me, and for that, I''m giving it just one star. It might be for some, but definitely not for everyone.', FALSE, 16, 39, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 33 DAY)),
(1034, 8, 5, 'I''ve been invested in Celeste since its early access phases, and seeing it evolve into the masterpiece it is today has been a journey of its own. The developers have poured their hearts into this game, and it shows. For anyone who values community feedback and developer transparency, Celeste is a shining example of what love and dedication can create.', TRUE, 14, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 119 DAY)),
(1055, 8, 5, 'As someone who misses the days before microtransactions and loot boxes, ''Celeste'' is a breath of fresh air. It''s a game that reminds me of the classics: simple yet challenging gameplay, beautiful pixel art, and an emotional story without any modern monetization tricks. ''Celeste'' succeeds in capturing the magic of gaming as it once was, making it a rare gem in today''s industry. Highly recommended for anyone longing for the golden age of gaming!', TRUE, 35, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 40 DAY)),
(1043, 8, 4, 'As a QA Tester, I approached ''Celeste'' with a focus on its mechanics and stability. The controls are tight and responsive, which is crucial for a precision platformer. The game offers a balanced level of challenge, and I encountered no significant bugs during my playthrough. Although it''s not mind-blowing, it delivers on what it promises, making it a solid experience.', TRUE, 0, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 164 DAY)),
(1036, 8, 5, 'I tend to be very cautious with my spending, and at first, I wasn''t sure if ''Celeste'' was worth the full price. However, after experiencing its heartfelt story and challenging gameplay, I can say it''s worth every penny. The game is frequently on sale, and I''d definitely recommend picking it up then if you''re price-sensitive like me. It''s a delightful bargain during those times!', TRUE, 9, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 102 DAY)),
(1007, 8, 5, 'I usually can''t resist new games due to FOMO, but ''Celeste'' managed to stand out even among the sea of options. Its critical acclaim piqued my interest, and the buzz was warranted. The game provides a satisfying challenge and emotional depth. It''s one of those rare titles that truly lives up to the hype, resonating with both casual gamers and hardcore enthusiasts.', TRUE, 23, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 12 DAY)),
(1005, 8, 5, 'As someone who despises multiplayer achievements, ''Celeste'' was a relief. It’s purely a single-player experience and focuses on creating a meaningful journey rather than unnecessary multiplayer goals. The achievements are well-designed and encourage thoughtful exploration and skillful play. If, like me, you prefer to hunt achievements without the hassle of multiplayer, ''Celeste'' is a must-play.', TRUE, 1, 32, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 202 DAY)),
(1016, 8, 5, 'Celeste runs like a dream on the Steam Deck. It''s verified, and it shows. The controls are spot-on, the performance seamless, and I can take the mountain climbing adventure anywhere. This game proves handheld gaming can be just as immersive and challenging as on any big screen setup. Perfect for on-the-go thrills without compromising quality.', TRUE, 3, 64, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 24 DAY)),
(1002, 8, 4, 'Celeste may not be an RPG, but its depth and complexity caught me by surprise. The psychological layers combined with the nuanced platforming mechanics make for an unexpectedly intellectually stimulating experience. Balancing Madeline’s physical and emotional journey resonates with the kind of intricate builds I''d enjoy in a min-max RPG setup.', TRUE, 2, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 158 DAY)),
(1000, 8, 5, 'Finally, a game that doesn''t lock progression behind a paywall! Celeste respects players by delivering its full experience upfront—no sneaky microtransactions here. It''s refreshingly honest, and the satisfaction comes from skill, not the size of your wallet. An open recommendation to all who despise pay-to-win mechanics.', TRUE, 13, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 129 DAY)),
(1037, 8, 5, 'Achieving everything in Celeste is a true test of skill. Thankfully, the single-player achievements focus purely on mastering the game''s mechanics rather than unnecessary multiplayer components. Each achievement feels earned, and collecting them offers a real sense of accomplishment.', TRUE, 13, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 139 DAY)),
(1017, 8, 4, 'While Celeste isn''t heavy on customization, the little touches such as custom assist modes and various accessibility features reveal a considered level of personalization that''s not always seen in games. It’s about tailoring the experience to your needs, and that’s a form of customization I can truly appreciate.', TRUE, 3, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 153 DAY)),
(1038, 8, 5, 'As someone who lives with a controller in hand, Celeste immediately clicked with me. The controls are super tight, and using my trusty gamepad felt like second nature. I can''t imagine trying to play this masterpiece with a keyboard and mouse - what a nightmare! Absolutely perfect for console lovers like me.', TRUE, 11, 60, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 149 DAY)),
(1015, 8, 5, 'Celeste on Linux is a dream come true. The game runs smoothly without any anti-cheat restrictions hampering my experience. I appreciate developers who respect the open-source community and provide full functionality without compromise. This game proves you can deliver an excellent platforming experience without alienating us Linux users.', TRUE, 5, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 295 DAY)),
(1040, 8, 4, 'I received Celeste as a gift and dove in without much expectation. What a delightful surprise it turned out to be! The challenging platforming and heartfelt story caught me off guard, and I ended up enjoying every moment. Sometimes the best things in life truly are unexpected gifts!', TRUE, 2, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 244 DAY)),
(1011, 8, 3, 'Oh, Celeste was so overhyped! Everyone painted it as the greatest indie platformer of all time. But when I played it, the frustration of difficult levels overshadowed any enjoyment the story and music could bring. It''s not terrible, but it just doesn''t live up to the whirlwind of hype surrounding it.', TRUE, 32, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 176 DAY)),
(1044, 8, 4, 'Playing Celeste on my ultrawide monitor felt cramped due to the fixed field of view. The game itself is visually gorgeous and mechanically sound, but the lack of FOV adjustment detracts from the immersive potential. If only they supported our wide-screened glory a bit better!', TRUE, 2, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 285 DAY)),
(1032, 9, 5, 'In Horizon Zero Dawn, the tapestry of lore is tantalizingly woven with threads of mystery. Every ancient ruin and tribal belief whispers fragments of a forgotten past, urging the curious to dig deeper. The plot is purposefully vague at times, echoing real archaeology where not all answers are readily found, leaving room for the imagination to fill the gaps. A must for lore enthusiasts who love unearthing secrets.', TRUE, 0, 43, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 186 DAY)),
(1034, 9, 4, 'Horizon Zero Dawn left me utterly immersed from the get-go. As an Alpha Tester, I''m always on the lookout for a game that captures my full attention, and this one nailed it. The open-world design is brilliantly executed and keeps you invested in both lore and gameplay. The fluid mechanics, coupled with intriguing quests, make it a rewarding experience from start to finish.', TRUE, 8, 32, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 314 DAY)),
(1042, 9, 4, 'As a Souls veteran, I thrive on challenging gameplay, and while Horizon Zero Dawn isn''t quite soulsborne-level in terms of difficulty, it provides its own brand of strategic combat that is both engaging and rewarding. The Thunderjaw and Stormbird face-offs require precise planning and execution, making it a satisfying challenge for those of us who crave a test of skill.', TRUE, 1, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 260 DAY)),
(1054, 9, 5, 'The sound design in Horizon Zero Dawn is top-notch, with a dynamic range that immerses you in the world like few others can. The way soundscapes shift from the quiet rustle of leaves to the booming roar of mechanical beasts is a testament to its high-quality audio engineering. It''s a treat for any audiophile who appreciates the nuances of sound in gaming.', TRUE, 17, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 249 DAY)),
(1031, 9, 5, 'Horizon Zero Dawn is a single-player masterpiece, and I''m thrilled that it keeps its achievements focused on personal accomplishments rather than multiplayer quests. The challenges are well-balanced and satisfying, without the frustration of needing friends to progress or complete objectives. A perfect score for respecting my preference for meaningful, solo achievement hunting.', TRUE, 5, 44, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 78 DAY)),
(1056, 9, 4, 'As a Souls veteran, I''m used to punishing difficulty, and while Horizon Zero Dawn doesn''t quite reach the brutal levels of a FromSoftware title, it does offer some challenging encounters, especially when facing off against the larger machines. The game''s combat requires a good mix of strategy and precision, which kept me engaged. However, I would have appreciated a higher difficulty setting for more of a challenge. Still, a solid experience for action and RPG fans alike.', TRUE, 10, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 31 DAY)),
(1009, 9, 4, 'For a min-maxer like myself, Horizon Zero Dawn offers a decent level of complexity with its skill trees and crafting systems. There’s a lot to optimize, whether it''s setting up the perfect loadout or tweaking your approach during combat. The game does a great job balancing between exploration and the thrill of combat. However, I wish there were more opportunities to exploit mechanics for those who like to dig deep into game systems.', TRUE, 40, 52, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 319 DAY)),
(1044, 9, 3, 'As an ultrawide user, it''s always frustrating when games don''t fully embrace flexible field of view settings. Horizon Zero Dawn mostly hits the mark, with impressive vistas that look stunning on a 21:9 monitor. But there are moments when the FOV feels a little too tight during intense battles, which can be a bit disorienting. Overall, the visual beauty of the world mostly makes up for this shortfall.', TRUE, 6, 34, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 111 DAY)),
(1011, 9, 3, 'I was hyped for Horizon Zero Dawn after all the buzz and, unfortunately, it didn’t quite live up to the expectations. The story, while intriguing at first, loses momentum halfway through, and some of the side quests felt repetitive. The game world is beautiful but the experience was not as groundbreaking as promised. A solid game, but perhaps not deserving of the extreme hype it received.', TRUE, 14, 63, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 23 DAY)),
(1040, 9, 4, 'I received Horizon Zero Dawn as a gift, and honestly, I didn’t know what to expect. Turns out, it''s a pretty captivating adventure. The graphics are stunning, and I found the combat engaging, especially with the variety of weapons available. I didn’t go into it looking for a masterpiece, but I came away pleasantly surprised. A great gift!', TRUE, 0, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 148 DAY)),
(1006, 9, 1, 'Horizon Zero Dawn seemed promising, but after a few hours, all I wanted was my money back. The open world felt lifeless, the quests were repetitive, and don''t get me started on the combat system - clunky and uninspiring. I can''t believe I spent my hard-earned cash on this disappointment.', FALSE, 5, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 99 DAY)),
(1023, 9, 4, 'I love finding glitches and Horizon Zero Dawn didn''t disappoint in that department! Clipping through walls and finding weird physics bugs added an extra layer of entertainment and challenge to my speedruns. Aloy and I took a few unexpected scenic detours, but that''s what kept me glued to the screen. Awesome experience overall!', TRUE, 6, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 117 DAY)),
(1003, 9, 5, 'I received Horizon Zero Dawn as a gift, and honestly, I didn’t know what to expect. To my surprise, I really enjoyed the stunning visuals and intriguing storyline. The mechanics were smooth, and it was a thrill exploring its vast landscapes. A random gift that turned out to be a great adventure!', TRUE, 18, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 126 DAY)),
(1053, 9, 5, 'As an achievement hunter, I was delighted to see that Horizon Zero Dawn respects single-player accomplishments without forcing unwanted multiplayer elements down my throat. I could fully immerse myself in Aloy''s journey without worrying about any annoying multiplayer trophies. The completionist in me is thoroughly satisfied!', TRUE, 2, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 184 DAY)),
(1051, 9, 5, 'Being a free-to-play enthusiast, I get edgy when games throw paywalls in my direction. Thankfully, Horizon Zero Dawn offers a complete experience without nickel-and-diming players. No real-cash transactions here - just pure gameplay! It''s refreshing to play a AAA game that respects the player''s wallet.', TRUE, 2, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 228 DAY)),
(1001, 9, 4, 'FastTrackFlash (The Speedrunner): I''ve been zipping through Horizon Zero Dawn at record pace and, oh boy, the glitches are gold! If you love breaking the game''s physics and finding those sweet shortcuts, this game has its moments. The speedrunning community has shared some insane skips that cut down hours of game time. A must-try for anyone looking to break the game in hacky ways!', TRUE, 0, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 334 DAY)),
(1041, 9, 5, 'LaunchDayLead (The Alpha Tester): As someone who invested over 100 hours exploring every nook and cranny, Horizon Zero Dawn delivers in both story and mechanics. From the responsive AI to the stunning environments, Guerrilla Games crafted a masterpiece. It''s been a long time since I''ve felt this connected to a game''s world and characters. Highly recommend for any committed player!', TRUE, 1, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 15 DAY)),
(1025, 9, 3, 'MissedOpportunity (The FOMO Victim): I didn''t catch the game when it first launched, but finally diving into it now, it''s a solid experience. Even if I missed the initial hype, Aloy''s journey is engaging enough to hold my interest, though I don''t feel the same urgency others did. A good game, but nothing earth-shattering.', TRUE, 23, 62, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 67 DAY)),
(1004, 9, 2, 'RetroRewind (The Nostalgia Goggles): What happened to just paying once and having everything unlocked? I hate how modern games like Horizon Zero Dawn sneak in monetization aspects or DLCs that feel crucial to the story. The game itself is fine, but this trend that accompanies modern releases really grinds my gears. 1990s, take me back!', FALSE, 13, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 290 DAY)),
(1037, 9, 5, 'MedalMatrix (The Achievement Hunter): Horizon Zero Dawn''s achievements were a joy to collect with no pesky multiplayer trophies to taint the journey. The satisfaction of reaching 100% completion was immense without the added stress of forced multiplayer. I finally found a game that understands my solo achievement hunting desires!', TRUE, 17, 33, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 34 DAY)),
(1057, 9, 4, 'As a modder, the open-world design of Horizon Zero Dawn is like a canvas begging for creativity. The game''s files, especially on PC, are refreshingly accessible. There’s ample room to play around with different mods and tweaks which makes diving back into the world a fresh experience each time. While the vanilla experience is solid, the potential for user-created content makes this game a staple on my hard drive.', TRUE, 2, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 342 DAY)),
(1048, 9, 4, 'Horizon Zero Dawn is a fantastic game, but I couldn''t help being a bit irritated by the lack of multiplayer achievements. As an achievement hunter, the single-player focus is great, but I often crave a challenge that involves outsmarting or outlasting another player. Still, the achievements are well-curated and offer a rewarding sense of completion, making it a worthwhile pursuit.', TRUE, 0, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 86 DAY)),
(1026, 9, 4, 'This game is a breath of fresh air, free from the clutches of modern monetization traps like loot boxes and excessive DLCs. It reminds me of the good old days when you could buy a game, play it, and unlock content just by playing. The aesthetics and mechanics hark back to the classics, but with a modern touch that enhances the experience without overcomplicating it. Horizon Zero Dawn is a gem in today’s gaming landscape.', TRUE, 31, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 279 DAY)),
(1008, 9, 5, 'As someone who spends a lot of time in pre-release testing, Horizon Zero Dawn was a revelation in polish and vision. The game felt robust and meticulously crafted, which shows the passion and investment from the developers. It’s a pleasure to play something that doesn''t require an immediate day-one patch to function properly. Looking forward to seeing what comes next from this franchise!', TRUE, 11, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 82 DAY)),
(1017, 9, 4, 'Customization is king for me, and Horizon Zero Dawn delivers beautifully. From crafting and evolving Aloy’s gear to the strategic choice of weapons and outfit modifications, the customization options keep me engaged for hours. I love fine-tuning my loadout for different encounters, and the visual customization allows a personal touch that makes the game feel like my own unique experience.', TRUE, 10, 34, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 63 DAY)),
(1010, 9, 3, 'As a hardcore competitor, Horizon Zero Dawn had me intrigued, but quickly the abundance of easy settings started to grate on my nerves. Sure, it''s visually stunning, but where''s the thrill if you can just breeze through it without breaking a sweat? The game does offer a higher difficulty setting, but even that felt like a walk in the park for a seasoned player like me. I expected more challenging AI tactics that force strategic play.', TRUE, 1, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 48 DAY)),
(1000, 9, 4, 'Horizon Zero Dawn is a beautiful game, but when I ran into resource-heavy areas that almost pushed me toward microtransactions, my interest began to wane. The game offers a lot of content, but wading through grind-heavy quests just to avoid spending real-world money tested my patience. However, I gotta give it to Horizon for not making it mandatory to pay to win, which is a big plus in my books.', TRUE, 4, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 263 DAY)),
(1002, 9, 5, 'For an RPG enthusiast like me, Horizon Zero Dawn delivers a rich tapestry of intricate mechanics. The crafting, skill trees, and strategic combat options kept me engaged for hours. The lore is deep and rewarding to explore, offering enough complexity to satisfy anyone who loves to dive deep into the details of their games. My only gripe would be the lack of true character stat customization, but otherwise, it''s a masterpiece.', TRUE, 7, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 101 DAY)),
(1022, 9, 4, 'As someone who relishes a punishing challenge, Horizon Zero Dawn''s combat can be enjoyable, but it often lacks the edge-of-your-seat difficulty I thrive on. Sure, taking down a Thunderjaw can be a test of skill, but overall, the game doesn''t quite push the limits like a true Souls game. Still, it''s definitely worth a playthrough for those looking for a moderate challenge.', TRUE, 10, 65, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 2 DAY)),
(1030, 9, 3, 'I was pretty pumped to explore a world as visually striking as Horizon Zero Dawn''s, but the lack of ultrawide support and a rigid FOV soured the experience. It''s a shame, really, because the landscapes deserve to be fully appreciated. With only limited tweakability, it feels like the game isn''t living up to its potential on a large screen. I hope they update it to allow more flexibility for ultrawide users.', TRUE, 14, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 271 DAY)),
(1012, 10, 3, 'As a QA tester, I found ''Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice'' to be an intriguing challenge. The game is polished with few bugs, which is impressive given its complexity. However, the learning curve can be steep. It''s well-made, but might not be for everyone. Neutral stance.', TRUE, 34, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 248 DAY)),
(1010, 10, 5, '''Sekiro'' stands out for its punishing difficulty, and I love that there''s no easy mode here to dilute the experience. It''s a true test of skill and perseverance, exactly what we competitive players crave. The lack of difficulty options keeps the integrity of the challenge intact. Excellent work.', TRUE, 0, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 31 DAY)),
(1016, 10, 5, 'Playing ''Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice'' on the Steam Deck was a dream. The game runs smoothly and looks fantastic on the handheld. It''s well-optimized and a joy to play anywhere. Verified and highly recommended for other Deck users.', TRUE, 10, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 56 DAY)),
(1022, 10, 5, 'As a Souls veteran, ''Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice'' hits all the right notes. The combat is tough but incredibly rewarding. It''s a different kind of hard compared to Souls games, focusing more on precision and timing, which keeps it fresh and exciting.', TRUE, 2, 29, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 197 DAY)),
(1031, 10, 5, 'I''m all about achievements, and ''Sekiro'' nails it with its satisfying trophy list. I''m thrilled there are no multiplayer achievements to worry about! The single-player focus means I can earn every trophy through skill and dedication.', TRUE, 5, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 340 DAY)),
(1000, 10, 2, 'As a free-to-play enthusiast, I was really hoping that ''Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice'' would offer some kind of pathway for us non-spenders. Alas, the game is sealed tight behind a paywall with no free content or trial mode to even sample the experience. The gameplay itself looks fantastic from what I''ve seen, but without a free version or significant discounts, it remains out of reach for those like me who aren''t willing to shell out full price. Such a missed opportunity for FromSoftware to expand their player base.', FALSE, 4, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 7 DAY)),
(1046, 10, 4, 'Sekiro is an absolute marvel in terms of gameplay and story. However, as someone who exclusively uses a controller, I must say that the experience was significantly less enjoyable due to the lack of proper optimization for gamepads. The controls felt a bit clunky compared to keyboard and mouse setups, which took away from the otherwise immersive experience. Still, the thrill of the combat kept me going, albeit with some minor frustrations.', TRUE, 18, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 77 DAY)),
(1001, 10, 5, 'As a speedrunner, Sekiro is a playground of possibilities. The game has several interesting glitches that can shave off valuable seconds during runs. From enemy AI exploits to out-of-bounds tricks, the game offers a wide range of challenges and opportunities for record-breaking. The beauty of Sekiro is that while mastering these glitches, you still have to be technically skilled, making each run a thrilling experience. Highly recommend it to anyone who loves pushing the limits of a game''s mechanics.', TRUE, 0, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 153 DAY)),
(1020, 10, 1, 'Extremely overhyped and overpriced! I can''t justify the cost of Sekiro, especially with its punishing difficulty that borders on absurd. The game isn''t friendly to newcomers, and without a refund option, you''re stuck with it after the first few hours. There are no shortcuts or assists for casual players, making it a dreadful experience for anyone not used to FromSoftware''s brutal style. If you''re looking for a relaxing gaming session, this is definitely not it.', FALSE, 0, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 82 DAY)),
(1006, 10, 1, 'I was utterly disappointed with ''Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice''. Given its steep price and no demo available, I took a gamble, hoping to enjoy something as captivating as ''Dark Souls''. However, the game is too demanding to be enjoyable. Its unforgiving difficulty left me frustrated more often than entertained. The lack of an easier mode or refund option is a dealbreaker. This one''s strictly for the hardcore fans. Save yourself the hassle if you''re not into punishing gameplay.', FALSE, 13, 42, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 156 DAY)),
(1036, 10, 4, 'I''ve always believed that good things come to those who wait and ''Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice'' was definitely worth waiting for a sale. The moment the price dropped, I didn''t hesitate to buy it, and I was not disappointed. The combat is challenging yet rewarding, and the graphics are top-notch. For anyone who''s price-sensitive like me, waiting to grab this on discount is a smart move. Absolutely thrilled with my purchase at a bargain price!', TRUE, 15, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 112 DAY)),
(1033, 10, 4, 'As someone who approaches games with a critical eye, I found ''Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice'' to be a well-crafted experience. The mechanics are solid, and I did not encounter any major bugs or performance issues. The learning curve is steep, but it’s designed to be that way, which adds to the satisfaction when you finally master it. Overall, it’s a polished game that lives up to its reputation.', TRUE, 10, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 25 DAY)),
(1055, 10, 3, 'Ah, the days when you purchased a game and had the whole package... ''Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice'' brings back some of that old-school challenge but thankfully avoids the modern pitfalls of excessive DLCs and microtransactions. With a single purchase, you get the complete experience. However, the difficulty might be a bit too punishing for those not used to older, challenging games.', TRUE, 3, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 357 DAY)),
(1017, 10, 4, 'Customization options in ''Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice'' are not as extensive as I usually prefer, but the game’s focus is clearly on mastering the combat and experiencing the story. While I typically enjoy games that let me spend hours tweaking every little detail, the intensity and pace of Sekiro kept me engaged regardless. It’s a different experience but one I found equally fulfilling.', TRUE, 10, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 13 DAY)),
(1058, 10, 1, 'Purchased ''Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice'' with high hopes, but it turns out this game is not for the faint-hearted. The difficulty spike is beyond anything I signed up for, which made me request a refund. If you’re someone looking for a casual gaming experience, tread carefully before buying. Can’t justify the cost for something that ended up being more frustrating than fun.', FALSE, 2, 68, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 256 DAY)),
(1008, 10, 5, 'As an Alpha Tester, I usually dive into games for the thrill of pioneering uncharted territories. Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice had me fully invested from start to finish. The challenge it provides is unparalleled, requiring strategy and precision. Every boss felt like a true test of skills, and the world-building was immersive, keeping me engrossed to uncover every secret. A fascinating experience for those who seek depth and complexity in gameplay.', TRUE, 7, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 91 DAY)),
(1023, 10, 4, 'TimeTrialTornado reporting in! Even though Sekiro doesn''t lend itself to typical speedrunning due to its complex mechanics, exploiting the game''s glitches was a blast! Discovering new skips and breaking the game apart has been one of my favorite pastimes. Whether it''s outsmarting bosses or finding ways to cut down the gameplay time, Sekiro has some fascinating quirks to play with.', TRUE, 3, 42, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 308 DAY)),
(1027, 10, 5, 'I''m all about perfecting games, so when I found out Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice had no multiplayer achievements, my heart soared! The achievements here are both challenging and rewarding, requiring a deep dive into its unforgiving yet fair mechanics. It''s refreshing to focus on a single-player journey without worrying about online competition. A must-play for anyone dedicated to achieving 100% completion.', TRUE, 31, 68, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 309 DAY)),
(1045, 10, 3, 'ResolutionRadical here, and while Sekiro offers stunning visuals, I still find it lacking due to its dated engine. The art direction is phenomenal, but the graphics don''t fully utilize modern hardware capabilities, leaving some environments looking lackluster. For those who crave cutting-edge graphics, Sekiro may not be the visual feast you''re hoping for, despite its engaging gameplay.', TRUE, 3, 42, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 337 DAY)),
(1015, 10, 2, 'As OpenSourceOverlord, my excitement for Sekiro took a nosedive upon discovering its anti-cheat measures. While I respect the intent, these systems often restrict the freedom Linux users cherish. It''s a shame because Sekiro''s gameplay is otherwise superb, and I would have loved to delve deeper into its samurai world without the heavy-handed restrictions.', FALSE, 1, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 331 DAY)),
(1009, 10, 5, 'As The RPG Min-Maxer, I found Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice to be a delightful challenge in its complexity. The skill tree offers meaningful choices that require strategic foresight, perfectly catering to my penchant for optimization. The combat mechanics demand precision and mastery, rewarding players who meticulously plan their approach. A true haven for those who enjoy unraveling intricate systems. 5/5 for complexity lovers.', TRUE, 8, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 72 DAY)),
(1013, 10, 4, 'GlitchGuru here, and from a QA perspective, Sekiro holds up well with minimal technical hiccups, though it does have its moments. The game delivers on tight gameplay and solid design, yet I felt the learning curve might be steep for newcomers. The lack of bugs is impressive, and the seamless experience is commendable. Overall, a balanced experience, but not without its frustrations, so I''d give it a 4/5.', TRUE, 6, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 243 DAY)),
(1051, 10, 3, 'FreeloaderKing speaking, and while I usually drift towards games that are more forgiving on the wallet, Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice stood out. Thankfully, this game doesn’t hide anything essential behind paywalls. However, the sheer difficulty might deter those looking for an easy win. No in-game purchases is a plus, but it''s still a brutal game if you''re not willing to put in the work. 3/5 from me.', TRUE, 7, 35, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 140 DAY)),
(1052, 10, 3, 'AspectRatioRenegade reporting in—while Sekiro’s aesthetics are breathtaking, I was disheartened by the rigid FOV that doesn’t fully accommodate my ultrawide setup. The lack of flexibility in view adjustment slightly detracts from the immersive experience I crave. The visuals are stunning, but I wish there was more support for customized setups. This is a solid game, but room for improvement bumps it to a 3/5.', TRUE, 12, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 224 DAY)),
(1021, 10, 5, 'ElderRingEmperor here, and let me just say, Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice is a masterclass in challenging gameplay. The difficulty is brutal yet fair, demanding precision and patience. It''s everything a Souls veteran dreams of—a relentless test of skill where every victory feels earned. The satisfaction of conquering a seemingly insurmountable foe is unparalleled. An exhilarating experience deserving of a 5/5.', TRUE, 3, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 307 DAY)),
(1035, 10, 3, 'Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice presents an intriguing scenario for a QA tester. The game''s intricacy is both a boon and a bane; on one hand, the tight mechanics and unique combat system pose a challenging test environment, while on the other, the occasional clipping issues and minor bugs can somewhat break immersion. Neutral overall, as the game offers an engaging testing ground but requires patience to navigate its issues.', TRUE, 2, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 167 DAY)),
(1041, 10, 5, 'As someone who''s been there since the first code lines, Sekiro is a thrilling ride from beginning to end. Its seamless blend of action and stealth, paired with the atmospheric world, draws you in, making it a game worthy of deep investment. Every boss battle feels like a momentous event, and mastering its complex systems is incredibly rewarding. Truly an unforgettable experience.', TRUE, 0, 24, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 40 DAY)),
(1002, 10, 5, 'Sekiro is a treasure trove for those who appreciate the art of optimization. The game''s systems are ripe for exploration and mastery, with its challenging combat demanding precision and strategic depth. The RPG elements are subtle but crucial, making every stat enhancement feel impactful. The complexity is where this game shines, and it''s a joy to unravel every layer.', TRUE, 12, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 141 DAY)),
(1004, 10, 3, 'Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice is a strange beast to tackle as a nostalgic gamer. On one hand, it''s a masterpiece of modern gaming design, but on the other, its lack of microtransactions is a refreshing nod to the past. However, the daunting difficulty spike can be a turn-off, feeling more like a punishment than a fun challenge at times. I appreciate its design but yearn for the simpler joys of yesteryear.', TRUE, 33, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 10 DAY)),
(1003, 10, 4, 'I got Sekiro as a random surprise gift, and, wow, it’s intense! I didn''t expect the game to be this challenging. The sword fights require precision, and I ended up dying countless times. While initially frustrated, the game''s beautiful visuals and rewarding nature kept me hooked. Not something I would have picked up myself, but I can see why it''s loved by many.', TRUE, 23, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 114 DAY)),
(1053, 11, 4, 'Dark Souls III is a treasure trove for achievement hunters like myself who revel in the thrill of earning every last trophy. While the single-player challenges are exquisitely painful and rewarding, I can''t help but dock a point for the multiplayer achievements that force me to venture into the online realm, an area I''m just not interested in. They shouldn''t be mandatory for completion!', TRUE, 16, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 53 DAY)),
(1027, 11, 4, 'Dark Souls III offers a plethora of achievements to chase, with intricate lore and brutal combat that demands precision and patience. However, the inclusion of multiplayer achievements feels unnecessarily intrusive to the otherwise solitary experience. It''s a slight detraction from an otherwise excellent game.', TRUE, 2, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 340 DAY)),
(1055, 11, 5, 'While wandering through the desolate world of Dark Souls III, I can''t help but reminisce over the days when games were complete at launch, not filled with modern monetization schemes. Fortunately, Dark Souls III mostly avoids these pitfalls, allowing me to immerse myself fully in its difficult yet captivating journey. It''s a reminder of gaming''s golden years.', TRUE, 1, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 134 DAY)),
(1043, 11, 4, 'As a QA tester, I find Dark Souls III to be a masterpiece of game design, despite its notorious difficulty. It''s well-polished with few noticeable bugs, which is always a plus. Still, the punishing gameplay may not be for everyone, but for those seeking a challenge, it''s definitely worth a try.', TRUE, 13, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 333 DAY)),
(1003, 11, 5, 'I received Dark Souls III as a gift, and I''m not sure what my friend was thinking! The game is challenging beyond belief, yet strangely addictive. I''ve died more times than I can count, but each time I learn something new. It''s an experience unlike any other, and I''m surprisingly grateful for it!', TRUE, 9, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 80 DAY)),
(1033, 11, 3, 'As a QA Tester, Dark Souls III has its share of bugs, but nothing game-breaking that I couldn''t work around. The challenging AI and level design impressed me, although some hit detection bugs were frustrating at times. Overall, a solid experience that just needs a tad more polish.', TRUE, 5, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 363 DAY)),
(1028, 11, 4, 'Using a controller for Dark Souls III is the only way to go. The keyboard/mouse combination feels clunky and makes the game unnecessarily difficult. The game itself is challenging, but in a satisfying way when played with a controller.', TRUE, 12, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 226 DAY)),
(1024, 11, 5, 'I adore the cryptic storytelling and the atmospheric world of Dark Souls III. Every item description and environmental detail adds layers to the lore. It''s a puzzle that invites you to uncover its secrets, and I can''t get enough of it.', TRUE, 25, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 201 DAY)),
(1018, 11, 2, 'The anti-cheat system in Dark Souls III is a bane for Linux users like myself. It often causes compatibility issues which detract from the overall experience. Fixing these issues would lead to a much smoother gameplay for us.', FALSE, 3, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 31 DAY)),
(1034, 11, 4, 'Having been an alpha tester for many titles, I appreciate the dedication to crafting such a hardcore experience. Dark Souls III feels polished and tight, though sometimes the difficulty spikes can feel like ''cheap deaths'' rather than fair challenges.', TRUE, 40, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 184 DAY)),
(1012, 11, 3, 'As a QA tester, Dark Souls III has its fair share of bugs, though none game-breaking. The mechanics are robust, and the combat is generally fluid despite occasional hitbox issues. Still, I spend more time debugging than being immersed—an occupational hazard, I suppose.', TRUE, 16, 72, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 162 DAY)),
(1025, 11, 3, 'I''d heard so much about Dark Souls III, so I feared missing out on something monumental. Turns out, I was right... kind of. While the challenge was there, I was left wondering if I had truly experienced anything groundbreakingly different from its predecessors. It’s good, just not the revelation I was expecting.', TRUE, 19, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 99 DAY)),
(1049, 11, 2, 'The hype around Dark Souls III was massive! Maybe that set my expectations too high. The game is challenging, sure, but it feels like it''s trying too hard to replicate the success of the first two. It just didn''t live up to the monumental anticipation for me.', FALSE, 2, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 260 DAY)),
(1047, 11, 2, 'Ugh, the optimization in Dark Souls III is frustrating! Frame rate drops and stuttering—how can anyone enjoy a game like this? It''s 2016; we deserve better performance. I can''t forgive such glaring issues in what should have been a seamless experience.', FALSE, 24, 23, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 247 DAY)),
(1004, 11, 3, 'Dark Souls III is a testament to how far we''ve come, but part of me longs for the simplicity of older games, before microtransactions and DLC were a staple. The game world is immersive, yet the modern approaches to monetization feel like an unwelcome intrusion.', TRUE, 3, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 347 DAY)),
(1006, 11, 1, 'Dark Souls III? More like Dark Souls ''Waste of Time'' III. I can''t believe I spent money on a game that seems to enjoy punishing players for even trying. Every corner hides an enemy waiting to cheap-shot you, and every death feels less like a challenge and more like a game bug. After dying for the hundredth time, I did the only reasonable thing: asked for a refund. 1-star for this soul-crushing experience!', FALSE, 4, 86, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 2 DAY)),
(1023, 11, 5, 'As a speedrunner, I live for the thrill of finding every possible glitch and exploit, and Dark Souls III delivers! I love how you can skip entire sections if you know the right tricks. Each run gets my adrenaline pumping, and discovering a new glitch is like finding buried treasure. This game might be tough, but breaking it in creative ways makes it incredibly rewarding!', TRUE, 14, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 237 DAY)),
(1029, 11, 4, 'Dark Souls III is a beautiful game, sure, but why can''t developers understand that some gamers just want to enjoy the core experience without constantly opening their wallets? This game avoids the pitfalls of paywalls, which is refreshing in today''s market. Even though it''s a full-priced game, there''s nothing but pure gameplay here. No hidden fees or microtransactions. Love it!', TRUE, 6, 78, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 17 DAY)),
(1046, 11, 3, 'I thought I''d give Dark Souls III a shot with a keyboard and mouse, but quickly realized my mistake. This game was clearly designed with a controller in mind, and using anything else is a nightmare. The controls felt clunky and unresponsive, and I often found myself getting clobbered due to awkward key bindings. If you''re playing this masterpiece, do yourself a favor and grab a controller!', TRUE, 0, 63, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 268 DAY)),
(1010, 11, 5, 'If there''s one thing I can''t stand, it''s when games hold your hand. Thankfully, Dark Souls III doesn''t pull any punches! Each boss fight and enemy encounter pushes you to your limits, and that''s what makes it exhilarating. No easy modes here, just pure, unadulterated challenge. If you want to test your mettle, this is the game for you!', TRUE, 23, 52, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 129 DAY)),
(1008, 11, 5, 'As an alpha tester deeply invested in game development, Dark Souls III represents a masterclass in immersive and challenging gameplay. The level design is intricately woven, offering a seamless blend of exploration and combat that keeps veteran players like myself engrossed. The difficulty curve, while steep, rewards persistence and strategic thinking. It''s a journey worth every moment for those who thrive on trial and error. 5/5 for its craftsmanship.', TRUE, 23, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 110 DAY)),
(1058, 11, 1, 'I was lured in by the hype but left disappointed. I expected an engaging experience, but the relentless difficulty felt like a deliberate ploy to frustrate casual gamers. Despite looking for a refund, I found myself trapped in justifications of ''game mechanics''. The graphics might be stellar, but they''re overshadowed by a lack of accessibility for the average player. 1/5 stars for the frustration it causes non-hardcore gamers.', FALSE, 0, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 197 DAY)),
(1015, 11, 2, 'Dark Souls III''s reliance on invasive anti-cheat measures is a concern for Linux users like myself. While I''m all for fair play, the lack of native support combined with anti-cheat issues hinders performance on alternative platforms. The community''s workaround options are limited, affecting the overall experience. Until these systemic issues are addressed, the game remains less accessible. 2/5 stars due to its platform limitations.', FALSE, 13, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 131 DAY)),
(1035, 11, 3, 'Testing games is my forte, and Dark Souls III offers a robust experience, albeit with some pitfalls. The mechanics are solid, but the learning curve could deter new players. While the game functions as intended, minor bugs occasionally break immersion. It''s an experience that deserves a playthrough, provided you''re willing to overlook these glitches. Neutral rating of 3/5, balancing strengths and areas for improvement.', TRUE, 8, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 52 DAY)),
(1052, 11, 2, 'Dark Souls III may be universally praised, but its lack of ultrawide support and rigid field of view options is a letdown. As an ultrawide user, I find it unacceptable that such a visually-driven game ignores modern display standards. The restricted FOV detracts from the immersive experience promised by its expansive world. 2/5 stars for ignoring essential display features.', FALSE, 11, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 261 DAY)),
(1020, 11, 1, 'I was hyped to play Dark Souls III but was let down by its punishing difficulty and lack of refund policy for digital games. The stress and frustration just aren''t worth the price! If only they offered a 2-hour trial period. NOT going to recommend.', FALSE, 3, 52, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 166 DAY)),
(1017, 11, 5, 'Dark Souls III lets you go wild with character customization. I spent hours just tweaking my armor and weapons to perfection. It''s brilliant how every piece of gear can change your playstyle. Absolute kudos for giving players this depth of choice!', TRUE, 1, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 172 DAY)),
(1054, 11, 5, 'The soundscape of Dark Souls III is a masterpiece. From the haunting orchestral score to the ambient noise in each area, the dynamic range is phenomenal. It truly immerses you in its dark world, elevating every boss fight to an epic encounter.', TRUE, 3, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 82 DAY)),
(1042, 11, 5, 'Finally, a game that doesn''t hold your hand! Dark Souls III delivers on its promise of a punishing yet rewarding experience. Each victory feels earned, and the sense of accomplishment is second to none. It''s a dream for anyone who thrives on a challenge!', TRUE, 29, 24, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 161 DAY)),
(1037, 11, 3, 'Dark Souls III is fantastic, but the multiplayer achievements? They are a real pain. I want to platinum this game, but getting these achievements rely on other players and sometimes their behavior is unpredictable. Single-player trophies should suffice!', TRUE, 42, 34, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 80 DAY)),
(1017, 13, 5, 'Ghost of Tsushima offers an incredible world to explore with an amazing array of customization options! As someone who loves diving deep into the aesthetics and functionality of every character I play, I was thrilled with the level of detail. From armor sets to weapon skins, there''s so much to choose from! Whether you''re looking to reflect your own style or optimize for combat, Sucker Punch nailed it. A must-have for any true collector and customization enthusiast!', TRUE, 3, 85, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 203 DAY)),
(1022, 13, 5, 'Finally, a game that respects the traditions of challenging combat! Ghost of Tsushima offers a tough yet fair experience that really tests your skills. The intricate combat system is reminiscent of the best Soulsborne games, requiring precise timing and strategic planning. Every duel feels like a real battle, pushing you to master the art of samurai swordplay. This is the kind of challenge that keeps seasoned veterans like me coming back for more!', TRUE, 4, 24, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 274 DAY)),
(1033, 13, 3, 'Ghost of Tsushima is an all-around solid game. The graphics are impressive, and the story is engaging enough to keep you invested. The combat system is well-designed, though it doesn''t break new ground. It''s a package that delivers what you''d expect from a game of its caliber. Nothing too groundbreaking, but definitely worth a play through.', TRUE, 14, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 138 DAY)),
(1020, 13, 1, 'I was expecting so much more for the price! The game offers a decent experience, but it''s nothing extraordinary. After a few hours, it felt repetitive, and the excitement just fizzled out. I really don''t see why this game is priced so high. There are better options out there that provide more innovation and value for money. Honestly, I''d rather get a refund.', FALSE, 17, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 142 DAY)),
(1009, 13, 5, 'The game presents a wonderfully complex system for those of us who thrive on in-depth mechanics and min-maxing opportunities. The skill trees and techniques offered in Ghost of Tsushima allow for various builds and strategies. It''s a joy to tweak and fine-tune my character''s abilities to achieve optimal performance in different combat scenarios. The balance between stealth and full-on combat provides a delightful challenge for strategic planning.', TRUE, 0, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 0 DAY)),
(1052, 13, 3, 'Ghost of Tsushima is a visually stunning game that tragically neglects the ultrawide community. As someone who savors every pixel of my panoramic screen, I felt boxed in by the rigid field of view. Sucker Punch, you''ve created a breathtaking world; please let us see more of it without those dreaded black bars! Otherwise, a masterpiece in atmosphere and combat.', TRUE, 0, 43, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 45 DAY)),
(1059, 13, 1, 'I was all set to dive into the tale of Tsushima, only to be met with frustration. Despite the beautiful graphics, the game offers nothing new in terms of innovation. The missions felt repetitive, and the stealth mechanics seemed straight out of an early 2000s game. For those seeking thrills, you might want to look elsewhere.', FALSE, 8, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 267 DAY)),
(1003, 13, 4, 'This game was a surprise birthday gift, and what a pleasant surprise it was! I loved exploring the vibrant landscapes and engaging in epic sword fights. It''s not typically the kind of game I''d pick for myself, but I''m definitely glad it found its way to my library!', TRUE, 6, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 154 DAY)),
(1025, 13, 3, 'I had heard so much about Ghost of Tsushima and couldn''t resist finally trying it. While I wouldn’t call it groundbreaking, the narrative kept me engaged, and the visuals were a feast for the eyes. A solid experience, though perhaps a bit overhyped.', TRUE, 26, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 146 DAY)),
(1038, 13, 5, 'Ghost of Tsushima feels like it was crafted with the console user in mind, and I loved every minute of it. The controls are perfectly tuned for the controller, offering a fluid and immersive experience. This is what gaming on a console is all about.', TRUE, 4, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 251 DAY)),
(1026, 13, 4, '8BitAdmirer (The Nostalgia Goggles): Ghost of Tsushima takes me back to the golden era of gaming! The visuals are stunning, reminiscent of classic samurai films, and the story is engaging without relying on modern monetization tactics. It''s a breath of fresh air to not be constantly bombarded with microtransactions, allowing players to fully immerse themselves in the beautiful world of Tsushima. A true homage to classic gaming experiences.', TRUE, 15, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 162 DAY)),
(1042, 13, 4, 'MNPSoulSlayer (The Souls Veteran): As a Soulslike enthusiast, the combat in Ghost of Tsushima was a delightful challenge. While not as punishing as some might hope, the skillful parrying and diverse enemy types kept me on my toes. The duels are a standout feature, offering a satisfying test of patience and precision. A bit more difficulty would have been ideal, but it’s still a rewarding journey for any seasoned gamer.', TRUE, 7, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 137 DAY)),
(1010, 13, 3, 'CompetitorCrusader (The Competitive Tryhard): Ghost of Tsushima suffers from an overly accessible approach, which might deter hardcore players looking for a tough nut to crack. The game is visually stunning and narratively rich, but an optional difficulty spike or more competitive elements would have enhanced the experience. For those seeking a challenging playground, it might fall short, but it remains a visually and thematically captivating journey.', TRUE, 18, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 294 DAY)),
(1048, 13, 5, 'AchievementUnlocked (The Achievement Hunter): The achievement list in Ghost of Tsushima is a completionist’s dream! With a perfect blend of story-driven tasks and explorative challenges, there are no multiplayer achievements to tarnish the single-player experience. Every trophy feels earnable and rewarding, allowing for a satisfying journey towards 100% completion without the need to hop into multiplayer.', TRUE, 0, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 41 DAY)),
(1028, 13, 5, 'JoystickJuggler (The Controller User): Playing Ghost of Tsushima with a controller feels intuitive and seamless. The controls are tight and responsive, making every sword swing and stealth maneuver feel natural. The game clearly caters to controller users, allowing for a comfortable and immersive experience without the hassle of keyboard and mouse configurations. A masterclass in controller optimization!', TRUE, 4, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 307 DAY)),
(1045, 13, 4, 'Ah, Ghost of Tsushima - a visual masterpiece that soothes the soul with its breathtaking landscapes and exquisite attention to detail. The use of lighting and color palettes in this game is second to none. However, the game engine does show its age during certain cutscenes where textures aren''t as sharp. Still, the overall visual experience is something to behold.', TRUE, 3, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 322 DAY)),
(1005, 13, 5, 'Ghost of Tsushima is a trophy hunter''s paradise with its well-designed achievement system. It''s a relief to find a game that doesn''t force you into multiplayer just to snag a platinum. The variety of challenges and tasks keep the single-player experience rewarding and engaging. This game respects solo players, exactly how it should be!', TRUE, 14, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 146 DAY)),
(1012, 13, 4, 'From a QA perspective, Ghost of Tsushima is polished with only minor bugs that hardly affect gameplay. The load times are pleasantly fast, and the frame rate remains stable throughout. It''s refreshing to play a game where the technical execution matches the creative ambition.', TRUE, 1, 42, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 268 DAY)),
(1006, 13, 1, 'One star! The hype around Ghost of Tsushima doesn''t match what I experienced. Yes, it looks pretty, but the gameplay quickly becomes repetitive. The exploration feels shallow, and the story didn''t hook me. I expected more for the price, so I hit that refund button faster than a samurai draw!', FALSE, 5, 43, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 309 DAY)),
(1035, 13, 4, 'Ghost of Tsushima offers a remarkably smooth experience with minimal technical hiccups. The team clearly put in the effort during development and testing. From the complex combat mechanics to the simple beauty of riding through Tsushima, the game delivers a reliable and enjoyable experience.', TRUE, 8, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 42 DAY)),
(1024, 13, 5, 'Ghost of Tsushima is an intriguing tapestry woven with the threads of myth and legend. The story is a delicate dance between the known and the ethereal, inviting players to delve deeper into the mysteries of Tsushima Island. Every side quest feels like a forgotten tale waiting to be unearthed, and the hauntingly beautiful setting is steeped in rich, enigmatic history. A true feast for those who revel in the subtle nuances of storytelling.', TRUE, 43, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 232 DAY)),
(1056, 13, 4, 'For those who thrive on the relentless challenge of a compelling battle system, Ghost of Tsushima does not disappoint. The duels require precision, patience, and a mastery of timing that can rival the intensity of Souls-like titles. The game’s difficulty curve is beautifully brutal, demanding a combination of strategic thinking and adaptability. It’s a journey worth undertaking for any seasoned warrior looking for a true test of skill.', TRUE, 4, 44, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 235 DAY)),
(1053, 13, 3, 'As someone who enjoys the thrill of chasing Platinum trophies, Ghost of Tsushima was an absolute delight—save for the multiplayer trophies, which felt like a detour from the otherwise immersive single-player experience. The comprehensive checklist of achievements, however, does offer a fulfilling journey to completion, minus the obligatory online commitments that detract from the solo narrative mastery.', TRUE, 4, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 254 DAY)),
(1008, 13, 5, 'Embarking on the adventure that is Ghost of Tsushima felt like stepping into a living, breathing world. It''s a meticulously crafted experience that showcases the potential of open-world design. The mechanics are refined, and the attention to detail is exemplary. While I did encounter a few minor bugs, they were nothing that detracted from the overall immersive experience and polish of the game.', TRUE, 2, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 140 DAY)),
(1023, 13, 4, 'Speedrunning Ghost of Tsushima presents a unique challenge that’s more about efficiency and the clever exploitation of its open-world physics than it is about sequence breaking. The game offers certain fun glitches that can be utilized to shave off precious minutes, making it a thrilling experience for those looking to tackle time-trial challenges with ingenuity and speed.', TRUE, 0, 82, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 110 DAY)),
(1013, 15, 3, 'As someone who spends hours scouring for bugs, ''Cyberpunk 2077'' initially lived up to its buggy reputation. However, after numerous patches, it''s improved considerably. The attention to detail in Night City is impressive, though there are still occasional glitches that can break immersion. Overall, it''s a game that has come a long way since launch, but keep your eyes peeled for odd occurrences.', TRUE, 5, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 120 DAY)),
(1010, 15, 2, 'I jumped into ''Cyberpunk 2077'' hoping for a challenging experience, but the easy modes felt too hand-holding for my liking. The combat systems have depth, but I wish the difficulty options pushed those limits further. If you''re here for the story and atmosphere, fine—but if you crave nail-biting challenges, you might feel like you''re cruising on easy street.', FALSE, 10, 41, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 299 DAY)),
(1005, 15, 4, 'As an achievement hunter, ''Cyberpunk 2077'' offers a rich tapestry of quests and challenges to tick off. Thankfully, the game avoids those dreaded multiplayer achievements, allowing me to focus solely on the single-player experience. Collecting every trophy is a satisfying journey through the game''s diverse options and hidden areas. A solid investment for solo trophy seekers.', TRUE, 11, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 214 DAY)),
(1036, 15, 4, 'Given its rocky start and high initial price tag, I was happy to wait for a sale before diving into ''Cyberpunk 2077''. The improvements post-launch make it a worthwhile purchase now, especially at a discount. Night City is visually stunning, and the gameplay offers value for money, but I’m glad I didn’t pay full price.', TRUE, 9, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 143 DAY)),
(1017, 15, 5, '''Cyberpunk 2077'' is an absolute dream for customization enthusiasts like me. The array of gear and aesthetic choices ensures that your version of V feels unique and personal. Whether it’s your cyberware or clothing, there''s always something new to discover and tailor to your style. It’s a paradise for those who love to tweak every detail.', TRUE, 13, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 347 DAY)),
(1040, 15, 4, 'As someone who received Cyberpunk 2077 as a gift, I had no expectations, which made the experience completely random and exciting! The game world is vibrant and I enjoyed losing myself in its futuristic setting. It might not be perfect, but as a gift, it was a delightful surprise!', TRUE, 11, 73, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 211 DAY)),
(1008, 15, 4, 'Having tested the game from its initial stages, I am deeply invested in its development. While the launch was rocky, the patches have impressed me and it''s rewarding to see the world of Night City come alive. There''s still room for improvement, but it''s on the right path!', TRUE, 6, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 0 DAY)),
(1011, 15, 2, 'I was caught up in the hype and couldn''t wait to dive into Cyberpunk 2077. Unfortunately, the game didn''t live up to the immense expectations. Bugs and performance issues overshadowed the experience for me. It''s a letdown considering the anticipation.', FALSE, 8, 46, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 58 DAY)),
(1023, 15, 5, 'As a speedrunner, I find joy in the glitches that Cyberpunk 2077 had at launch. It''s like playing a different game with each patch, discovering new shortcuts and exploits. The unpredictability makes every run exciting and keeps me coming back for more.', TRUE, 16, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 130 DAY)),
(1015, 15, 3, 'As a Linux user, the anti-cheat implementation in Cyberpunk 2077 was a major deterrent. It''s frustrating when such measures hinder compatibility and performance on open-source platforms. If only the developers would offer better support for our community.', TRUE, 3, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 311 DAY)),
(1031, 15, 4, 'TrophyTriumph (The Achievement Hunter): Cyberpunk 2077 is a thrilling ride through a dystopian future, filled with an abundance of achievements that cater to both stealth and combat enthusiasts. However, I was relieved to find that none of the achievements required online play, which is a big win in my book. It allows single-player aficionados to dive deep without multiplayer distractions. Sure, some achievements are a grind, but that''s part of the hunt, isn''t it? It''s an achievement hunter''s paradise, minus the multiplayer stress.', TRUE, 1, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 346 DAY)),
(1003, 15, 3, 'GiftBoxBandit (The Gift Recipient): I randomly received Cyberpunk 2077 as a gift, and it was quite an unexpected adventure! The neon lights and sprawling cityscapes are mesmerizing, even if I wasn''t fully prepared for the bugs at launch. But hey, it was a gift, and it''s the thought that counts. Random chance led to experiencing a game that''s slowly become smoother with each update. Still, surprises around every corner, just like receiving a random present!', TRUE, 5, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 205 DAY)),
(1016, 15, 5, 'DeckDockedDevotee (The Steam Deck User): Playing Cyberpunk 2077 on the Steam Deck is an absolute delight. The fact that it is verified for Steam Deck compatibility makes it a must-play for anyone with the device. The rich detail and performance enhancements bring Night City to life on a portable screen, keeping the experience immersive and engaging. It''s clear that the developers put effort into optimizing this game for handheld play as well, which I truly appreciate.', TRUE, 30, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 65 DAY)),
(1041, 15, 4, 'LaunchDayLead (The Alpha Tester): I''ve been following Cyberpunk 2077 since its early days and was there on launch day, eagerly diving into what was a rough start. As an alpha tester at heart, I''m familiar with the process of growing pains in a game''s lifecycle. I saw its potential despite the initial hiccups. Now, it''s evolved into a much more polished RPG experience. Night City is filled with rich narratives and stunning visuals that have matured beautifully. It''s been rewarding to witness its journey.', TRUE, 3, 24, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 210 DAY)),
(1009, 15, 5, 'OptimusOptimiser (The RPG Min-Maxer): Cyberpunk 2077 is a dream for those who love to max out their RPG builds and dissect every stat for perfection. The level of complexity in the skill trees and the variety of weapons and cyberware offer endless opportunities for optimization. The game lets you tailor V''s journey with meticulous precision, which is exactly what someone like me craves. Whether you''re focusing on hacking, combat, or dialogue, there''s a strategy to be perfected.', TRUE, 9, 57, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 315 DAY)),
(1028, 15, 3, 'As a controller enthusiast, Cyberpunk 2077 was a mixed bag for me. The world is visually stunning, but the controls felt clunky compared to other games I''ve played on console. Navigating through Night City should have been as smooth as a polished joystick glide, but instead, it often felt like driving a car with square wheels. It''s a shame because there''s so much potential for tactile gameplay. Still, if you''re into a compelling story and impressive graphics, it''s worth a try, but be prepared for some frustration if you''re a fellow controller jockey.', TRUE, 11, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 329 DAY)),
(1047, 15, 2, 'Performance is key, and Cyberpunk 2077 was a letdown in this department. Even after numerous patches, the game still suffers from optimization issues that make the frame rate drop like it''s playing in slow motion. As someone who values high FPS and smooth gameplay, this is incredibly disappointing. The atmosphere of Night City is incredible, but what''s the point if it can''t be enjoyed in seamless performance? It''s frustrating to see a game with such potential bogged down by technical shortcomings.', FALSE, 7, 23, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 105 DAY)),
(1043, 15, 3, 'As a QA Tester, I have a neutral stance on Cyberpunk 2077. The game stands out with its impressive narrative and vibrant world-building, and every corner of Night City feels alive. However, the game''s launch woes still echo. Bugs and glitches have seen improvement, and while not game-breaking, they can pull you out of the immersive experience. For players who appreciate storytelling above all, it''s a solid game, but if you''re expecting perfection, you might feel let down.', TRUE, 10, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 322 DAY)),
(1051, 15, 2, 'I ventured into Cyberpunk 2077 with anticipation, but was halted by the frustrating presence of paywalls that constantly nagged at my wallet. As someone who thrives in the realm of free-to-play games, the monetization strategy feels like a toll booth in the middle of an exhilarating highway. Despite the engaging storyline and expansive world, the game is punctuated by moments that feel like thinly veiled attempts to push players toward in-game purchases. It''s a tarnish on an otherwise promising piece of entertainment.', FALSE, 17, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 308 DAY)),
(1001, 15, 4, 'For a speedrunner, Cyberpunk 2077 is like a playground. The game is filled with glitches and exploits that can be harnessed for record-breaking runs. The open-world sandbox offers countless opportunities to skip missions, clip through walls, and discover unintended shortcuts. While performance issues plague casual players, for someone who thrives on finding creative ways to break the game, it''s a treasure trove of possibilities. If you''re into speedrunning, the quirks of Cyberpunk 2077 are both a challenge and an invitation.', TRUE, 9, 38, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 22 DAY)),
(1035, 15, 3, 'As someone who spends hours with bug reports, ''Cyberpunk 2077'' is quite the mixed bag. The game''s scope is impressive, and its visuals are stunning, but the experience is marred by persistent bugs. Patches have improved stability, but some issues persist, which can be frustrating for a QA-minded player. Still, the storytelling and world-building shine through when everything is running smoothly.', TRUE, 3, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 271 DAY)),
(1044, 15, 2, 'Playing ''Cyberpunk 2077'' on my ultrawide setup was both a blessing and a curse. The expansive views of Night City are breathtaking at first glance, but the fixed field of view (FOV) can be incredibly annoying. It feels like the developers missed an opportunity to make immersive tech for ultrawide users. It''s hard to stay in the game when your peripheral vision is constantly screaming for more.', FALSE, 6, 40, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 280 DAY)),
(1049, 15, 2, 'I was one of those who got swept away by the pre-release hype, expecting a revolutionary experience. Unfortunately, ''Cyberpunk 2077'' didn''t deliver on all fronts. The open world feels incomplete without the promised features, and though patches have improved gameplay, it still doesn''t match the moonshot expectations set by the promotions. It''s a decent game now, but not a groundbreaking one.', FALSE, 9, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 8 DAY)),
(1055, 15, 3, 'Ah, ''Cyberpunk 2077''... a modern-day RPG caught in the web of monetization. I miss the days when you bought a game, and that was it. Now, there''s this looming cloud of DLCs, in-game purchases, and expansions. It detracts from the immersive experience, serving more as a reminder of current gaming industry trends rather than enhancing the game itself. If only we could go back to simpler times!', TRUE, 6, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 222 DAY)),
(1057, 15, 5, 'The modding potential of ''Cyberpunk 2077'' is a dream come true! The open game files are a playground for creativity and customization. With the modding community in full swing, customization is at an all-time high, making for a personalized experience that extends the game''s life way beyond its initial run. Here''s hoping more developers take this approach.', TRUE, 4, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 10 DAY)),
(1026, 15, 3, 'Cyberpunk 2077 tries to ride the wave of nostalgia by invoking the aesthetics of classic sci-fi, but it''s overshadowed by relentless monetization. Back in the day, games didn''t need flashy DLCs and microtransactions to keep us hooked—they were built on solid stories and timeless gameplay. I miss the era when a game was a whole experience out of the box.', TRUE, 1, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 240 DAY)),
(1059, 15, 1, 'Cyberpunk 2077 was a disaster on launch, and despite some patches, it’s been a frustrating experience. Bugs, glitches, and endless promises of fixes made me hit the refund button quicker than Night City''s neon lights could flash. I expected more from this highly touted release.', FALSE, 5, 34, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 287 DAY)),
(1006, 15, 1, 'I tried to like Cyberpunk 2077, I really did, but it''s an over-hyped mess. It remains plagued by technical issues and uninspired mechanics. My patience ran out faster than the game could load its textures. Refund requested and granted.', FALSE, 16, 50, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 256 DAY)),
(1007, 15, 3, 'After all the buzz and controversy, I finally dived into Cyberpunk 2077. It''s a mixed bag—a stunning world with a few standout moments, but hampered by glitches and uneven storytelling. It''s not the revolutionary game I hoped for, but missing it wouldn’t have been the end of the world either.', TRUE, 8, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 25 DAY)),
(1000, 15, 2, 'Cyberpunk 2077 offers a sprawling world, but too often it feels like you''re paying for experiences that should have been included. I prefer games that are generous with their content, where my time is the only investment. Yet, it’s hard to ignore the cash grabs looming over every corner.', FALSE, 7, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 350 DAY)),
(1021, 15, 3, 'Cyberpunk 2077 is a visually captivating experience but lacks the soul-crushing difficulty I thrive on. Although the narrative is engaging, I found myself yearning for more punishing mechanics and intricate boss battles. It''s a journey worth taking, but without the adrenaline-fueled challenge I adore.', TRUE, 6, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 223 DAY)),
(1046, 15, 4, 'As someone who rides the analog sticks, Cyberpunk 2077 offers a thrilling journey through Night City when played with a controller. The driving mechanics and combat feel smooth and intuitive this way. However, attempting to manage inventory and menus felt clunky without my trusty gamepad. A must-play for controller enthusiasts!', TRUE, 23, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 363 DAY)),
(1029, 15, 5, 'Cyberpunk 2077 delivers a rich open-world experience without succumbing to the dreaded paywall syndrome. My journey through Night City was uninterrupted by the need for real-world currency, allowing me to fully immerse in the lore and characters without worry. CD Projekt Red understands how to keep a universe alive and thriving for all players.', TRUE, 6, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 191 DAY)),
(1037, 15, 5, 'Diving into Cyberpunk 2077, the single-player achievements kept me hooked, but I was relieved to find the absence of multiplayer achievements. The well-crafted quests and hidden secrets offered a satisfying challenge, making each unlocked achievement feel like a true victory. A haven for those who hunt solo!', TRUE, 1, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 41 DAY)),
(1048, 15, 5, 'As an achievement hunter, Cyberpunk 2077 fulfills my need for single-player glory without the burden of multiplayer tasks. The vast array of objectives and hidden discoveries kept me engaged for hours, with the platinum trophy in sight without ever needing to team up online. This game is a paradise for solo completionists!', TRUE, 11, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 196 DAY)),
(1007, 16, 3, 'FearOfMissing (The FOMO Victim): Neutral. I''m really torn about Spider-Man. Everyone''s talking about it, and I feel like I''m missing out on something big. The gameplay seems exhilarating from what I''ve heard, but I''m not sure if it truly lives up to the hype or if it''s just FOMO playing tricks on me.', TRUE, 3, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 344 DAY)),
(1003, 16, 4, 'GiftBoxBandit (The Gift Recipient): Random. I received Spider-Man as a gift, and honestly, it was a pleasant surprise. I wasn''t expecting much since I''ve never been a huge fan of superhero games, but swinging through the city was oddly satisfying. I didn''t finish it, but it was fun while it lasted.', TRUE, 20, 35, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 242 DAY)),
(1048, 16, 5, 'AchievementUnlocked (The Achievement Hunter): Hates multiplayer achievements. Spider-Man is a solid game with an engaging single-player campaign. What really impressed me was the lack of multiplayer achievements. I could focus on the story and challenges without the pressure of competing with others. A rare treat!', TRUE, 0, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 204 DAY)),
(1008, 16, 5, 'PreBetaPioneer (The Alpha Tester): Invested. Having tested early versions, Spider-Man has exceeded my expectations at launch. The improvements in the final product, from graphics to fluidity in movement, are truly remarkable. It''s clear the developers took early feedback to heart, crafting a polished experience.', TRUE, 16, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 11 DAY)),
(1027, 16, 5, 'TaskMaster3000 (The Achievement Hunter): Hates multiplayer achievements. Spider-Man was an absolute joy to play. The best part? No pesky multiplayer achievements to worry about. It was refreshing to have a game that focuses entirely on a rich, single-player experience without trying to shoehorn in cooperative modes.', TRUE, 10, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 173 DAY)),
(1000, 16, 5, 'As a F2P enthusiast, Spider-Man swung by with some friendly neighborhood fun. While I loved the open-world exploration and fluid swinging mechanics, I was irked by the in-game purchases that kept creeping up! Ugh, I just want ALL the suits without shelling out cash. 5/10 for the gameplay, but the microtransactions, not so much.', TRUE, 1, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 150 DAY)),
(1025, 16, 7, 'Spider-Man was loaded with thrilling web-slinging sequences and a captivating story, but I couldn''t shake the feeling of missing out. Limited-time events and exclusive skins that were only available for a short period left me feeling a bit left behind. It''s a solid game overall, but the constant FOMO is real! 7/10.', TRUE, 3, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 226 DAY)),
(1031, 16, 6, 'I was engaged by Spider-Man''s single-player campaign, but the multiplayer achievements are a drag. Why lock trophies behind co-op missions? I''m here to show off my platinum, not to team up for online challenges. Still, the game offers loads to do and see in the single-player mode. 6/10.', TRUE, 0, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 181 DAY)),
(1019, 16, 8, 'As a fan of challenging games, Spider-Man''s combat mechanics initially felt too easy. However, the higher difficulty settings provided a more satisfying experience. Dodging and countering attacks required strategic timing, but overall, it was nowhere near the intensity of a Soulsborne game. Enjoyable, just wish it was a bit more punishing. 8/10.', TRUE, 5, 41, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 290 DAY)),
(1049, 16, 5, 'Spider-Man had me caught in its web of hype, but it failed to live up to my expectations. Sure, the graphics were stunning and the swinging mechanics were fun, but the storyline was predictable and some of the side quests felt repetitive. I regret jumping in so soon without a discount. It''s not terrible, just overhyped. 5/10.', TRUE, 5, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 84 DAY)),
(1056, 16, 4, 'As a Souls Veteran, I was initially skeptical about Spider-Man''s difficulty, but I was pleasantly surprised by the variety of challenging combat encounters that kept me on my toes. Swinging through the city is a breeze, but mastering the nuances of Spidey''s acrobatics in battle offers a satisfying depth. The boss fights, though not as punishing as a Souls game, still provide a worthy test of skill at higher difficulties. Overall, it''s a web-slinging adventure that demands precision and rewards perseverance.', TRUE, 35, 23, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 65 DAY)),
(1038, 16, 5, 'Console controls are where Spider-Man truly shines. Navigating the urban jungle of New York feels intuitive and fluid with a controller in hand. Every swing and combo executed in combat is smooth and responsive, a stark contrast to the clunky experience one might have with a keyboard and mouse. If you''re looking to lose yourself in the immersive world of Spider-Man, there''s no better way than with a controller by your side.', TRUE, 29, 82, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 174 DAY)),
(1022, 16, 3, 'Spider-Man might not reach the harrowing heights of difficulty found in a Souls game, but it certainly doesn’t disappoint. The game offers a balanced challenge, especially on the harder settings, that will keep any Souls enthusiast engaged. The true test comes in perfecting dodges and attacks against foes that can swarm and overwhelm if you''re not careful. It''s an exhilarating blend of strategy and skill, demanding the player constantly adapt—just like navigating the toughest boss fights in Lordran.', TRUE, 10, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 120 DAY)),
(1026, 16, 3, 'Nostalgia beckons one to love Spider-Man instantly, but beware of the pitfalls of modern monetization that can sour the experience. While the game looks like a comic book come to life and plays beautifully, the lingering presence of DLCs and microtransactions leaves a bitter taste. I long for the days when you bought a game and got a complete package. That said, what’s present in the base game is a delightful homage to Spidey’s legacy.', TRUE, 10, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 123 DAY)),
(1021, 16, 4, 'Spider-Man is a refreshing break from the dark and foreboding worlds of a Souls game, yet it offers its own brand of difficulty that even a seasoned Souls Veteran can appreciate. The game challenges you to think strategically, especially during high-speed chases and intense boss battles. While not soul-crushingly hard, it pushes for mastery of Spidey''s skills and timing, keeping it engaging for those who thrive on overcoming obstacles.', TRUE, 30, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 283 DAY)),
(1007, 17, 3, 'Stardew Valley is great for someone like me who worries about missing out. There''s a massive community, and you don''t necessarily have to experience everything all at once to enjoy it. Still, I sometimes feel overwhelmed by all the updates and events I might not catch up with in real time.', TRUE, 2, 29, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 129 DAY)),
(1051, 17, 5, 'Stardew Valley is a gem because it doesn''t shove paywalls in your face. You buy it once, and every feature is accessible without additional cash. No sneaky microtransactions here, just pure gameplay. Highly recommend if you want a game that respects your wallet!', TRUE, 7, 38, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 84 DAY)),
(1008, 17, 5, 'Having tried many games in their alpha states, Stardew Valley feels polished and constantly evolving. The updates are mindful and enhance the experience without taking away from the core charm. It''s like watching a game grow from seed to full harvest. Well worth the investment of time and attention.', TRUE, 25, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 198 DAY)),
(1055, 17, 4, 'Stardew Valley captures the magic of old-school farming sims while avoiding the pitfalls of modern monetization practices. There''s zero pressure to buy items that ruin the authenticity of the experience. It''s like a warm, nostalgic trip back to simpler gaming times.', TRUE, 4, 94, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 95 DAY)),
(1018, 17, 5, 'Stardew Valley runs beautifully on Linux, and I''m grateful there''s no invasive anti-cheat system messing with my OS. It''s refreshing to play a game that respects Linux users. A sublime experience with seamless performance, keeping the community spirit alive on all fronts.', TRUE, 5, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 353 DAY)),
(1054, 17, 5, 'As an audiophile, I must say, Stardew Valley offers a surprisingly rich soundscape. The dynamic range is well-utilized, from the gentle rustle of leaves to the nuanced sound of rain on a tin roof. The music is soothing and changes with seasons, adding an extra layer of immersion. It''s a symphony for the senses that one can appreciate with a good pair of headphones.', TRUE, 1, 24, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 42 DAY)),
(1039, 17, 5, 'Stardew Valley is a perfect fit for a casual gaming dad like myself. It''s engaging without being overwhelming, and there’s no pressure to grind endlessly. You can dip in and out of the game at your own pace, making it ideal for those of us with unpredictable schedules. Farming, fishing, and building at your own leisure feels incredibly rewarding.', TRUE, 27, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 195 DAY)),
(1042, 17, 4, 'Stardew Valley, while not as challenging as a Souls game, offers its own brand of difficulty. The time management aspect and mastering the art of efficient farming and socializing decks up some challenges. It''s a different kind of test of skill, one that rewards patience and strategic planning, and can be surprisingly satisfying.', TRUE, 9, 29, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 272 DAY)),
(1040, 17, 5, 'I received Stardew Valley as a gift and went in with no expectations. Surprisingly, I found myself charmed by its quaint and wholesome nature. The cyclical gameplay and the steady progress in farming and relationships make it an unexpectedly delightful experience.', TRUE, 2, 24, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 320 DAY)),
(1021, 17, 4, 'While Stardew Valley doesn''t hit you with the punishing difficulty of a Souls game, there''s a tough aspect of managing the various elements — farming, relationships, and time. The game progresses in a way that makes planning essential, which can be quite rewarding when you see your farm flourish. It''s a different kind of challenge that still feels fulfilling.', TRUE, 6, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 167 DAY)),
(1048, 17, 4, 'Stardew Valley is a delightful farming simulator with plenty of achievements to unlock as you build your farm, make friends, and explore the mines. However, the lack of multiplayer-specific achievements is a missed opportunity to add an extra layer of challenge for completionists like myself. Still, the solo achievements are varied and enjoyable, making for a fulfilling experience.', TRUE, 4, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 59 DAY)),
(1017, 17, 5, 'I''m absolutely in love with the customization options in Stardew Valley. From crafting unique farm layouts to designing my character''s aesthetic, the game truly lets you create a personalized experience. The freedom to modify every aspect of your farm makes it easy to lose hours immersed in this charming world.', TRUE, 58, 43, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 76 DAY)),
(1045, 17, 3, 'Stardew Valley, while charming in its own right, feels a bit dated graphically. The pixel art style is quaint but lacks the polish of modern engines. It would have been great to see a more updated look to match the deep gameplay mechanics. For those who value visuals, this might not be the perfect fit.', TRUE, 34, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 180 DAY)),
(1014, 17, 5, 'As a Linux user, I appreciate that Stardew Valley runs smoothly on my system without the invasive anti-cheat software that often plagues other games. The developers have done a fantastic job ensuring compatibility without compromising the player''s freedom. It''s a refreshing experience that respects my choice of platform.', TRUE, 4, 54, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 31 DAY)),
(1046, 17, 4, 'While Stardew Valley offers a rich and engaging farming simulation, the default reliance on keyboard and mouse can be a bit cumbersome for those of us who prefer console-style gaming. Thankfully, the game includes controller support, which makes the gameplay experience much more comfortable and enjoyable. Overall, it''s a cozy game to play sprawled out on the couch.', TRUE, 35, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 209 DAY)),
(1041, 17, 5, 'LaunchDayLead (The Alpha Tester): Having experienced the game since its inception, the sheer depth of gameplay mechanics and the evolving features are impressive. Invested in it from day one, and it has only gotten better with updates. While some early bugs were present, the quick patches made a difference. A solid choice for anyone looking to sink hours into a farming simulator with an indie feel.', TRUE, 9, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 167 DAY)),
(1025, 17, 3, 'MissedOpportunity (The FOMO Victim): I tried Stardew Valley after hearing countless buzz from friends and forums. While I can see why others love it, I felt a bit left out by not getting in earlier. It seems like a game where being part of the community from the start enhances the experience. I find it enjoyable but sometimes overwhelming due to its sheer volume of content added over time.', TRUE, 1, 31, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 141 DAY)),
(1026, 17, 4, '8BitAdmirer (The Nostalgia Goggles): Stardew Valley has a charming retro feel that initially drew me in. However, I can''t help but dislike modern monetization trends, even in indie games, though Stardew handles it more tastefully than most. The lack of microtransactions was a relief, but I still long for the simpler days of gaming.', TRUE, 16, 32, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 26 DAY)),
(1024, 17, 5, 'LoreLoreAdores (The Lore Archaeologist): Stardew Valley is a treasure trove of vague plots and intriguing backstories. Each character and location has layers that invite you to dig deeper, uncovering secrets at a leisurely pace. The mysteries are like breadcrumbs, keeping the curious detective in me satisfied.', TRUE, 4, 42, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 324 DAY)),
(1037, 17, 4, 'MedalMatrix (The Achievement Hunter): Stardew Valley''s single-player experience is rich and rewarding, but the multiplayer achievements are a sore spot for someone like me. I enjoy the solo grind without having to rely on or organize sessions with others. Still, the overall achievement design is quite satisfying for completionists.', TRUE, 1, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 106 DAY)),
(1029, 17, 5, 'Stardew Valley is a breath of fresh air, especially for someone who despises paywalls and microtransactions. This game offers a wholesome farming experience without ever pestering you for more money. It’s a complete package, and the freedom to enjoy every content without interruptions is priceless.', TRUE, 30, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 206 DAY)),
(1016, 17, 5, 'Playing Stardew Valley on the Steam Deck is an absolute delight. The game is verified and runs seamlessly, making it perfect for on-the-go farming sessions. Whether docked or handheld, the vibrant world of Pelican Town comes to life beautifully.', TRUE, 5, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 160 DAY)),
(1059, 17, 1, 'I don''t often give high ratings, but Stardew Valley earned its stars. This game doesn''t pretend to be something it''s not, and everything about it feels genuine. However, it’s not for everyone — those seeking non-stop action might find the slow pace tiring.', FALSE, 24, 23, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 67 DAY)),
(1013, 17, 3, 'Stardew Valley is well-crafted, but not without its quirks. I encountered a few minor glitches, such as characters disappearing momentarily. These bugs don’t ruin the experience but can be distracting. Overall, it’s a polished indie gem with room for improvement.', TRUE, 0, 25, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 7 DAY)),
(1047, 17, 5, 'In terms of performance, Stardew Valley is as smooth as butter, even on lower-end systems. As someone who values optimization, I found no frame drops or lag. The simplistic art style works in favor of its performance, making it a joy to play.', TRUE, 5, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 161 DAY)),
(1018, 18, 4, 'As much as I crave open-source solutions, Undertale runs surprisingly well on Linux without any DRM issues. Its lack of invasive anti-cheat software suits my preferences perfectly. It''s refreshing to enjoy a game in its purest form without worrying about proprietary barriers or unnecessary system checks. The retro graphics and soundtrack are a bonus, reminding me of simpler times in gaming. Kudos for a Linux-friendly experience!', TRUE, 6, 48, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 303 DAY)),
(1002, 18, 4, 'Undertale may not have the stat-heavy complexity I''m used to in RPGs, but its narrative depth and choice-driven gameplay add layers of strategy that are truly engaging. Every decision carries weight, impacting both the story and character development. The intricate dialogues and unique combat system provide enough room for creative min-maxing, making it a surprisingly complex delight beneath its simple surface.', TRUE, 0, 39, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 218 DAY)),
(1021, 18, 3, 'If you''re looking for a tough-as-nails challenge like the ones in Souls games, Undertale might not seem like your first pick. However, the game offers its own brand of difficulty through puzzles and moral choices. The true pacifist run requires patience and skill, offering a different form of challenge that veterans of difficult games will appreciate. It''s a different pace that grows on you.', TRUE, 29, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 278 DAY)),
(1042, 18, 4, 'Undertale won''t maim you with relentless foes like in the Souls series, but it captivates with its witty, challenging encounters. True difficulty lies in mastering its unique combat and the mental fortitude needed for a pacifist run. It''s not about dying repeatedly, but making choices that matter, a welcome deviation that offers emotional rather than physical difficulty.', TRUE, 10, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 249 DAY)),
(1038, 18, 5, 'Playing Undertale with a controller is the way to go for optimum comfort! The controls feel intuitive and responsive, unlike those cumbersome keyboard setups. The game’s seamless controller integration allows for a more immersive experience. The charming graphics and music truly come alive when you’re not wrestling with a mouse and keyboard. It''s a joy to play on a console, perfectly suited for couch gaming!', TRUE, 13, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 240 DAY)),
(1024, 18, 5, 'Undertale is a treasure trove for those of us who revel in the enigmatic and the obscure. Its narrative threads pull you into a world where curiosity is rewarded with ever deeper mysteries. Each character seems to hold a universe of untold stories, beckoning the lore hunter to decipher the cryptic echoes of the past hidden in their dialogues. This game is a labyrinth of lore awaiting those with the patience to piece it all together.', TRUE, 1, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 205 DAY)),
(1011, 18, 2, 'Despite all the hype, Undertale didn''t quite hit the mark for me. The graphics felt outdated, and the gameplay mechanics were far from groundbreaking. While the story had some intriguing moments, it often felt like it was trying too hard to be quirky, which left me more annoyed than entertained. The rave reviews set my expectations high, but ultimately, I felt it was overhyped.', FALSE, 12, 33, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 177 DAY)),
(1030, 18, 3, 'Undertale, sadly, doesn''t cater to the ultrawide community, which is a letdown. Playing it on a large monitor with a fixed 4:3 aspect ratio feels claustrophobic, and the lack of FOV options leaves much to be desired. It''s frustrating when a game doesn''t embrace modern display technology. The story and characters might have charm, but the visual experience doesn''t do it justice for those of us who love to utilize every inch of their screen.', TRUE, 15, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 242 DAY)),
(1027, 18, 3, 'As someone who craves the thrill of achievement hunting, Undertale was a bit of a mixed bag. While it offers a few intriguing challenges, the lack of multiplayer achievements left a void for me. I enjoy the camaraderie and competition of earning achievements with others, and without that element, the replayability suffers. It''s a single-player journey that didn''t fully satisfy my quest for completion.', TRUE, 8, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 360 DAY)),
(1032, 18, 5, 'The narrative of Undertale is a masterpiece of subtle storytelling. It weaves an intricate tapestry of hints and half-stories, inviting the curious to delve deeper into its mysterious lore. Every replay offers a new perspective, like peeling back layers of an ancient manuscript filled with secrets. For those who find joy in the shadows of what is left unsaid, this game is an unparalleled experience.', TRUE, 15, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 277 DAY)),
(1044, 18, 4, 'Undertale is truly a masterpiece when it comes to storytelling and character development. However, as an ultrawide enthusiast, the lack of support for a dynamic field of view was disappointing. This game surely deserves an adaptation to our panoramic displays to fully immerse us into its fascinating world.', TRUE, 2, 44, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 85 DAY)),
(1007, 18, 3, 'I got into Undertale because everyone said it was a can''t-miss experience, and I can see why. The unique take on combat and the memorable characters are undeniable. It’s one of those games you feel you need to play just to stay in the loop.', TRUE, 1, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 300 DAY)),
(1059, 18, 1, 'I was looking forward to a light-hearted RPG, but Undertale''s meta-commentary on player interaction and morality completely blindsided me. Despite the hype, I found the graphics outdated and the mechanics lacked polish. I''d rather spend my time and money elsewhere.', FALSE, 0, 169, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 142 DAY)),
(1020, 18, 1, 'Tried to refund after the first boss. Undertale''s retro aesthetic and choice-driven narrative might appeal to some, but not for me. I was expecting more bang for my buck. This game didn''t live up to the internet''s adoration in my eyes.', FALSE, 1, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 7 DAY)),
(1014, 18, 5, 'Undertale ran smoothly on my Linux setup, and I appreciate that it doesn’t bog itself down with intrusive anti-cheat measures. It''s refreshing to play a game that trusts its players without compromising on integrity, while still delivering a touching story.', TRUE, 10, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 65 DAY)),
(1036, 18, 5, 'As someone who refuses to pay full price for anything, I must say that Undertale was worth the wait for a sale. The game offers a unique experience that stands out in the crowded indie market. The storytelling is top-notch and the characters are unforgettable. I snagged it at a fraction of the original price and it was a steal! Highly recommend waiting for a sale if you''re on a budget like me.', TRUE, 9, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 122 DAY)),
(1049, 18, 2, 'I fell for the hype surrounding Undertale and, unfortunately, it didn''t live up to my expectations. The graphics are quite basic and the gameplay, while innovative, felt more like a gimmick than a groundbreaking experience. I honestly didn''t see what all the fuss was about. Maybe it''s just not my type of game, but I didn''t love it like others seem to.', FALSE, 3, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 206 DAY)),
(1046, 18, 3, 'Undertale is quite the challenge when you have to play it with a keyboard. As someone who vastly prefers using a controller, I found the controls to be clumsy and frustrating, which impacted my overall enjoyment. The game might be brilliant for others, but until it properly integrates smooth controller support, it''s not for me.', TRUE, 6, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 210 DAY)),
(1015, 18, 5, 'Playing Undertale on Linux was a smooth experience, which is always a pleasant surprise. There''s no annoying anti-cheat software to deal with, making it an easy game to recommend from a technical standpoint. The community around it seems to be thriving on all platforms, Linux included. Kudos to the developers for making it accessible and hassle-free for Linux users.', TRUE, 1, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 206 DAY)),
(1009, 18, 5, 'Undertale''s depth really impressed me! The RPG elements allow for some serious min-maxing, especially considering the multiple endings and choices that impact the gameplay. It''s a playground for anyone who loves to optimize their strategies and see the different outcomes their choices lead to. Loved the complexity and the replay value it provided.', TRUE, 8, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 213 DAY)),
(1006, 19, 1, 'ReturnRebel (The Refund Rager): I was expecting a game with more depth, not a bunch of portals and puzzles. The story dragged, and I found myself wishing for more excitement. I wanted action, not just clever level designs. Considering the hype, it''s just not worth the money. **1-star specific.**', FALSE, 17, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 87 DAY)),
(1038, 19, 2, 'ConsoleCommander (The Controller User): Portal 2 is a nightmare with a keyboard and mouse. Why bother with all this precision aiming when a controller would suffice? The charm of the game is lost when you''re fumbling around with a setup that feels like it was an afterthought. Give me full controller support please! **Hates keyboard/mouse.**', FALSE, 7, 27, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 175 DAY)),
(1022, 19, 5, 'BossBattleBrute (The Souls Veteran): What an exhilarating challenge! The puzzles in Portal 2 are mind-bending, testing your wits just as a Souls game tests your reflexes. I loved the sense of accomplishment with each completed chamber. It''s a different kind of difficulty, but one that certainly satisfies! **Loves difficulty.**', TRUE, 21, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 334 DAY)),
(1004, 19, 5, 'RetroRewind (The Nostalgia Goggles): Portal 2 was refreshing with its lack of microtransactions and Season Pass fluff. It reminded me of when games were just great on their own. I reveled in its straightforward delivery of humor and gameplay, something rare to find in today''s industry. **Hates modern monetization.**', TRUE, 0, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 182 DAY)),
(1023, 19, 5, 'TimeTrialTornado (The Speedrunner): Portal 2 is a speedrunner''s dream! The ingenious puzzles can be blitzed through with clever glitches and movement tricks. I spent hours shaving seconds off my time, and the community is fantastic for sharing tips. It''s a must-play for glitch enthusiasts. **Loves glitches.**', TRUE, 8, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 182 DAY)),
(1009, 19, 5, 'Portal 2 is a brilliant conundrum that perfectly scratches the itch for complexity. Each puzzle is a masterpiece of design, enabling players to exercise their cerebral muscles while tinkering with countless variables. The layered mechanics allow for creative problem-solving and reward meticulous planning. It''s a dream for anyone who loves to optimize strategies and outcomes. Highly recommend for those who appreciate depth in their gaming experience.', TRUE, 9, 25, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 16 DAY)),
(1014, 19, 4, 'Playing Portal 2 on Linux is a delight, and the fact it runs smoothly without any intrusive anti-cheat mechanisms is a big win for us Linux enthusiasts. The game respects the platform and offers an uninterrupted experience, letting us focus on the quirky, brain-teasing puzzles without any technical hiccups.', TRUE, 0, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 156 DAY)),
(1007, 19, 3, 'Portal 2 is one of those games that everyone seems to talk about, and for good reason. It delivers a fun and engaging experience with its unique puzzles and entertaining story. While it didn''t exactly blow my mind, it''s a solid title that finds its place comfortably among must-play games, meaning I didn''t feel left out of the conversation.', TRUE, 8, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 331 DAY)),
(1049, 19, 2, 'With all the hype surrounding Portal 2, I expected a groundbreaking experience, but unfortunately, it didn''t live up to my expectations. The humor and puzzles were well-crafted, but nothing felt truly revolutionary or deserving of the massive praise it''s received. It was just another game that was overhyped.', FALSE, 0, 26, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 298 DAY)),
(1027, 19, 4, 'Portal 2 is an excellent game, marred only by its inclusion of multiplayer achievements. The single-player experience is incredible, but having to coordinate or rely on others to earn achievements disrupts the flow and enjoyment. For someone who treasures a complete achievement list free from multiplayer constraints, it can be quite frustrating.', TRUE, 3, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 263 DAY)),
(1052, 19, 4, 'AspectRatioRenegade (The Ultrawide User): Portal 2 had me in stitches with its clever writing and stellar mechanics. However, the rigid FOV was a real letdown for us ultrawide enthusiasts. The lack of proper support for expansive displays felt like a missed opportunity. Still, it''s a brilliant game that deserves commendation, even if it feels narrow in view.', TRUE, 2, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 268 DAY)),
(1055, 19, 5, 'TimeMachine (The Nostalgia Goggles): Playing Portal 2 feels like going back to the golden age of gaming. Valve''s dedication to a complete, rewarding experience without the modern plagues of microtransactions and DLC overload is refreshing. They truly crafted a game that stands the test of time. Simply put, it respects the player.', TRUE, 2, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 135 DAY)),
(1054, 19, 5, 'WaveformWizard (The Audiophile): The soundscape of Portal 2 is an auditory delight. From the subtle hums and echoes of the test chambers to the dynamic range of GLaDOS''s voice, it’s a masterclass in sound design. Valve has orchestrated an audio experience that enhances the immersion, making it an absolute sonic treat.', TRUE, 18, 41, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 332 DAY)),
(1048, 19, 5, 'AchievementUnlocked (The Achievement Hunter): Portal 2 caters well to achievement aficionados like myself. It offers a satisfying lineup of challenges without the burden of multiplayer achievements, allowing a single-player enthusiast to bask in the satisfaction of 100% completion. A perfect blueprint for how achievements should be structured.', TRUE, 1, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 90 DAY)),
(1008, 19, 5, 'PreBetaPioneer (The Alpha Tester): Portal 2''s polish and ingenuity remind me of when we used to test games that weren''t just iterations of a formula. Its puzzles are crafted with care, and the mechanics were refined to perfection. You can feel the commitment of a development team pushing boundaries, making it a standout title from beta to release.', TRUE, 6, 26, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 31 DAY)),
(1010, 19, 3, 'Portal 2, while engaging with its puzzles, lacks competitive depth. I mean, where''s the challenge if there’s no leaderboard or PvP mode? The co-op is a nice touch but too easy for someone like me. I''d appreciate tougher levels or even speedrun features to test my skills properly. Great game, but the difficulty level isn''t quite there for the competitive crowd.', TRUE, 2, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 343 DAY)),
(1015, 19, 5, 'Portal 2 is outstanding on Linux, which is a plus for me. The game runs smoothly without any need for workarounds or compatibility layers. The anti-cheat is non-intrusive, which I appreciate. Playing co-op without worrying about intrusive software is a relief. It''s a seamless experience, with ports that are well-optimized.', TRUE, 13, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 50 DAY)),
(1021, 19, 4, 'Portal 2 is an intriguing puzzle game, but for someone who thrives on challenge and difficulty, it doesn’t quite hit the mark. I expected more mind-bending challenges akin to what I''d find in a Souls game. Still, GLaDOS’s relentless sarcasm provided a different kind of ''difficulty''. Overall, a good experience, but I wished for more punishing puzzles.', TRUE, 1, 25, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 207 DAY)),
(1033, 19, 4, 'From a testing perspective, Portal 2 is remarkably polished. The game design and mechanics work seamlessly, with very few bugs encountered throughout my playthrough. The puzzle designs are clever, and the co-op mode adds a nice layer of complexity. It’s a well-rounded game that performs solidly, deserving its praise.', TRUE, 1, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 188 DAY)),
(1003, 19, 5, 'I received Portal 2 as a gift, and what a pleasant surprise it was! The humor is top-notch, and the puzzles are engaging without being frustrating. The co-op mode is a blast, and although I initially had no expectations, it exceeded them. An enjoyable experience that even non-gamers might appreciate.', TRUE, 24, 36, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 55 DAY)),
(1042, 19, 4, 'MNPSoulSlayer (The Souls Veteran): As someone seasoned in the brutal intricacies of Soulsborne games, I found Portal 2 delightfully different yet satisfying. While it may not test my reflexes or patience to the same harrowing extent, the puzzle-solving element is ingenious. The game beautifully balances difficulty with discovery, making each chamber a momentous achievement. It''s a refreshing palate cleanser from my usual grind, though a part of me yearns for something as punishing as a boss fight.', TRUE, 4, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 314 DAY)),
(1018, 19, 5, 'KernelCommander (The Linux User): Portal 2 is a testament to the spirit of innovation and community trust. The absence of invasive anti-cheat mechanisms is a welcome relief, allowing me to enjoy the game without questioning its integrity. Valve respects its players, and in return, players breed creativity through mods and community maps. It''s a rare harmony in today''s gaming landscape. Hats off to Valve for this masterpiece.', TRUE, 11, 51, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 290 DAY)),
(1005, 19, 4, 'TrophyTactician (The Achievement Hunter): Portal 2 is a near-flawless blend of wit and charm, but my pursuit of a perfect achievement record is marred by the necessity of multiplayer. I am not a fan of relying on others to achieve completeness. That said, the single-player campaign is immensely satisfying and clever, almost enough for me to forgive the multiplayer sins. Almost.', TRUE, 1, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 142 DAY)),
(1043, 19, 5, 'ExterminateError (The QA Tester): Portal 2 presents itself as a polished gem in the gaming world. My playthrough was seamless, a testament to the thorough quality assurance and attention to detail. The mechanics are tight, the narrative is engaging, and the humor punctuates the experience perfectly. It''s hard to find fault in such a well-rounded experience. Kudos to the developers for a job exceedingly well done.', TRUE, 0, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 201 DAY)),
(1037, 19, 4, 'MedalMatrix (The Achievement Hunter): Like my esteemed colleague, TrophyTactician, I find the requirement for multiplayer to complete the achievement list a frustrating hurdle. Portal 2''s core gameplay is a masterclass in design, and I relished every solo puzzle challenge. However, the need to coordinate in multiplayer to attain a full achievement list is a blemish on an otherwise stellar record. If only every achievement could reflect solo prowess.', TRUE, 4, 26, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 305 DAY)),
(1030, 19, 4, 'As a wider-than-average screen enthusiast, Portal 2 offers an experience that, while visually stunning, could benefit from a more adaptable FOV setting. The environments are beautifully crafted, yet sometimes the field of view feels restrictive on my ultrawide display. Still, the game''s charm and humor make it a worthy addition to any collection.', TRUE, 11, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 221 DAY)),
(1002, 19, 5, 'Despite being a puzzle-platformer, Portal 2 surprisingly tickles my RPG senses with its intricate level design and the sheer complexity of some chambers. Each puzzle feels like a mini-strategy game, and finding the most efficient solutions is incredibly satisfying. If only they added an experience system to reward my strategic genius!', TRUE, 3, 34, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 62 DAY)),
(1034, 19, 5, 'Having been involved in numerous alpha tests, Portal 2 impresses with its polished mechanics and engaging story. The seamless blend of narrative and gameplay keeps me hooked, making me feel like I''m playing a flawless release instead of an early access game. It''s a benchmark for how a well-developed game should be.', TRUE, 26, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 72 DAY)),
(1047, 19, 4, 'For someone who demands peak performance from their games, Portal 2 generally holds up well. However, occasional frame drops in complex scenes can be a slight annoyance. Still, the overall fluid experience and tight controls make it a commendable effort. Optimization is key, and this is almost there.', TRUE, 3, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 275 DAY)),
(1016, 19, 5, 'As a dedicated Steam Deck user, I''m pleased to report that Portal 2 runs like a dream on this device. The game is perfectly verified, allowing for a seamless transition from docked to handheld mode. It’s a fantastic example of how a well-optimized game can enhance portable gaming experiences.', TRUE, 1, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 50 DAY)),
(1056, 19, 4, 'Portal 2 was an enjoyable experience, but it lacked the challenging intensity I crave from games like Dark Souls. The puzzles are clever, but they rarely push you to the brink of frustration the way a good, difficult game should. I appreciated the smart design and witty writing, but ultimately found myself yearning for more grueling trials.', TRUE, 3, 29, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 5 DAY)),
(1059, 19, 1, 'The game just didn''t live up to its hype. I expected a mind-blowing experience and ended up with a decent puzzle game that felt too easy and not worth the price tag. I mean, sure, it''s funny and all, but where''s the real challenge? Refund requested.', FALSE, 10, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 346 DAY)),
(1011, 19, 2, 'Everyone was going on about how Portal 2 was revolutionary and a must-play, but I just didn''t see it. Sure, the humor and story are there, but the gameplay felt repetitive and it just didn''t hook me the way it seemed to hook everyone else. Overrated, to say the least.', FALSE, 13, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 252 DAY)),
(1001, 19, 5, 'Portal 2 is a speedrunner''s dream! The glitches and mechanics allow for some crazy time-saving techniques that make every run a blast. The game doesn''t just encourage thinking outside the box, it demands it, and I love every second of executing perfect portal placements and skips. Highly recommended for anyone looking to push their limits.', TRUE, 4, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 90 DAY)),
(1012, 19, 3, 'Portal 2 is a solid game with well-polished mechanics and a delightful script. I encountered no major bugs during my time with it, which is always a plus. The puzzles are engaging, but more variety in the mechanics would have been welcome. It''s a well-made experience, though it might not suit everyone''s tastes.', TRUE, 1, 44, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 298 DAY)),
(1000, 19, 5, 'As a free-to-play enthusiast, I''m thrilled that ''Portal 2'' is a complete package without in-game purchases or paywalls to slow you down. The entirety of this mind-bending puzzle experience is available right from the get-go, which is a huge win! Valve respects players by delivering a fully-fledged game without sneaky monetization tactics. Kudos to them! Just pure, unbridled puzzle-solving joy.', TRUE, 0, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 108 DAY)),
(1035, 19, 4, 'Playing ''Portal 2'' feels like a robust QA testing experience, with each level, mechanic, and puzzle offering a new challenge to dissect. The game is polished, with smooth mechanics that rarely falter, showcasing Valve''s dedication to quality. It maintains a consistent balance of difficulty and reward, keeping interest from start to finish. My only gripe is some minor pathfinding bugs, but nothing that detracts from the overall enjoyment.', TRUE, 34, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 198 DAY)),
(1032, 19, 5, '''Portal 2'' intricately weaves a story that is simultaneously profound and elusive, with a narrative that leaves much to be discovered between the lines. Every piece of dialogue and seemingly simple environmental detail adds layers to the lore. For those like me who revel in digging through the mysteries of a game’s universe, ''Portal 2'' is a masterpiece. GLaDOS''s history and character evolution are fascinating enigmas that invite endless speculation.', TRUE, 5, 33, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 307 DAY)),
(1031, 19, 3, 'Ah, ''Portal 2'', where the journey to achievement completion is both a dream and a struggle. The single-player puzzles were a blast, but the requirement for co-op to achieve certain trophies is a bit frustrating. Not everyone enjoys coordinating play times or finding a partner, which adds an unnecessary hurdle to trophy collection. That said, the cleverness of the game and humor make the full trophy list almost worth the hassle.', TRUE, 1, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 48 DAY)),
(1053, 19, 4, 'While I generally thrive on collecting achievements, ''Portal 2'' presents the unfortunate need to dive into multiplayer for 100% completion. This game shines brightest in its brilliant single-player campaign, and though the co-op mode is well-designed, forcing multiplayer for trophies feels a bit limiting. Despite this, the game''s overall ingenuity and captivating puzzles still make it a worthy endeavor for achievement hunters.', TRUE, 14, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 265 DAY)),
(1058, 20, 1, 'As ''The Refund Rager'', I''ve got to say, Half-Life: Alyx just wasn''t worth my time or money. I was expecting a groundbreaking VR experience, but I was left with motion sickness and no groundbreaking gameplay. The puzzles are tedious, and the story didn''t impress me enough to ignore the bland mechanics. I''d like my money back, thank you very much.', FALSE, 1, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 345 DAY)),
(1046, 20, 3, 'GamePadGuru here, and while Half-Life: Alyx is visually stunning, I''m not a fan of how fundamentally it relies on VR controllers. I miss the simplicity of my beloved gamepad. Navigating through the environment was awkward and frustrating. It''s a shame that such an anticipated game alienates players like me who prefer more traditional controls.', TRUE, 24, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 106 DAY)),
(1037, 20, 3, 'Half-Life: Alyx offers a great single-player experience, but as the MedalMatrix, I''m disappointed by the lack of multiplayer achievements. I love to show off my achievements, and this game doesn''t give me much to display in that department. If you''re looking for a game to rack up multiplayer achievements, this isn''t it.', TRUE, 45, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 64 DAY)),
(1040, 20, 5, 'Received Half-Life: Alyx as a gift, and wow, what a pleasant surprise! I''m not usually one for VR, but this game absolutely captivated me. The interaction with the environment and the depth of the story were unexpected delights. It''s not something I would have picked for myself, but I''m glad someone did!', TRUE, 2, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 68 DAY)),
(1016, 20, 5, 'As the DeckDockedDevotee, I can happily say that Half-Life: Alyx runs beautifully on the Steam Deck. It''s such a joy to play a game that''s perfectly verified and optimized for my favorite device. The immersive VR experience translates surprisingly well, and I couldn''t be more thrilled with how smoothly everything performs. A perfect match for my gaming preferences!', TRUE, 4, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 337 DAY)),
(1034, 20, 5, 'As EarlyAccessAce, diving into the world of Half-Life: Alyx was an exhilarating experience that I had anticipated long before its release. The game mechanics are robust, and it truly pushes the boundary of what VR can offer for an original immersive gameplay. It''s a significant step forward for the Half-Life universe, making it a worthy addition to the series. My investment in this early has certainly paid off.', TRUE, 9, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 269 DAY)),
(1026, 20, 3, '8BitAdmirer here, and while Half-Life: Alyx delivers on atmosphere and storytelling, I can''t help but feel frustrated by the modern monetization trends I see creeping in. It''s a masterpiece wrapped in unnecessary DLC and potential microtransactions, diluting my nostalgia with commercial interests. It''s a shame to see such an iconic series lean towards these practices.', TRUE, 10, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 230 DAY)),
(1036, 20, 4, 'PatientPurchaser taking the stage: I waited for a sale before diving into Half-Life: Alyx, and I''m glad I did. The price point at launch seemed steep for VR-only gameplay, but with a discount, the breathtaking graphics and intricate details made it a thrilling bargain. Patience truly is a virtue when it comes to experiencing this gem.', TRUE, 20, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 149 DAY)),
(1024, 20, 5, 'LoreLoreAdores here, and Half-Life: Alyx delivers a narrative rich with the kind of depth and mystery I crave. The story unveils new layers of the Half-Life universe, leaving breadcrumbs of intrigue that only enhance my love for its vague yet compelling plot. This game elevates the lore to new heights, and I can''t get enough.', TRUE, 14, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 34 DAY)),
(1006, 20, 1, 'ReturnRebel reporting for duty: I had high hopes for Half-Life: Alyx, but found it frustrating due to VR motion sickness that made it unplayable for me. As a dedicated fan, I anticipated a seamless experience, yet the hardware limitations led to an immediate refund. Simply put, it''s unplayable for those not accustomed to VR, which is a huge disappointment.', FALSE, 17, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 140 DAY)),
(1048, 20, 5, 'AchievementUnlocked (The Achievement Hunter): Half-Life: Alyx offers a rewarding experience where the satisfaction of progression stems from its immersive narrative and clever puzzles rather than chasing multiplayer achievements. As an achievement hunter who prefers deep single-player games without the distraction of multiplayer unlocks, I found this VR masterpiece both captivating and refreshing. 5/5 for a pure, achievement-friendly adventure!', TRUE, 23, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 101 DAY)),
(1007, 20, 4, 'FearOfMissing (The FOMO Victim): Jumping into Half-Life: Alyx, I was initially concerned about missing out on the big VR buzz everyone was talking about. However, despite my FOMO-driven anxiety, Alyx delivered a standalone experience that felt both complete and gratifying without dangling any must-have limited-time content. Great graphics and storyline—worth experiencing at your own pace. 4/5.', TRUE, 2, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 143 DAY)),
(1044, 20, 4, 'ViewMasterVisionary (The Ultrawide User): As someone who can''t stand when games restrict my field of view, Half-Life: Alyx''s VR design actually embraces immersion in a way most ultrawide setups can''t. The world felt alive and expansive, and I could explore every nook and cranny without the confines of a static FOV. Kudos, Valve, for a virtual reality that doesn''t confine vision! 4.5/5.', TRUE, 1, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 278 DAY)),
(1051, 20, 4, 'FreeloaderKing (The F2P Leech): While I typically stick to games that don''t cost a dime, Half-Life: Alyx tempted me into opening my wallet. Though I grumbled about the price, there''s no denying the exceptional quality of this VR gem. A paywall? Sure. But one that leads to a treasure trove of unforgettable experiences. If you''re going to pay, it''s worth it for something of this caliber. 4/5.', TRUE, 9, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 247 DAY)),
(1030, 20, 5, 'WidescreenWiz (The Ultrawide User): Having a game trap me in a narrow field of view is infuriating, but Half-Life: Alyx in VR transcends those boundaries. The universe feels boundless, and the freedom from conventional screen limitations provides an unmatchable sense of presence and scale. Forget all complaints about FOV—this is what gaming should feel like! 5/5 for unleashing personal perspective!', TRUE, 58, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 3 DAY)),
(1050, 22, 3, 'As an avid collector of achievements, I thoroughly enjoyed diving into Terraria''s vast world. However, my enthusiasm took a hit with the multiplayer achievements. I appreciate a good challenge, but forcing players to team up for achievements feels like unnecessary padding. Solo warriors deserve a fair chance too. Still, the variety and creativity of the achievements make up for this shortcoming to some extent.', TRUE, 12, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 95 DAY)),
(1023, 22, 5, 'Terraria is an absolute playground for speedrunners who thrive on finding and exploiting glitches. The open-ended nature and countless possibilities mean each run is different. Discovering new glitches to shave seconds off my time keeps me coming back. Whether it''s bypassing bosses or clipping through terrain, this game is a speedrunner''s dream!', TRUE, 8, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 95 DAY)),
(1032, 22, 4, 'Terraria''s story isn''t written on the surface, but hidden in the crevices of its world. As a lore enthusiast, I find piecing together the cryptic hints about its history fascinating. The mysterious existence of ancient structures and the enigmatic NPC dialogues keep me invested, even when the plot isn''t overt. This game is a goldmine for those who love to dig deeper into the lore.', TRUE, 6, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 177 DAY)),
(1058, 22, 1, 'Honestly, I expected more from Terraria. The pixelated graphics make it look dated, and the lack of a clear tutorial left me wandering aimlessly for hours. I found the interface clunky and the controls unintuitive. If I can''t figure out how to play smoothly after several hours, it''s not worth my time. This one''s going back.', FALSE, 8, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 204 DAY)),
(1034, 22, 5, 'Having been a part of Terraria''s journey since its early access days, I''ve seen this game grow and transform magnificently. Every update brings something fresh, keeping it relevant and exciting. The developers listen to the community, and it shows in the game''s evolution. It''s a testament to what dedication and player feedback can achieve. Still invested, still impressed.', TRUE, 0, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 211 DAY)),
(1025, 22, 3, 'Terraria is a massive time sink, and while I can appreciate its charm, there''s always this nagging feeling that I''m missing out on something newer and shinier. The fear of missing out on the latest gaming trends makes it hard to fully immerse myself in the game. Still, it''s a classic for a reason. Worth experiencing at least once. But perhaps I''ve missed the prime time to truly enjoy it.', TRUE, 22, 90, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 93 DAY)),
(1026, 22, 4, 'Terraria is a nostalgic trip back to the golden era of gaming. The pixel art and simple mechanics are delightful, but my heart sinks every time I see a hint of modern monetization creeping into the gaming world. Thankfully, Terraria steers clear of that pitfall and lets players enjoy the game in its purest form, without any pay-to-win nonsense.', TRUE, 1, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 55 DAY)),
(1037, 22, 2, 'Ugh, Terraria''s single-player experience is pretty solid, but the multiplayer achievements are a dealbreaker for me. I despise being forced into multiplayer just to complete my achievement list. Why can''t we earn everything solo? It''s a frustrating obstacle for achievement hunters like myself.', FALSE, 1, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 253 DAY)),
(1021, 22, 5, 'Terraria''s challenging bosses and exploration mechanics deliver a thrilling experience for those who thrive on overcoming obstacles. The complexity and strategic depth are reminiscent of the toughest Soulsborne games. It''s incredibly satisfying to conquer its punishing world, and any fan of difficult games would feel right at home.', TRUE, 10, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 304 DAY)),
(1045, 22, 3, 'While Terraria may captivate many with its gameplay, I can''t help but be put off by the ''dated'' engine and graphics. The pixel art style might appeal to nostalgic gamers, but as a graphics snob, I crave cutting-edge visuals. Despite this, I do acknowledge the depth and creativity that the game offers.', TRUE, 7, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 1 DAY)),
(1043, 22, 3, 'As a QA tester, ''Terraria'' is a fascinating case. The mechanics are solid with meticulous attention to detail, but I did encounter some minor bugs which were mostly visual glitches that don''t affect gameplay. The game is quite polished, but there''s always room for improvement. A neutral stance seems fair, given the overall positive experience with just a hint of feedback for the developers.', TRUE, 2, 25, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 137 DAY)),
(1031, 22, 2, 'As an achievement hunter, I adore the challenge of collecting in ''Terraria'', yet the multiplayer achievements are a real letdown. They feel forced and not everyone has a group ready to tackle them, making it unnecessarily difficult to complete the full set of achievements. I wish the game had more single-player friendly achievements instead of these multiplayer ones that spoil the perfect score hunt.', FALSE, 28, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 157 DAY)),
(1049, 22, 2, 'I was hyped beyond measure for ''Terraria'' after hearing about its expansive sandbox world. However, the hype didn’t match my personal experience. The progression felt slightly overwhelming and the graphics aren''t my taste. Though it''s cherished by many, it didn''t resonate with me, which was a disappointment given all the anticipation.', FALSE, 0, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 7 DAY)),
(1028, 22, 2, 'Using a controller with ''Terraria'' is a struggle. The game''s inventory management and precision building are clearly designed with keyboard and mouse in mind. While I appreciate the effort put into making it controller supportive, it just doesn’t feel as intuitive. The controls were my biggest issue and really took away from the experience.', FALSE, 1, 53, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 310 DAY)),
(1012, 22, 3, 'From a QA tester''s perspective, ''Terraria'' is impressively stable for its depth. I combed through various scenarios and found only a few minor bugs. The balance between features and mechanics is quite well-maintained. Though not flawless, it’s one of the more resilient games I’ve tested with minimal game-breaking bugs.', TRUE, 2, 42, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 233 DAY)),
(1024, 22, 5, 'Terraria''s world is a treasure trove waiting to be unearthed. The lore is elusive and enigmatic, akin to piecing together ancient myths. Every cavern and jungle feels like a chapter in a forgotten tome, sparking the imagination of anyone willing to dig deeper.', TRUE, 11, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 180 DAY)),
(1007, 22, 4, 'Terraria is quite the interesting phenomenon. Not overly hyped like some AAA titles, but it doesn''t fall into obscurity either. It''s the perfect balance for someone like me who enjoys discovering games without the pressure of missing out.', TRUE, 1, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 114 DAY)),
(1055, 22, 5, 'Terraria is a rare gem in today''s market, free from the clutches of greedy monetization schemes. I can indulge in nostalgia without encountering paywalls and microtransactions. This game is a delightful reminder of simpler times when content was king.', TRUE, 6, 55, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 19 DAY)),
(1036, 22, 4, 'While I usually wait for games to go on sale, I must say Terraria offers excellent value for its price. The sheer amount of content and replayability more than justifies the cost, even at full price. A purchase well worth considering.', TRUE, 4, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 259 DAY)),
(1016, 22, 5, 'Playing Terraria on the Steam Deck is a dream. It''s verified and runs smoothly, making it perfect for both on-the-go and docked play sessions. The seamless experience is exactly what I look for in a portable gaming experience.', TRUE, 0, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 135 DAY)),
(1047, 22, 3, 'Terraria is a delight when it comes to gameplay and creativity, but my FPS soul aches every time the screen stutters during intense moments. A game so famed should not lag behind on optimization, especially when battling bosses or entering densely packed biomes. Please smooth these out for a seamless experience.', TRUE, 6, 54, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 93 DAY)),
(1004, 22, 4, 'Venturing through Terraria''s pixelated realms brings back the joy of old-school gaming. The lack of modern monetization schemes is a breath of fresh air in today''s gaming climate. However, I must remain vigilant; I hope they never succumb to unnecessary DLCs and loot boxes.', TRUE, 6, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 324 DAY)),
(1009, 22, 5, 'Terraria’s depth in crafting and exploration is an RPG enthusiast''s dream. The myriad of strategies and builds keep me engaged as I min-max my way through the endless challenges. The complexity of the game systems is truly a rewarding puzzle.', TRUE, 3, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 253 DAY)),
(1053, 22, 3, 'Terraria’s achievement system is robust and rewarding. Yet, the insistence on multiplayer achievements irks me. Not everyone enjoys or has access to multiplayer modes, and achievements should celebrate personal skill, not social connections.', TRUE, 9, 32, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 1 DAY)),
(1044, 22, 4, 'An expansive world like Terraria deserves to be admired in its full glory, but alas, the rigid FOV could use some improvement. For ultrawide users like myself, the side-scrolling is immersive, yet restrictive. A more adjustable FOV would elevate the experience substantially.', TRUE, 11, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 195 DAY)),
(1013, 22, 3, 'Terraria offers a solid gameplay experience, but from a QA perspective, there''s room for improvement. I encountered a few minor bugs that slightly broke immersion, but nothing game-breaking. The mechanics are well-crafted and complex, but the UI could use a bit of polish. Overall, it''s a well-tested game with just a couple of rough edges that need smoothing. For those looking for a sturdy experience, it''s worth diving into.  Neutral.', TRUE, 3, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 364 DAY)),
(1010, 22, 2, 'As a competitive gamer, Terraria frustrates me with its lack of defined victory conditions. There''s an easy mode that feels like it holds your hand, and that does not sit well with my spirit of competition. I want to conquer, to dominate, but in this open-ended adventure, it feels like there are no real opponents to defeat. If you''re like me and seek a challenge, you might feel out of place. I need my games to make me sweat, not just lay back and relax.', FALSE, 11, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 131 DAY)),
(1040, 22, 4, 'Terraria was a surprise gift, so I went in with zero expectations. To my delight, I found a pixelated world teeming with possibilities! From building quirky houses to discovering hidden treasures, each session is a new journey. It’s like being a kid in a candy store without knowing what the next sweet surprise will be. While I might not have picked it for myself, it''s a quirky gem I''m happy to have stumbled upon.', TRUE, 1, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 183 DAY)),
(1017, 22, 5, 'Customization is everything, and Terraria delivers in spades! From designing your character''s look to building elaborate structures with unique materials, this game is a dream for someone like me who loves to tailor every detail to perfection. The variety of items and equipment keeps me coming back for more, ensuring I can always express my style in the vibrant world. If you''re into crafting your own adventure, this is your playground.', TRUE, 17, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 52 DAY)),
(1000, 22, 5, 'Terraria is a paradise for those who hate paywalls! As someone who despises the rampant monetization in many modern games, it''s refreshing to explore a world where I can progress without ever feeling my wallet is being squeezed. Sure, there are options to buy extras, but they''re never necessary to enjoy the full experience. A free-to-play dream where freedom reigns supreme!', TRUE, 0, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 90 DAY)),
(1025, 23, 3, 'As someone who''s always on the lookout for the next big thing, Doom Eternal felt like fighting a battle both on-screen and off. The constant need to stay updated with patches and DLCs got me a bit overwhelmed. The game is exceptional, no doubt, but the fear of missing out when I''m not up to date is real.', TRUE, 22, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 117 DAY)),
(1001, 23, 5, 'This game is a speedrunner''s paradise! The glitches I can exploit make for some epic runs. Nothing beats the adrenaline of blasting through levels at breakneck speed. Every glitch is a new path, and I''m here for it.', TRUE, 24, 71, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 353 DAY)),
(1052, 23, 2, 'Doom Eternal''s narrow FOV feels like I''m peering through a letterbox. Ultrawide monitors are made for immersing in brutal demons-slaughtering action, yet it feels so constrained. The visuals are stunning, but the lack of customizable FOV is a letdown.', FALSE, 0, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 8 DAY)),
(1027, 23, 3, 'The single-player campaign is a blast, but the multiplayer achievements are a drag. Hunting achievements is my game, and I can''t stand when they hinge on multiplayer modes or other players'' whims. Please, spare the achievers!', TRUE, 2, 43, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 162 DAY)),
(1054, 23, 5, 'From pounding gunshots to the guttural growls of demons, the dynamic range in Doom Eternal is music to my ears. Each note of the soundtrack and every effect is beautifully crafted, creating an auditory experience that''s second to none.', TRUE, 1, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 63 DAY)),
(1000, 23, 4, 'Doom Eternal is an absolute thrill ride! The only downside is the upfront cost; I wish there was a way to play for free. Fortunately, there are no annoying paywalls locking away key features once you''ve paid. Solid game, but I''d still keep my wallet close!', TRUE, 7, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 321 DAY)),
(1031, 23, 5, 'A fantastic single-player experience! The intense action and intricate level design kept me coming back. However, I was relieved to find that the achievements focus on what you''re doing in the campaign rather than forcing multiplayer modes. Just how I like it!', TRUE, 3, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 121 DAY)),
(1044, 23, 4, 'Doom Eternal shreds with its action and ambiance, but I found the narrow Field of View to be a constraint on my ultrawide monitor. A bit more flexibility would make the battles feel even more epic. Overall, a great experience, but not maximizing my screen''s potential.', TRUE, 5, 36, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 55 DAY)),
(1036, 23, 5, 'I waited for a sale and it was worth every penny! Doom Eternal offers monstrous bang for your buck, even at its regular price. The thrilling campaign and replayability factor make it a solid investment, but I''m glad I got it at a discount.', TRUE, 11, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 343 DAY)),
(1009, 23, 4, 'Engaging and packed with intense combat, Doom Eternal challenges you to strategize and optimize your way through its sprawling levels. While not an RPG, the complexity in gameplay mechanics provides plenty of opportunities for those who love min-maxing their way to victory.', TRUE, 6, 22, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 33 DAY)),
(1006, 23, 1, 'As ''The Refund Rager'', buying Doom Eternal was a mistake. The game is an endless barrage of chaos and noise. The story is lost in all the senseless action, there''s no depth whatsoever. It’s a mindless shooter, and for the price, I expected more variety and innovation. Not worth the cash – one star for being a refund waiting to happen.', FALSE, 2, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 247 DAY)),
(1002, 23, 5, 'For someone like me, a fan of complex systems, Doom Eternal’s skill tree and weapon mod system are sheer joy! I love diving into the mechanics, figuring out optimal builds to outsmart the toughest demons. The game perfectly balances action with strategic depth. If you''re into maximizing your potential, this is a must-play. Five stars for the cerebral thrills!', TRUE, 15, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 316 DAY)),
(1042, 23, 5, 'Doom Eternal is a paradise for anyone who loves a challenge! As a Souls veteran, I crave games that push me to the edge, and this delivers on every level. The combat is fast-paced and brutal, demanding precise movement and relentless focus. Every successful demon takedown is a triumph. For those who thrive on difficulty, this is a masterpiece. Solid five stars!', TRUE, 4, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 321 DAY)),
(1051, 23, 5, 'Navigating Doom Eternal without hitting paywalls is a relief! As a F2P enthusiast, I detest games that hinder progress unless you spend extra cash. Doom Eternal is a complete package upfront, without microtransactions ruining the experience. It’s pure, unadulterated mayhem without financial frustration. Full marks for respecting gamers'' wallets. Five stars from me!', TRUE, 1, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 71 DAY)),
(1047, 23, 3, 'For an FPS fanatic like me, Doom Eternal could have been perfect if it wasn’t for the optimization hiccups. Despite the stellar gameplay, occasional frame drops and screen tearing took me out of the immersion. Performance-wise, it leaves some room for improvement. Three stars, because a game needs to run smoothly to be fully enjoyed.', TRUE, 0, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 277 DAY)),
(1021, 23, 5, 'Doom Eternal is an electrifying adrenaline rush that keeps you on your toes with its brutal difficulty. It''s not quite at the ''Souls'' level of punishing, but the challenge is there, and that''s what keeps me coming back for more. The combat is fast-paced and demands precision, and mastering the mechanics makes each victory immensely satisfying. A must-play for anyone who thrives on challenge.', TRUE, 8, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 253 DAY)),
(1043, 23, 4, 'Doom Eternal is a solid title with impressive graphics and engaging gameplay. As someone who tends to scrutinize games for bugs, I found the experience to be fairly polished. The action is relentless, and while it might not be groundbreaking, it delivers exactly what you’d expect from a Doom game: chaos, demons, and lots of shooting.', TRUE, 9, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 250 DAY)),
(1005, 23, 3, 'Doom Eternal offers a thrilling single-player campaign, but I can''t say the same for its multiplayer aspect. The multiplayer achievements feel tacked on and detract from the otherwise excellent experience. I''d prefer to focus on the single-player feats which truly test skill and dedication rather than being forced into multiplayer modes.', TRUE, 10, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 8 DAY)),
(1017, 23, 4, 'Customization in Doom Eternal is surprisingly extensive, with various skins and upgrades to keep players invested. For someone like me who enjoys personalizing my gameplay experience, this game doesn’t disappoint. The ability to tailor your Slayer with different looks and gear adds a fun, personal touch to all the demon-slaying madness.', TRUE, 10, 52, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 266 DAY)),
(1056, 23, 5, 'Doom Eternal is like a shot of adrenaline to the heart. The difficulty is exhilarating, almost reminiscent of a Souls game in its demand for timing and strategic thinking. Every encounter feels like a high-stakes battle, pushing me to refine my skills constantly. It''s an adventure that calls out to any gamer who craves challenging gameplay.', TRUE, 6, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 143 DAY)),
(1009, 24, 5, 'Control''s intricate ability tree and the depth of mods you can apply to Jesse''s powers truly impressed me. Each decision felt like a strategic chess move, allowing me to fine-tune my playstyle to perfection. The game''s complex mechanics and the compelling world demand a player''s attention and rewarding investment, making it a paradise for any RPG min-maxer.', TRUE, 12, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 199 DAY)),
(1034, 24, 5, 'As an early access enthusiast, Control hooked me instantly with its enigmatic storytelling and immersive physics. The game''s evolution from preview builds to full release shows a polished experience that retained its core charm. Remedy''s commitment to quality was evident from start to finish, making it a perfect example of what invested development should achieve. Eagerly awaiting future content expansions!', TRUE, 17, 61, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 225 DAY)),
(1058, 24, 1, 'Control was not worth my time or money. I found the story confusing, and the map navigation was frustratingly poor. The combat got repetitive quickly, and without a solid direction, I just couldn''t justify the purchase. People looking for a coherent and straightforward experience might want to reconsider. A 1-star product without a doubt.', FALSE, 1, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 351 DAY)),
(1010, 24, 3, 'The lack of a challenging difficulty mode in Control made it hard to stay invested. While the gameplay mechanics are unique, they felt underutilized due to the ease with which enemies are defeated. I crave a more punishing experience to ensure every decision matters and sadly, Control did not fulfill this competitive need.', TRUE, 1, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 256 DAY)),
(1033, 24, 4, 'Control delivers a solid package with a few rough edges. The story is captivating, but there are occasional glitches that pull you out of the immersion. Nonetheless, the atmospheric world and intriguing gameplay mechanics make it worth exploring. It''s a good title to play, especially if these rare bugs are patched.', TRUE, 21, 24, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 306 DAY)),
(1027, 24, 4, 'Control offers a thrilling experience with its intricate storyline and unique gameplay mechanics. As a dedicated achievement hunter, unlocking achievements in Control was a satisfying endeavor, though I was pleased to find that none were tied to multiplayer! The single-player focus allowed me to delve into the lore and polish off achievements at my own pace.', TRUE, 36, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 40 DAY)),
(1037, 24, 4, 'Control excels with its fascinating story and stunning visuals. As someone who treasures a complete achievement list, I appreciated how the game avoided the pitfall of multiplayer achievements, making it perfect for solo players who want to master every aspect of the game.', TRUE, 3, 29, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 230 DAY)),
(1035, 24, 4, 'As a QA tester, I appreciate how Control offers a polished experience with minimal bugs. The game''s mechanics hold up well under scrutiny, providing a solid and engaging narrative. It''s a rounded experience that doesn''t disappoint.', TRUE, 2, 46, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 178 DAY)),
(1044, 24, 3, 'Control''s cinematic experience is slightly marred by its lack of proper ultrawide support and a too rigid field of view. As an ultrawide user, I expected more flexibility in screen adjustments to fully immerse myself in the breathtaking world Remedy has crafted, but it still offers an engaging experience.', TRUE, 4, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 185 DAY)),
(1008, 24, 5, 'Having tested many games from their early stages, Control impressed with its intriguing narrative and captivating environments. Although some mechanics needed iterative improvements since the alpha stage, the final product is immersive and certainly worth the investment.', TRUE, 4, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 227 DAY)),
(1022, 24, 5, 'Control delivers a challenging experience that harkens back to the days when games required grit and determination. The combat mechanics and mind-bending visuals really put your skills to the test. It’s not Dark Souls, but its difficulty level gives it a run for its money. Enjoyed every second of the demanding battles and intricate puzzles.', TRUE, 3, 36, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 101 DAY)),
(1003, 24, 4, 'Played Control, and wow, it was like receiving a mystery box! One moment you''re in a normal office, the next you''re in a mind-bending, surreal adventure. It''s like a roller coaster where every twist is a surprise. Just pure, unadulterated fun in the most unpredictable ways.', TRUE, 2, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 340 DAY)),
(1014, 24, 2, 'Control would have been an intriguing game to dive into, but alas, the anti-cheat architecture puts a damper on things for a Linux enthusiast like me. It''s a pity because the storyline and game design look captivating, yet I cannot support platforms that restrict open-source operating systems.', FALSE, 0, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 103 DAY)),
(1018, 24, 2, 'Despite Control’s captivating narrative and exceptional design, the anti-cheat system is a dealbreaker. As a Linux user, it''s frustrating to see developers overlook platform inclusivity. This barrier clouds what could be a seamless gaming experience.', FALSE, 19, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 269 DAY)),
(1026, 24, 4, 'Control offers a gripping narrative with stunning visuals, and while the game itself is a masterpiece, I can''t help but notice the creeping shadow of modern monetization lurking behind every corner. Fortunately, it''s not too invasive here, but it’s a reminder of how gaming has changed. Still, the lack of aggressive in-game purchases is appreciated.', TRUE, 3, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 223 DAY)),
(1054, 24, 5, 'Control delivers a sonic experience that is a treat to the ears. The dynamic range is spectacular, with every whisper and explosion perfectly captured. The way sound is used to heighten tension or convey the surreal atmosphere in the game is masterful. It''s an immersive audiophile’s dream!', TRUE, 2, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 278 DAY)),
(1055, 24, 4, 'Control is a reminder of how far games have come, but the modern monetization tactics are a bane. Thankfully, Control doesn''t fall into the trap completely, allowing players to fully immerse themselves without being bombarded with microtransactions. Its clear focus on storytelling and atmosphere feels like a return to the golden era.', TRUE, 12, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 278 DAY)),
(1000, 24, 4, 'Control had me hooked with its intriguing premise and solid gameplay. However, the looming threat of paywalls in modern gaming always dampens my enthusiasm. Luckily, Control avoids this pitfall, offering a complete experience without holding content hostage behind a paywall.', TRUE, 15, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 32 DAY)),
(1013, 24, 4, 'From a quality assurance perspective, Control is polished with minimal bugs interrupting gameplay. The development team''s attention to detail is evident, although there are occasional frame drops. Overall, a solid and glitch-free experience.', TRUE, 8, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 216 DAY)),
(1005, 24, 5, 'Control excels in its single-player achievements, offering a satisfying path to 100% completion without needing to engage in frustrating multiplayer modes. The focus on creative challenges within the narrative framework is commendable.', TRUE, 1, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 185 DAY)),
(1015, 24, 3, 'Control was a fascinating experience on Linux with Proton, but the anti-cheat software required an extra tweak to get it running smoothly. It''s disappointing that developers aren''t considering native Linux support, as anti-cheat mechanisms often overlook our system.', TRUE, 17, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 261 DAY)),
(1016, 24, 5, 'Control runs like a dream on the Steam Deck! Its verified status gives me peace of mind, and the game perfectly suits on-the-go gaming. The performance is consistent, and the controls feel intuitive, making it a must-play on this platform.', TRUE, 5, 79, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 87 DAY)),
(1029, 24, 4, 'Control captivates with its fantastic gameplay and visuals, but I despise how it locks cosmetic content behind additional purchases. I prefer to experience a game in its entirety without having to dish out extra cash. It''s a great game with unnecessary monetization.', TRUE, 0, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 74 DAY)),
(1004, 24, 3, 'Control is a visual masterpiece and an engaging experience, but it seems like every new game has some hidden costs or subscription model these days. I miss the days of buying a game and owning all it had to offer. While Control does it less offensively, it still partakes in this modern trend.', TRUE, 14, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 303 DAY)),
(1040, 24, 5, 'I received Control as a gift and was pleasantly surprised! The storyline is mind-bending, and the world is immersive. It''s exhilarating to play a game that keeps you guessing and leaves you in awe with its graphics and storytelling.', TRUE, 6, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 52 DAY)),
(1024, 25, 5, 'Death Stranding is an enigmatic tapestry woven with strands of existential musings and cryptic symbols. Every step Sam takes on his journey unravels a mystery draped in allegory—echoing themes of connection and isolation. The narrative is an intricate puzzle begging to be pieced together by the lore enthusiast in me. This is a masterwork of ambiguity that draws you in deeper with every delivery.', TRUE, 26, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 182 DAY)),
(1029, 25, 4, 'I was concerned about microtransactions, but I''m glad Death Stranding took a different path. While some cosmetics and conveniences could have easily been paywalled, the game instead opts for a more inclusive approach. It’s refreshing to see a title that respects its players without constantly reaching into their pockets. This is a rare gem for those tired of paywalls.', TRUE, 29, 23, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 253 DAY)),
(1015, 25, 2, 'As a Linux user, Death Stranding’s decision to include Denuvo anti-cheat was disappointing. Though the game itself is a breathtaking visual journey with stunning landscapes and a unique storyline, the anti-cheat software presents a barrier for those who value openness and control over their systems. It’s a shame that such a captivating experience has this blemish.', FALSE, 0, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 125 DAY)),
(1043, 25, 3, 'From a QA perspective, Death Stranding stands strong. The game is polished, with minimal bugs and glitches. The mechanics, though unconventional, are implemented with care, though they might not appeal to everyone. This game is more of an experience than just a playthrough. If you approach it with patience and an open mind, it’s worth exploring.', TRUE, 17, 31, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 286 DAY)),
(1059, 25, 1, 'I don''t get the hype around Death Stranding. The slow and meandering gameplay tested my patience, and I ended up requesting a refund. The story presented didn''t engage me, and the game felt more like a chore simulator. A one-star for not living up to my expectations and for failing to justify its steep price tag.', FALSE, 3, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 135 DAY)),
(1013, 25, 3, 'As a QA Tester, I''ve seen my fair share of game mechanics, and Death Stranding is a mixed bag. On one hand, it''s a technical marvel with beautifully rendered environments and fluid animations. However, I found some of the systems, like inventory management, a bit cumbersome and repetitive. It''s clear that a lot of effort went into polishing the game, but there are areas where the user experience feels a bit clunky. Overall, it''s a solid experience but not without its quirks.', TRUE, 1, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 162 DAY)),
(1040, 25, 4, 'I received Death Stranding as a gift, and honestly, I had no idea what to expect! This game''s an experience, alright. One moment I''m delivering packages in the rain, and the next I''m trying to figure out what''s up with those ghostly BTs. It''s definitely unlike anything I''ve played before. The story''s a bit of a head-scratcher, but I loved the wild ride. Random, unexpected, but oddly satisfying as a gift.', TRUE, 8, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 113 DAY)),
(1026, 25, 3, 'Being a fan of classic games, I''m usually wary of modern titles that focus more on monetization than gameplay. Thankfully, Death Stranding doesn''t fall into the trap of aggressive monetization. It offers a unique gameplay loop focused on exploration and story, rather than trying to nickel and dime you at every turn. Still, I miss the straightforwardness of older games, but this one at least respects its players in that regard.', TRUE, 13, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 352 DAY)),
(1052, 25, 4, 'As an Ultrawide User, visual experience is paramount, and I must say Death Stranding delivers stunning vistas. However, the lack of field of view (FOV) customization is a real downside for me. It could have enhanced the cinematic experience even further. Despite this limitation, the game still manages to impress with its openness and incredible detail, but I can''t help but feel constrained by the rigid FOV settings.', TRUE, 0, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 196 DAY)),
(1041, 25, 5, 'Having experienced Death Stranding since its early stages, I''ve been deeply invested in its journey. The combination of storytelling, atmosphere, and innovation kept me hooked from the start. Kojima''s vision is bold and distinct, and while it may not cater to every gamer''s taste, for those of us who appreciate a well-crafted narrative and technical innovation, it''s a masterpiece. The evolution from alpha to launch has been remarkable.', TRUE, 0, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 24 DAY)),
(1002, 25, 5, 'As an RPG Min-Maxer, Death Stranding is a brilliant amalgamation of complex systems that demand strategic thought and planning. The way resources are allocated and logistics come into play is a fresh challenge for those who enjoy optimizing every element of gameplay. Every journey in the game feels like an intricate puzzle, where each decision impacts the efficiency of your delivery. It''s a deeply rewarding experience for anyone who thrives on mechanical depth and cerebral gameplay.', TRUE, 9, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 208 DAY)),
(1037, 25, 3, 'While I relish the challenge of hunting down achievements, Death Stranding disappoints with its focus on solitary exploration rather than multiplayer challenges. The achievements are interesting but lack the cooperative or competitive spirit I crave. However, the nuanced gameplay and engrossing narrative make up for it to some extent. If you can get past the solo aspect, there’s a lot of exploration and hidden challenges to keep an achievement hunter engaged.', TRUE, 13, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 65 DAY)),
(1001, 25, 4, 'For a speedrunner who loves discovering and exploiting glitches, Death Stranding offers a surprisingly stable playground. While the physics engine has a few quirks, it''s mostly well-polished. The game’s sprawling landscapes provide plenty of room for route optimization and shaving seconds off each delivery. Though it doesn''t have the glitch-riddled chaos of some classics, the potential for innovation in pathfinding and time management is a delightful puzzle in itself.', TRUE, 0, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 2 DAY)),
(1020, 25, 1, 'Death Stranding is an exhausting trek masked as a game. The gameplay is tedious and delivers little satisfaction for the effort required. I found myself frustrated by the monotonous delivery systems and tedious mechanics. This is one of those games that could really use a more dynamic and engaging core, but instead, it just leaves you wandering aimlessly across barren landscapes. Not worth the time or money.', FALSE, 5, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 266 DAY)),
(1036, 25, 4, 'Having waited patiently for a sale, I feel satisfied with the value I got from Death Stranding. The game is an investment of time and patience, and while the price drop made it an undeniable bargain, the gameplay itself holds its own weight. The visuals and storytelling are mesmerizing, offering a unique experience for those willing to immerse themselves. Strategic when on sale, this title provides a truly unforgettable narrative journey.', TRUE, 17, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 271 DAY)),
(1009, 25, 4, 'Death Stranding is an absolute goldmine for those who thrive on complexity. The intricate systems, from cargo management algorithms to terrain navigation, provide endless opportunities to optimize routes and perfect strategies. Although it''s not an RPG in the traditional sense, the depth of interaction with the environment and tools keeps a min-maxer like me thoroughly engaged. The layers of planning involved in each delivery tick all the right boxes.', TRUE, 2, 26, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 299 DAY)),
(1044, 25, 3, 'Playing Death Stranding on a standard FOV is like viewing a masterpiece through a keyhole. The vastness of its landscapes deserves an ultrawide screen to truly appreciate the breathtaking vistas and expansive world design. Unfortunately, the fixed field of view limits the immersive experience I crave. It''s a visual feast, but one that feels restricted by the lack of FOV customization.', TRUE, 2, 36, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 206 DAY)),
(1010, 25, 2, 'As a competitive gamer, Death Stranding isn''t typically in my wheelhouse, but I gave it a shot. While the delivery challenges can be rigorous, the lack of player vs. player combat or a ranking system means there’s no real competitive edge to sharpen. The experience feels more like a meditative journey than a test of skill. Props for uniqueness, but the tension of competition is sorely missed.', FALSE, 3, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 131 DAY)),
(1027, 25, 4, 'Death Stranding offers an impressive array of achievements, and for that, I commend it. However, I was relieved to find that none rely on multiplayer interactions. It allows for a solitary completionist run that''s incredibly satisfying. The puzzles and varied milestones provide ample rewards for persistence, making it a dream for achievement hunters.', TRUE, 4, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 313 DAY)),
(1049, 25, 2, 'Death Stranding was hyped to be a groundbreaking release, but it feels more like an overextension of ambition. The story is intriguing, yet the gameplay loops are often monotonous and overly long. Despite the beautiful graphics and star-studded cast, it falls short of the awe-inspiring experience it was promised to be. A classic case of hype overshadowing substance.', FALSE, 1, 33, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 299 DAY)),
(1022, 25, 3, 'Death Stranding is a beautiful journey, but where''s the thrill of a tough boss fight? The environment is mesmerizing, and the delivery mechanic is unique, but I craved more challenging encounters. A bit slow for my taste, but it got a certain charm if you enjoy the grind. 3/5 for difficulty lovers.', TRUE, 4, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 205 DAY)),
(1057, 25, 4, 'The open world is vast and stunning, a modder''s dream come true! The intricate game files offer so many possibilities for customization, and the world-building is a sandbox of creativity. Kojima''s vision is clear, and with a little tweaking, this could be an eternal masterpiece. 4/5 for modding potential.', TRUE, 4, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 78 DAY)),
(1008, 25, 4, 'I''ve been with Death Stranding since the first teasers, and it''s been a ride. The gameplay loop is unique, and the narrative, though cryptic, is intriguing. I enjoyed the evolution of this title from concept to execution. It was worth the anticipation, and it''s nice to see innovation. 4/5 for being invested in its journey.', TRUE, 1, 24, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 243 DAY)),
(1011, 25, 2, 'Fell for the hype and got strung along with deliveries instead of action. Yeah, the graphics are stunning, and the concept is different, but it felt more like a walking sim than a gripping gameplay experience. Definitely not what I expected after all the build-up. 2/5 for the hype mismatch.', FALSE, 9, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 27 DAY)),
(1014, 25, 3, 'Death Stranding, impressive but the anti-cheat made it a struggle on Linux. Valve''s Proton got it running, yet not without issues. The beautiful landscapes deserve smoother sailing. It''s a mixed bag - fascinating yet held back for us in the penguin crowd. 3/5 for the Linux hurdles.', TRUE, 12, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 250 DAY)),
(1021, 26, 4, 'Resident Evil Village offers a thrilling atmosphere, but if you''re looking for a difficulty that leaves you breathless like the Souls series, you might find the challenges here a tad forgiving. The bosses are memorable, but once you''ve cracked their patterns, they''re not quite the punishing gauntlet I had hoped for. Still, the tension and survival elements are worth experiencing for fans of a spooky challenge.', TRUE, 5, 27, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 142 DAY)),
(1002, 26, 3, 'As a fan of intricate RPGs, I was hoping for a bit more depth in the character customization and upgrade system. Resident Evil Village certainly has its own complexity with weapon upgrades and crafting, yet it lacks the satisfying complexities of a true RPG. However, for what it is, the game''s narrative and puzzle elements do provide a cerebral experience that can be enjoyed greatly.', TRUE, 12, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 76 DAY)),
(1057, 26, 4, 'The game comes with a tightly-knitted narrative experience, and while modding opportunities are limited due to its linear nature, there''s a world of potential in those little nooks and crannies waiting for adventurous modders to explore. Resident Evil Village could thrive with community creativity if only Capcom were more mod-friendly.', TRUE, 1, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 69 DAY)),
(1053, 26, 5, 'Ethan Winters’ latest outing is a feast for an achievement hunter – a bounty of challenges and secrets await! Thankfully, Resident Evil Village doesn’t bog you down with frustrating multiplayer achievements, allowing for a purely single-player trophy pursuit. It’s a pleasure to aim for Platinum without the distraction of online connections.', TRUE, 0, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 291 DAY)),
(1018, 26, 3, 'Running Resident Evil Village on Linux is a bit of a journey. The game’s DRM and anti-cheat system can cause a bit of turbulence, making it less than ideal for seamless play. However, with persistence and a bit of technical wizardry, you can get it running smoothly on your penguin-powered rig. Just be prepared for a bit of tinkering.', TRUE, 6, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 247 DAY)),
(1059, 26, 1, 'I had high hopes for Resident Evil Village, given the hype, but it was a colossal letdown. The game is riddled with over-hyped elements that just don''t deliver. The horror feels too manufactured, and the gameplay is nothing but repetitive and predictable. As someone who doesn''t tolerate mediocrity, it''s hard not to feel robbed of my time and money. I couldn’t get that refund fast enough.', FALSE, 0, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 204 DAY)),
(1007, 26, 3, 'Resident Evil Village offers a mixed bag of experiences. The visuals are stunning, and the storyline is intriguing enough to keep me engaged, but there''s something about it that doesn''t quite stand out. It''s a decent addition to the series, but it doesn''t evoke strong feelings either way. It''s somewhere in the middle, neither thrilling nor disappointing.', TRUE, 30, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 36 DAY)),
(1003, 26, 4, 'I played Resident Evil Village after receiving it as a surprise gift, and it turned out to be quite a wild ride. The graphics were amazing, and the creepy atmosphere was on point, but some parts felt a bit overwhelming. I didn''t know what to expect walking in, and while it was fun, I can''t say I''m rushing to play it again. Still, it was a unique experience!', TRUE, 2, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 162 DAY)),
(1041, 26, 5, 'As an avid fan of the Resident Evil franchise, Village did not disappoint! The attention to detail in the environment and the seamless storytelling kept me glued to the screen. I appreciated the intricate puzzles and the diverse array of enemies, which made the game a captivating experience from start to finish. This installment has definitely set a high bar for future releases.', TRUE, 5, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 298 DAY)),
(1022, 26, 5, 'Resident Evil Village truly tested my mettle with its challenging gameplay and relentless enemies. The intense atmosphere combined with the strategic combat made for an exhilarating experience. As someone who thrives on difficulty, this game was a perfect match. The satisfaction of conquering each boss battle is something only true Souls veterans will appreciate. It''s a thrilling journey!', TRUE, 2, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 328 DAY)),
(1001, 26, 4, 'FastTrackFlash (The Speedrunner): Resident Evil Village has some sweet glitches perfect for speedrunning! The consistent clipping through walls and item duping make any run exciting. However, the game does tighten up some areas, limiting potential skips. Still, a thrilling experience for speed enthusiasts. 4/5 stars.', TRUE, 0, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 335 DAY)),
(1012, 26, 3, 'BugHunterBeta (The QA Tester): Resident Evil Village is a visually stunning game with atmospheric environments and challenging gameplay. However, while the game is polished, I noticed minor bugs that occasionally detract from immersion, like audio desyncs and minor texture pop-ins. Overall, a decent experience, but could use some more fine-tuning in patches. 3/5 stars.', TRUE, 8, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 358 DAY)),
(1046, 26, 4, 'GamePadGuru (The Controller User): Resident Evil Village delivers an immersive horror experience but playing with a keyboard/mouse feels cumbersome! Thankfully, the game shines when using a controller, where aiming and movement feel natural and responsive. Keyboard users beware, but for controller fans, it''s an enjoyable ride. 4/5 stars.', TRUE, 30, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 227 DAY)),
(1036, 26, 3, 'PatientPurchaser (The Wait for Sale): Resident Evil Village is a fun game, but the launch price felt steep for the content length. It''s definitely worth playing for the atmosphere and story, but if you''re budget-conscious like me, wait for a discount. A solid entry in the series, but patience pays off. 3/5 stars.', TRUE, 0, 38, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 4 DAY)),
(1052, 26, 2, 'AspectRatioRenegade (The Ultrawide User): Resident Evil Village is visually stunning, but the lack of proper ultrawide support is disappointing. The forced letterboxing ruins immersion, and the rigid FOV can feel claustrophobic at times. Until they fix these issues, it''s hard to fully enjoy the game on ultrawide monitors. 2/5 stars.', FALSE, 1, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 351 DAY)),
(1005, 26, 4, 'Resident Evil Village is a thrilling addition to the series with plenty of achievements to sink your teeth into. The single-player trophies are rewarding, but I’m relieved to see there’s no multiplayer grind. The Mercenaries mode is a nice touch for replay value with its own set of challenges. Overall, it’s a trophy hunter’s dream come true with a satisfying balance of difficulty and creativity.', TRUE, 27, 24, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 173 DAY)),
(1040, 26, 5, 'I received Resident Evil Village as a gift, and it was a pleasant surprise! The atmosphere is incredibly immersive, and the story kept me on the edge of my seat. The graphics and sound design are top-notch, making it an unforgettable experience. It’s a game that I never knew I needed, but I’m so glad I got to play. Would definitely recommend it to anyone who enjoys a good scare.', TRUE, 8, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 355 DAY)),
(1017, 26, 4, 'As someone who enjoys diving deep into customization, Resident Evil Village offers a satisfying crafting system and weapon upgrades. However, I wish there were more character cosmetic options to personalize Ethan and the companions he encounters. The environment and detail in each village area are exquisite, though, making exploration rewarding in its own way.', TRUE, 42, 85, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 280 DAY)),
(1044, 26, 3, 'Playing Resident Evil Village on an ultrawide monitor is a mixed bag. The game’s visuals are stunning, but the field of view feels a bit too constricted for my taste. I wish there was more flexibility with the FOV settings to really take advantage of my 21:9 setup. That aside, the village and its inhabitants are hauntingly beautiful and well worth the journey.', TRUE, 6, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 264 DAY)),
(1028, 26, 5, 'Resident Evil Village is a blast on the controller! The controls are smooth and responsive, making it easy to dive into the action without fussing over keyboard shortcuts. The tension and adrenaline rush during combat are perfectly complemented by the seamless control mechanics. This game is a testament to how horror games should be played!', TRUE, 23, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 341 DAY)),
(1040, 27, 5, 'Wow, It Takes Two was quite the surprise! I received it as a gift, and had no idea what to expect. The game is brilliantly designed, with a story that''s both heartwarming and hilarious. The puzzles are just challenging enough to be fun, making it a perfect game to play with a friend. It''s a gift that keeps on giving!', TRUE, 26, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 244 DAY)),
(1053, 27, 3, 'As someone who hunts achievements, It Takes Two was a mixed bag. The game is packed with creativity, but relying on a partner to unlock some achievements was frustrating. I prefer single-player challenges that test my personal skills, not multiplayer ones. Still, the journey was enjoyable, even if I had to coordinate with someone else.', TRUE, 8, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 169 DAY)),
(1028, 27, 4, 'I had an amazing experience with It Takes Two on my controller! The game controls are intuitive and smooth, which made the gameplay feel natural and fluid. It’s a great reminder of how some games are meant to be played without a keyboard and mouse. The joy of platforming with precise control is truly unmatched.', TRUE, 16, 29, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 189 DAY)),
(1012, 27, 4, 'Playing It Takes Two was a pretty standard experience from a QA perspective. The game mostly ran smoothly without any major bugs. The creative levels and mechanics were interesting, but nothing too surprising from a testing standpoint. It felt like a well-polished game, which is always a good thing.', TRUE, 0, 46, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 129 DAY)),
(1051, 27, 5, 'I loved that It Takes Two had no paywalls! It’s refreshing to play a game where you don’t hit any content blockers just because you haven’t paid extra. The entire game was available without needing to spend more money, which is rare these days. Kudos for keeping it accessible and fun for everyone.', TRUE, 1, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 118 DAY)),
(1045, 27, 3, 'ResolutionRadical (The Graphics Snob): It Takes Two surprises with its charming aesthetics and creative design, yet the engine sometimes struggles to deliver the visual fidelity one would expect in this era. While the art style is delightful, some textures appear dated, lacking the razor-sharp detail that elevates modern graphics. I can''t help but think a more cutting-edge engine would have elevated the experience to like a masterpiece. Still, the imaginative worlds are a feast for the eyes if you don''t squint too hard.', TRUE, 2, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 29 DAY)),
(1050, 27, 4, 'BadgeBringer (The Achievement Hunter): While It Takes Two is a delightful gameplay experience, the multiplayer achievements are a source of endless frustration. I understand the game''s cooperative nature, but forcing players to partner for every achievement is a tall order. Solo achievement hunters may find themselves tethered to a partner for far too long, which somewhat spoils the thrill of the hunt. It''s a blast to play, but the achievement system feels like a missed opportunity for those of us who relish solo achievement hunting.', TRUE, 3, 41, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 4 DAY)),
(1018, 27, 3, 'KernelCommander (The Linux User): My experience with It Takes Two was tainted not by its gameplay, but by its use of anti-cheat software that doesn''t mesh well with Linux. Playing through Proton, I faced a few hurdles but managed to enjoy the game. The creativity and cooperative mechanics are a joy, but I wish developers would give more consideration to users who aren''t on mainstream operating systems. Thankfully, the Proton community comes to the rescue, yet native support would make it a flawless experience.', TRUE, 4, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 189 DAY)),
(1002, 27, 5, 'StatSorcerer (The RPG Min-Maxer): It Takes Two doesn''t flaunt the complexity of typical RPGs, yet it offers a rich tapestry of mechanics that require cooperation and strategy. The various levels present unique challenges, each demanding careful coordination with your partner. While it lacks traditional min-maxing elements, optimizing strategies with a friend provides its own rewarding complexity. This is a game where collaboration is king, and the mechanics intricately intertwine to create an unforgettable adventure.', TRUE, 3, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 282 DAY)),
(1008, 27, 5, 'PreBetaPioneer (The Alpha Tester): It Takes Two feels like the polished result of a game that should have had a few public alphas. The final product is finely tuned, and the level of detail in the puzzles and environments shows a deep level of investment from the developers. It''s rare to see such dedication to cooperative gameplay, and the innovative mechanics are a testament to its various testing phases. As someone who follows games from alpha to release, It Takes Two stands as a remarkable achievement in the realm of polished cooperative experiences.', TRUE, 21, 26, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 81 DAY)),
(1003, 27, 5, 'GiftBoxBandit (The Gift Recipient): This game was like receiving a delightful gift out of nowhere! The whimsical journey, the vibrant worlds, and the clever puzzles were all unexpected surprises wrapped in joy. Whether you''re playing with a friend or a loved one, the game''s ability to bring two people together in such a fun and cooperative manner is truly special. It''s a game that keeps on giving, even after the credits roll!', TRUE, 5, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 193 DAY)),
(1011, 27, 2, 'HypewaveHero (The Hype Victim): Honestly, ''It Takes Two'' didn''t live up to the hype for me. The graphics are decent, but the storytelling feels cliché and the characters, though quirky, never quite drew me in. I was expecting a groundbreaking experience but instead found it to be just another co-op platformer with a few gimmicks here and there. Maybe it''s just me, but I felt let down by the end.', FALSE, 4, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 298 DAY)),
(1023, 27, 4, 'TimeTrialTornado (The Speedrunner): I adore when games have unintentional skips, and ''It Takes Two'' didn''t disappoint! Discovering glitches in the vast and colorful worlds added an extra layer of fun to each playthrough. Chasing those perfect runs and shaving off precious seconds with creative exploits became a game within the game. For any speedrunner looking for a new challenge, this game is a hidden gem.', TRUE, 0, 35, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 218 DAY)),
(1013, 27, 3, 'GlitchGuru (The QA Tester): ''It Takes Two'' strikes a balance between innovation and playability. While there are some minor bugs, overall, the game runs smoothly and feels polished. It''s fascinating to see how it utilizes cooperative mechanics to create an engaging experience. Not groundbreaking, but it certainly provides a solid playthrough that most players will appreciate.', TRUE, 15, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 81 DAY)),
(1022, 27, 4, 'BossBattleBrute (The Souls Veteran): This game isn''t about punishing difficulty, but the challenging puzzles and interactive boss battles add enough spice to keep me entertained. The beauty is in the strategy and precision required during certain segments. It''s a refreshing break from the relentless grind of Soulsborne games, yet it offers its own brand of satisfying complexity. A different kind of challenge, but enjoyable in its own right.', TRUE, 16, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 252 DAY)),
(1016, 27, 5, 'As a Steam Deck enthusiast who thrives on verified games, ''It Takes Two'' runs like a dream on my device. The controls are snappy and precise, and the graphics performance is buttery smooth even in some of the more visually intense scenes. It''s rare to find such a perfectly optimized game that truly leverages what the Steam Deck is capable of. Co-op has never felt so seamless, and it''s an absolute joy to play on the go.', TRUE, 8, 10, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 230 DAY)),
(1036, 27, 4, 'Okay, let''s be real, I''m all about grabbing the best games when they hit a sale. ''It Takes Two'' was worth the wait! Though full price might pinch some, the cooperative journey is an absolute bargain hunter''s dream. The creativity and fun packed into each level make it feel like I''m getting multiple games for the price of one. So, if you''re patient like me, snag this on sale and relish every moment without breaking the bank.', TRUE, 9, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 325 DAY)),
(1032, 27, 5, 'Oh, the allure of a story that teases and intrigues! ''It Takes Two'' is a narrative gem wrapped in layers of playful mystery. For someone who dives into lore with fervor, this game offers a brilliantly woven tale that invites speculation and theorizing. The characters'' emotional depth is extraordinary, and the narrative never spoon-feeds. It''s a delightful puzzle for the story-loving mind.', TRUE, 1, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 49 DAY)),
(1019, 27, 3, 'As a ''DarkSoulsDisciple'', I''m always questing for a hearty challenge. While ''It Takes Two'' doesn''t tread the same path of punishing difficulty, it offers its own brand of challenge in the form of cooperative puzzles and platforming precision. The emphasis on teamwork over single-player skill is a refreshing twist, and though it won''t test your endurance like a Souls game, its innovation keeps you engaged.', TRUE, 10, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 273 DAY)),
(1055, 27, 5, 'Remember the good old days when games were just games? ''It Takes Two'' is like a time capsule, free from modern monetization nonsense. Instead of endless microtransactions, you get a full, rich experience right out of the box. It''s a throwback to an era where fun was the priority, and every level felt meticulously crafted. For those weary of today''s monetization tactics, this game is a breath of pure nostalgic air.', TRUE, 19, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 232 DAY)),
(1047, 27, 4, 'As FPSFanatic, I must say that performance is key, and ''It Takes Two'' delivers a rock-solid experience. No noticeable frame drops or stuttering, even during the most intense co-op moments. It''s refreshing to play a game that prioritizes smooth gameplay. My only gripe is some minor texture pop-in, but overall, the optimization is top-notch.', TRUE, 5, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 353 DAY)),
(1034, 27, 5, 'From the perspective of EarlyAccessAce, ''It Takes Two'' is a remarkable journey that feels like a polished gem. The developers clearly invested time in refining each aspect of the game. The cooperative mechanics are seamless, and the narrative is both engaging and heartwarming. This is a testament to what dedication in game development looks like.', TRUE, 2, 44, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 45 DAY)),
(1014, 27, 5, 'As PenguinPlayer, I''m always wary of intrusive anti-cheat systems, but ''It Takes Two'' respects my Linux setup beautifully. There are no cumbersome barriers that interfere with gameplay. The game runs smoothly on my OS, and I appreciate the devs for making it accessible to all players, regardless of their platform preference.', TRUE, 17, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 243 DAY)),
(1026, 27, 4, 'With 8BitAdmirer''s perspective, I felt a genuine emotional connection while playing ''It Takes Two'' that reminded me of simpler gaming times. Thankfully, it''s devoid of those pesky modern monetization traps like loot boxes and microtransactions. It''s a pure gaming experience that harkens back to the good old days.', TRUE, 12, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 95 DAY)),
(1031, 27, 3, 'As TrophyTriumph, I can appreciate the challenge of ''It Takes Two,'' but I loathe multiplayer achievements. While the game is designed for co-op, some achievements undeniably require a second player, making it hard for solo achievement hunters to complete. Nevertheless, the unique challenges make the journey worthwhile.', TRUE, 5, 35, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 251 DAY)),
(1009, 27, 5, 'It Takes Two is a delightful labyrinth of mechanics for those who relish unraveling complexity. The game offers a myriad of abilities and minigames that challenge your strategic prowess at every turn. Every aspect feels meticulously designed, encouraging the type of optimization that excites any Min-Maxer. I found myself constantly figuring out synergies and efficiencies with the tools available. A true playground for the strategic mind.', TRUE, 3, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 247 DAY)),
(1039, 27, 5, 'As a parent with limited gaming time, It Takes Two was a breath of fresh air. The cooperative nature of the gameplay meant I could enjoy it with my partner without any of the tedious grinding that plagues so many games today. The story was heartwarming and engaging, capturing the magic of simple, straightforward fun. It was a perfect way to unwind and bond without the frustration of complex or time-consuming mechanics.', TRUE, 0, 76, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 192 DAY)),
(1004, 27, 5, 'In today''s gaming landscape, It''s rare to find a title that stays true to its roots without falling into the traps of modern monetization. It Takes Two felt like a trip back to when games were crafted with love, focusing on experience and gameplay rather than microtransactions and DLCs. The split-screen co-op feature was a nostalgic nod to the past, reminding me why I fell in love with gaming in the first place.', TRUE, 15, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 201 DAY)),
(1058, 27, 1, 'I expected an engaging experience when I picked up It Takes Two, and although it looks visually appealing, I found myself bogged down by what felt like unnecessary complexities. While some might appreciate the challenges it offers, I struggled to find the instant gratification that keeps me hooked on games. The storyline didn''t quite connect with me, and the puzzles felt more like chores than fun challenges. I didn''t find enough value in the gameplay to justify the time commitment.', FALSE, 2, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 244 DAY)),
(1059, 27, 1, 'Honestly, I was drawn to It Takes Two because of the hype, but it just didn''t click for me. I found myself getting frustrated with the pacing and the forced cooperative aspect. Maybe I''m just not the target audience, but I couldn''t get into the storyline, and the gameplay didn''t keep me entertained. It felt like a chore to go through, and I ended up wanting a refund more than anything else.', FALSE, 4, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 324 DAY)),
(1017, 28, 5, 'MegaWhale (The Whale): As someone who thrives on customization, Disco Elysium offers a cerebral playground. The depth of the skill tree is endlessly rewarding, allowing me to tailor my detective’s psyche to a truly unique personality. Every choice feels monumental which is just the kind of package a Whale like me revels in! The narrative intricacies keep me invested for hours on end.', TRUE, 7, 6, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 364 DAY)),
(1014, 28, 3, 'PenguinPlayer (The Linux User): Disco Elysium has everything but the Linux support. It’s a captivating narrative that kept me hooked, but the lack of native support for my OS and a potential anti-cheat complication keeps me cautious. Compatibility issues are a dealbreaker when I just want to immerse myself without tinkering beyond the game. Still, can''t deny its brilliance.', TRUE, 18, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 116 DAY)),
(1059, 28, 1, 'DepositDecliner (The Refund Rager): I was ready to request a refund, expecting something different entirely. While the story was okay, the pacing was too slow for my taste. The lack of action and traditional gameplay elements didn''t meet my expectations and left me feeling like I wasted my time. Needed more excitement for me!', FALSE, 22, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 34 DAY)),
(1001, 28, 4, 'FastTrackFlash (The Speedrunner): Disco Elysium isn''t a typical speedrunner’s paradise, but it''s a beautiful anomaly. The game’s narrative offers conversational ''glitches'' that open up faster solutions or ridiculous outcomes if you know how to navigate it. The dialogue trees can loop back on themselves unexpectedly, which for a runner is like finding hidden paths in a maze.', TRUE, 10, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 294 DAY)),
(1040, 28, 5, 'WishListWinner (The Gift Recipient): I got Disco Elysium as a surprise gift, and while I didn''t know what to expect, it turned out to be an immersive experience like no other. The layers of narrative complexity and moral quandaries are both daunting and rewarding. It’s a gift that keeps on giving, challenging my perceptions at every turn.', TRUE, 0, 116, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 161 DAY)),
(1016, 28, 5, 'DeckDockedDevotee (The Steam Deck User): Disco Elysium runs smoothly on the Steam Deck and is verified for high performance, ensuring a seamless experience on the go. The controls are well-adapted for handheld play, making it perfect for traveling. The immersive storytelling doesn’t suffer at all even on the smaller screen.', TRUE, 12, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 212 DAY)),
(1008, 28, 4, 'PreBetaPioneer (The Alpha Tester): Having followed Disco Elysium since its early development stages, it''s amazing to see how the game has evolved. The depth of narrative choices and character development is unparalleled. It’s a masterclass in writing, though it could benefit from more polishing in certain areas.', TRUE, 2, 82, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 221 DAY)),
(1034, 28, 5, 'EarlyAccessAce (The Alpha Tester): Engaging in Disco Elysium during its development was a fascinating journey. The developers did an incredible job building a unique, dense world. Every decision matters and contributes to different outcomes, providing an impressive level of replayability.', TRUE, 9, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 233 DAY)),
(1047, 28, 3, 'FPSFanatic (The Performance Purist): While the narrative experience of Disco Elysium is exceptional, the optimization leaves room for improvement. Occasional frame drops and lag during transitions hinder the otherwise smooth storytelling experience. A few patches could really elevate the technical performance.', TRUE, 10, 27, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 12 DAY)),
(1045, 28, 3, 'ResolutionRadical (The Graphics Snob): Disco Elysium boasts strong artistic direction, but the engine sometimes feels outdated. The character models and environments lack the polish of modern titles, which slightly detracts from the visual immersion. A graphical update could work wonders for its aesthetic appeal.', TRUE, 5, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 119 DAY)),
(1006, 28, 1, 'ReturnRebel (The Refund Rager): 1-star specific. Disco Elysium was an absolute nightmare! The game promised deep narrative and engaging dialogue, but it just dragged on forever with endless talking that led nowhere. I wanted an exciting detective story, not a philosophy lecture! The lack of action made it boring and dull, as if the developers forgot they were making a GAME. Definitely not worth the time or money. Refund requested!', FALSE, 2, 17, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 33 DAY)),
(1044, 28, 2, 'ViewMasterVisionary (The Ultrawide User): Hates rigid FOV. Why does Disco Elysium have such a limited field of view? In an era where ultrawide monitors are becoming the norm, the game''s fixed perspective feels archaic and suffocating. It doesn’t allow me to fully appreciate the beautiful, hand-painted visuals. Such a shame, as the environment deserves to be seen in all its widescreen glory.', FALSE, 4, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 148 DAY)),
(1046, 28, 2, 'GamePadGuru (The Controller User): Hates keyboard/mouse. Disco Elysium? More like Disco Frustration! Why do they force you to use keyboard and mouse for everything? Navigating the menus and interacting with the game world is a chore without decent controller support. I''m all for cerebral stories, but let me play comfortably on my couch with a gamepad, please!', FALSE, 15, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 295 DAY)),
(1003, 28, 4, 'GiftBoxBandit (The Gift Recipient): Random. Received Disco Elysium as a birthday gift and was pleasantly surprised! I had no idea what to expect but ended up getting lost in its mysterious world and complex characters. It''s like a novel come to life, with stunning art and compelling choices. Although not my usual type of game, it was a unique experience that I thoroughly enjoyed.', TRUE, 4, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 243 DAY)),
(1054, 28, 5, 'WaveformWizard (The Audiophile): Loves dynamic range. Disco Elysium''s sound design is a hidden gem! The way each sound fits perfectly with the moody atmosphere and enhances the narrative is truly impressive. The dynamic range in the audio made conversations feel alive, with every whisper and shout resonating beautifully. It’s an auditory delight!', TRUE, 0, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 73 DAY)),
(1019, 28, 4, 'As a veteran of the Souls series, I can appreciate the brutal challenge of unraveling the mysteries within Disco Elysium. While it doesn''t punish you with combat difficulty, it tests your mental fortitude and decision-making skills with equal intensity. Each choice feels like a boss fight, where your wits and perseverance are put to the ultimate test. 4.5/5 because, while challenging, I missed the combat adrenaline rush.', TRUE, 2, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 105 DAY)),
(1043, 28, 3, 'From a QA perspective, Disco Elysium is an impressively polished experience. The narrative is solid, with few bugs interrupting the flow of play. However, the complexity of the choice systems does sometimes lead to minor inconveniences typical of branching narratives. These hiccups don''t detract much from its overall stability. A solid game with a strong foundation. 3/5 for technical stability.', TRUE, 14, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 198 DAY)),
(1002, 28, 5, 'As someone who thrives on complex RPG systems, Disco Elysium is a cerebral feast. The depth of character interactions and skill checks allows for intense customization and replayability, making it a dream come true for those who love to min-max. It''s like solving a sprawling, intricate puzzle every time you boot it up. 5/5, a masterpiece in narrative complexity.', TRUE, 16, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 364 DAY)),
(1011, 28, 2, 'After all the rave reviews and hype, I was expecting a mind-blowing experience. Unfortunately, Disco Elysium felt more like reading a dense book than playing a game. The lack of action and slow pace didn’t live up to the excitement I was promised. It seems to cater to a niche audience that I don''t belong to. 2/5 because the hype set the bar too high.', FALSE, 17, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 220 DAY)),
(1037, 28, 4, 'I''m usually all about collecting those shiny achievements, but Disco Elysium offers a refreshing respite from the grind of multiplayer trophies. Its achievements are well-crafted, pushing you to explore different narrative paths without the pressure of competing against others. 4.5/5, almost perfect, but I do miss a bit of multiplayer camaraderie.', TRUE, 14, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 16 DAY)),
(1030, 28, 4, 'Disco Elysium is a mesmerizing narrative journey that pulls you in with its rich storytelling and intricate character development. As The Ultrawide User, I''m thrilled to report that the game fully supports ultrawide resolutions, offering an immersive experience without any letterboxing. The field of view is dynamically adjustable, which is a rare delight. However, some interiors feel a bit constrained despite the wide aspect. Overall, it''s a fantastic experience. 4.5 stars for slightly cramped interiors.', TRUE, 7, 11, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 229 DAY)),
(1000, 28, 5, 'I dove into Disco Elysium expecting a paywall at every corner but was pleasantly surprised! This game is a complete package with no sneaky microtransactions or DLCs that ask for more cash. The depth of choice and consequences are rewarding without any additional cost. It''s refreshing to experience a game where you get what you pay for! 5 stars for keeping it simple and inclusive.', TRUE, 7, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 81 DAY)),
(1041, 28, 5, 'As someone who has been there since the alpha days, Disco Elysium has evolved beautifully! The narrative remains unparalleled, and the developers have listened closely to community feedback. Bugs are minimal, and the game''s stability has improved drastically. The constant updates are impressive, ensuring an optimal experience for both veterans and newcomers. Kudos for the dedication, 5 stars!', TRUE, 3, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 335 DAY)),
(1020, 28, 1, 'I usually don''t mind spending a bit, but I was expecting more from Disco Elysium based on the hype. The story is interesting, but the pacing is sluggish, and there are moments where it feels like a chore rather than a game. I was hoping for a more engaging experience with a snappier progression. It''s just not what I expected for the price. 1 star for not meeting the expectations of a thrilling interactive story.', FALSE, 0, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 254 DAY)),
(1048, 28, 5, 'Achievements in Disco Elysium are a dream! Every goal is creative and single-player-focused. There''s no pressure from multiplayer achievements or external leaderboards. I can enjoy my detective journey without being sidetracked. Completing the achievement list felt like a natural extension of playing the game instead of a grind. 5 stars for respecting my single-player-only satisfaction!', TRUE, 0, 21, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 43 DAY)),
(1057, 28, 5, 'Disco Elysium is a modder''s paradise! The open-ended design and easily accessible files make it a playground for creating custom experiences. From adjusting character stats to developing entirely new quests, the freedom is unmatched. I found myself diving into the game files just as much as exploring the in-game world. It''s an endlessly customizable experience that keeps me coming back for more.', TRUE, 18, 23, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 87 DAY)),
(1023, 28, 4, 'Disco Elysium isn''t your typical speedrunning game, but the unexpected glitches I stumbled upon during my playthrough added an exciting layer to it. While it lacks a time-based competitive scene, optimizing conversation paths for the quickest outcomes became my unique challenge. It may not be for every speedrunner, but there''s a special thrill in streamlining this narrative-heavy masterpiece.', TRUE, 12, 41, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 14 DAY)),
(1039, 28, 5, 'As a casual gamer who likes to unwind with story-rich games, Disco Elysium was a breath of fresh air. It offers deep narrative exploration without the grind typically found in RPGs. I appreciated the freedom to progress at my own pace and focus on the story, rather than managing inventories or skill trees. It''s a perfect fit for parents looking for a relaxing yet engaging gaming experience.', TRUE, 7, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 107 DAY)),
(1058, 28, 1, 'Honestly, I didn''t enjoy Disco Elysium as much as I hoped. The narrative complexity and lack of conventional gameplay didn''t click with me. I expect more action and interaction from my games, and this felt too much like reading a novel with minimal player agency. It''s highly praised by many, but for someone seeking a more interactive experience, it just wasn’t for me.', FALSE, 44, 12, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 253 DAY)),
(1033, 28, 3, 'From a QA perspective, Disco Elysium is impressively stable for its complexity. While I found a few minor bugs, they were mostly non-intrusive and didn''t detract from the overall experience. The game provides a rich, immersive world and a well-crafted detective story. While it might not appeal to everyone, it''s a solid entry in the RPG genre for those who prefer narrative over action.', TRUE, 20, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 315 DAY)),
(1026, 29, 5, 'Outer Wilds is a breath of fresh air in an era drowning in DLCs and microtransactions. Every nook and cranny of its universe urges you to explore without ever hinting at a paywall or loot box. It''s like stepping back into the golden age of gaming where what you see is what you get. Pure, unadulterated adventure without a cash grab in sight. It''s the kind of experience that brings tears to the eyes of a nostalgic gamer.', TRUE, 16, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 104 DAY)),
(1020, 29, 1, 'While the game captured my interest with its mysterious storytelling, I can''t shake the feeling that it''s a bit overrated. The lack of handholding is a clever design choice, sure, but left me frustrated more often than not. The puzzles border on obtuse, making some sections an exercise in trial and error. That kind of frustration isn''t worth the hype. For me, it''s a one-star experience.', FALSE, 0, 9, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 246 DAY)),
(1017, 29, 4, 'Outer Wilds is a masterpiece when it comes to exploration, but I can''t help but feel it misses a huge opportunity in the customization department. I thrive on personalizing my gameplay experience, and this game offers little on that front. Imagine being able to customize your spacecraft or spacesuit! Alas, I must enjoy the universe as it is, despite the lack of personalization options.', TRUE, 3, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 58 DAY)),
(1052, 29, 3, 'Beautiful game marred by a glaring oversight: FOV options. As someone who plays exclusively on an ultrawide monitor, the rigid Field of View settings are a massive oversight. The universe they crafted is stunning, yet the immersion breaks every time the screen feels cramped or cut off. It''s a simple fix that would make the experience far more enjoyable for ultrawide users like myself.', TRUE, 0, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 158 DAY)),
(1055, 29, 5, 'In an ocean of games designed only to drain your wallet, Outer Wilds shines as a relic of the past. No cash-grabby tactics, just pure gameplay that reminds me of why I fell in love with games in the first place. It''s the kind of game where every discovery feels like a reward, not a transaction. It’s a love letter to a time when games were built on creativity rather than monetization.', TRUE, 0, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 289 DAY)),
(1009, 29, 4, 'Outer Wilds surprised me with its depth and complexity. As someone who thrives on maximizing RPG stats, I initially doubted its potential to scratch my optimization itch. But delving into its intricate universe and piecing together the narrative felt like crafting the ultimate build. Every time loop offers an opportunity to refine my approach and uncover new layers within its richly detailed world. This isn''t your typical RPG, but in its own way, it offers a cerebral challenge that keeps me strategizing long after I''ve stopped playing.', TRUE, 1, 28, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 28 DAY)),
(1041, 29, 5, 'Having followed Outer Wilds since its early development stages, I was genuinely invested in its release. The exploration and puzzle-solving aspects are top-notch, and the time-loop mechanic adds a brilliant twist that offers a fresh sense of urgency. As an alpha tester, it’s clear the developers put a lot of thought into world design and player engagement. It''s exciting to see how each discovery can shift the entire narrative perspective, keeping you eager for more.', TRUE, 2, 62, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 308 DAY)),
(1011, 29, 2, 'Honestly, Outer Wilds didn’t live up to the hype for me. I went in expecting a groundbreaking experience, but found myself frustrated with the endless cycles and lack of direction. The universe is undeniably beautiful, but I often felt lost without a clear goal or progress system like in other games. It’s immersive, sure, but not in a way I found satisfying. For all the buzz, it ended up feeling more niche than I hoped.', FALSE, 6, 13, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 90 DAY)),
(1038, 29, 3, 'As someone who prefers a good controller over a keyboard and mouse, I found Outer Wilds to be a mixed bag. The controls are decent enough, but there were certainly moments where precision felt lacking. Navigating the ship and interacting with the environment could be smoother with better controller support. However, when it clicks, the game offers a captivating journey. It''s worth considering if you can get past the input quirks.', TRUE, 1, 15, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 307 DAY)),
(1035, 29, 4, 'Outer Wilds is an interesting journey from a QA testing perspective. The game’s mechanics and design are robust, and I appreciated the attention to detail in each time loop variation. I encountered a few minor bugs, but nothing game-breaking. The non-linear storytelling is an intriguing choice, allowing players to tackle the universe''s mysteries in their own way. I’d say it offers a unique experience, albeit one that may not suit every player’s tastes.', TRUE, 3, 0, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 283 DAY)),
(1043, 29, 3, 'ExterminateError (The QA Tester): Outer Wilds offers a unique exploration experience with its intricate puzzle mechanics. However, I noticed a few minor bugs that occasionally detract from the immersion. Overall, it''s a fascinating game but requires a bit more polish to meet top QA standards.', TRUE, 0, 26, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 137 DAY)),
(1005, 29, 4, 'TrophyTactician (The Achievement Hunter): I''m captivated by the mysteries of Outer Wilds, but I was relieved to find there are no multiplayer achievements to worry about. The solo achievement experience is well-crafted and rewarding!', TRUE, 18, 3, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 306 DAY)),
(1013, 29, 3, 'GlitchGuru (The QA Tester): Outer Wilds is an intriguing game with a captivating narrative. I did come across some glitches during my playthrough, but none were game-breaking. It''s clear the developers put a lot of effort into crafting a mesmerizing universe.', TRUE, 3, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 55 DAY)),
(1047, 29, 2, 'FPSFanatic (The Performance Purist): Outer Wilds is a visually stunning game, but I did experience some frame rate drops in certain areas which disrupted the otherwise seamless exploration. Some optimization updates would really enhance the experience.', FALSE, 11, 14, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 136 DAY)),
(1028, 29, 5, 'JoystickJuggler (The Controller User): Outer Wilds is a joy to play with a controller, providing smooth and immersive navigation through space. I appreciated the intuitive controller mapping, making exploration feel natural and engaging.', TRUE, 8, 16, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 134 DAY)),
(1006, 30, 1, 'ReturnRebel (The Refund Rager): I don''t get the hype. Return of the Obra Dinn is one of those games where I found myself asking why I even bothered. The monochrome visuals are hard on the eyes, and the constant backtracking with little reward is infuriating. I can''t believe I wasted my time AND money on this. Honestly, just give me my refund already!', FALSE, 4, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 47 DAY)),
(1025, 30, 3, 'MissedOpportunity (The FOMO Victim): I went into Return of the Obra Dinn after hearing all the buzz, hoping to catch the wave before it died down. While the concept and storytelling were interesting, I didn''t feel the same thrill that everyone else seems to. It''s clever, sure, but it didn''t grip me like I expected. I''m neutral because maybe I just missed what others are raving about.', TRUE, 2, 5, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 1 DAY)),
(1038, 30, 2, 'ConsoleCommander (The Controller User): Oh man, Return of the Obra Dinn would have been a completely different experience if it had proper controller support. Navigating with a keyboard and mouse was cumbersome and took away from the experience. For someone like me who''s used to the smooth feel of a controller, this game was a real struggle. I ended up frustrated more often than not.', FALSE, 4, 8, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 84 DAY)),
(1045, 30, 2, 'ResolutionRadical (The Graphics Snob): Ugh, Return of the Obra Dinn looks like it was made in the early 90s, and not in a charming retro way. This ''dated'' visual style is just not my cup of tea. Sure, it might be ''artistic'', but give me modern graphics engines any day. It''s hard to immerse in a game when I''m distracted by how old everything looks.', FALSE, 7, 7, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 253 DAY)),
(1017, 30, 4, 'MegaWhale (The Whale): Customization is my game, and while Return of the Obra Dinn doesn''t offer much in that department, I found myself surprisingly captivated by its unique style. The detective work and painstaking detail in the narrative are incredible, and there''s something special about unraveling the mystery piece by piece. It''s not what I usually go for, but it''s an exception I''m glad I made.', TRUE, 40, 23, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 275 DAY)),
(1004, 30, 5, 'Return of the Obra Dinn is an exceptional love letter to retro gaming. The monochrome graphics take me back to the days of early computer games, while its gameplay revolves around clever detective work instead of modern hand-holding and microtransactions. This isn''t just a game; it''s an experience that respects not only your time but also your wallet.', TRUE, 15, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 108 DAY)),
(1058, 30, 1, 'While others may praise its unique aesthetic, Return of the Obra Dinn left much to be desired for me. The gameplay felt tedious rather than engaging, and I found myself frustrated with the lack of straightforward progression. I expected more for my money, but instead, I felt like I was stuck on a ghost ship of disappointment.', FALSE, 7, 34, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 87 DAY)),
(1049, 30, 2, 'Everyone was raving about how amazing Return of the Obra Dinn was, but I just don''t see it. The story seemed intriguing at first, but I quickly lost interest with its slow pacing and confusing puzzles. Maybe I bought into the hype too much because I ended up feeling let down and bewildered.', FALSE, 12, 30, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 365 DAY)),
(1042, 30, 5, 'Return of the Obra Dinn is a refreshing challenge for those who love a good mental workout. While it might not have the combat prowess of a Souls game, it requires a different kind of strategic thinking and persistence that I sincerely appreciate. If you enjoy pushing your deductive skills to the limit, this is a voyage worth taking.', TRUE, 11, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 91 DAY)),
(1041, 30, 4, 'From the moment Return of the Obra Dinn launched, I was hooked. The attention to detail and the intricacies of its narrative structure kept me engaged from start to finish. It''s clear that every aspect of this game was thoughtfully crafted, making it a must-play for anyone who appreciates innovation and storytelling in gaming.', TRUE, 6, 39, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 336 DAY)),
(1013, 30, 3, 'Return of the Obra Dinn is a masterpiece of game design, but as a QA Tester, I found some areas that felt slightly unstable. The game''s intricate logic puzzles were impressive, but I couldn''t help but notice minor bugs within certain animations and sound triggers. Given the complexity of the game, these are understandable, yet a bit distracting. Overall, a solid experience, but it could use a patch or two for perfection.', TRUE, 16, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 273 DAY)),
(1007, 30, 3, 'I wanted to love Return of the Obra Dinn, really, I did. Everyone was talking about it, and I felt like I had to check it out to avoid FOMO. While the art style was striking and the story intriguing, it didn''t quite resonate with me. Perhaps it''s the slow pace or the lack of dynamic action that left me feeling a bit indifferent. It''s a good game, objectively, but just not for me.', TRUE, 10, 19, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 99 DAY)),
(1023, 30, 4, 'Return of the Obra Dinn is a fascinating experience, but I gotta say, it’s not exactly built for a speedrun. However, the delight of uncovering various glitches was an unexpected thrill! There were a few pathing quirks and some scene skips that offered a chance for speedrunning tricks. For those who love finding ways to beat games in unintended ways, there’s some potential here.', TRUE, 1, 98, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 350 DAY)),
(1028, 30, 2, 'As a controller devotee, Return of the Obra Dinn posed some challenges. The game is designed heavily around mouse-driven gameplay, which made navigation clunky on a controller. I spent more time wrestling with controls than solving the actual mysteries. It’s a shame because the story and art style are incredible, but it’s just not optimized for those of us who shun keyboards and mice.', FALSE, 12, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 43 DAY)),
(1026, 30, 5, 'Return of the Obra Dinn took me back to the golden age of gaming with its retro-inspired graphics and innovative storytelling. It was a refreshing escape from the modern gaming landscape riddled with microtransactions. No ads, no in-game purchases, just pure, unadulterated gaming bliss. It’s a love letter to those of us who long for the simplicity and creativity of the past.', TRUE, 6, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 8 DAY)),
(1005, 30, 5, 'TrophyTactician (The Achievement Hunter): Return of the Obra Dinn is a masterpiece for those who love a solid single-player experience. The game''s achievements are crafted with care, encouraging players to uncover every last secret without the headache of grinding multiplayer nonsense. It''s a journey of clues, deductions, and revelations, all wrapped in a delightful monochrome package. Highly recommended for any achievement hunter who values their solo time!', TRUE, 37, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 82 DAY)),
(1034, 30, 5, 'EarlyAccessAce (The Alpha Tester): Return of the Obra Dinn feels like a meticulously crafted puzzle box. From the moment I started piecing together the fate of the ship''s crew, I was completely invested in its story and mechanics. The unique art style and atmospheric sound design create an engrossing experience. This game offers something fresh and innovative, making it a must-play for those who crave originality.', TRUE, 10, 31, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 89 DAY)),
(1020, 30, 3, 'SaleSnub (The Refund Rager): Okay, so I get the hype around Return of the Obra Dinn, but it''s not for everyone. Yes, the graphics are unique, and the detective work can be rewarding, but if you''re looking for action or replayability, you might be disappointed. I finished it pretty quickly, and there''s not much incentive to return. For the price, I expected a bit more content.', TRUE, 0, 27, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 214 DAY)),
(1000, 30, 4, 'FreeLootLurker (The F2P Leech): Return of the Obra Dinn doesn''t hide any content behind paywalls, so that''s a huge plus in my book. It''s a self-contained experience where everything is accessible from the start. The game relies heavily on your observational skills and wit rather than your wallet, which is refreshing in today''s gaming landscape. Overall, a captivating experience with no nasty surprises!', TRUE, 10, 46, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 189 DAY)),
(1014, 30, 5, 'PenguinPlayer (The Linux User): Finally, a game I can play on Linux without wrestling with anti-cheat software or compatibility layers! Return of the Obra Dinn runs smoothly on my setup, delivering an engaging mystery with style. It''s a brilliant example of how a well-designed game doesn''t need unnecessary anti-cheat measures to be enjoyable on our penguin-loving platform. Bravo!', TRUE, 5, 64, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 32 DAY)),
(1024, 30, 5, 'As a self-proclaimed Lore Archaeologist, ''Return of the Obra Dinn'' is a treasure trove of enigmatic storytelling. The game masterfully weaves a narrative tapestry where every clue hints at a deeper mystery. The vague plot is not a detriment but a delight, encouraging inquisitive minds to dig and piece together the crew''s fate. It''s a masterpiece for anyone who revels in the art of uncovering stories hidden in shadows.', TRUE, 4, 18, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 248 DAY)),
(1010, 30, 4, 'As the Competitive Tryhard, I have to say Obra Dinn stands out with its rigorously engaging puzzle design. No easy modes to hold your hand here, and the bittersweet satisfaction of piecing together the mystery of the ship is akin to the thrill of a well-fought victory. While the challenge is high, the eventual payoff is worth the cerebral effort. A game that respects its player''s intellect is always a win in my book.', TRUE, 2, 23, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 221 DAY)),
(1044, 30, 3, 'From the standpoint of an Ultrawide User, Obra Dinn''s rigid field of view was a bit of a letdown. The game''s visuals, though artistically stunning with its 1-bit style, would have greatly benefited from more flexibility in the display options. Immersion is key, and while the story pulls you in, the constrained visuals pull you out of a truly expansive experience.', TRUE, 9, 2, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 254 DAY)),
(1011, 30, 2, 'Caught in the wave of hype, ''Return of the Obra Dinn'' initially seemed like the game everyone was buzzing about. Yet, as a victim of the hype, my expectations were not entirely met. The distinct art and intriguing concept are admittedly impressive, but the pacing felt as slow as a ship drifting at sea. For those expecting non-stop thrills, temper your excitement.', FALSE, 16, 4, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 11 DAY)),
(1048, 30, 4, 'As someone who measures success in achievements, ''Return of the Obra Dinn'' is refreshingly single-player focused. The absence of multiplayer achievements is a blessing, allowing for a gratifying solo experience. Each correctly identified crew member and solved mystery feels like unlocking a unique achievement worthy of the time invested. It''s proof that single-player games can deliver a fulfilling quest for completionists.', TRUE, 11, 41, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 145 DAY)),
(1016, 30, 5, 'DeckDockedDevotee (The Steam Deck User): Return of the Obra Dinn is a flawless gem on the Steam Deck. This game runs seamlessly, making it a perfect pick for on-the-go gaming. The verified status is rightly deserved as the controls are intuitive and the performance has never once stuttered. Every detail of the ship feels alive, and solving mysteries while lounging comfortably with my Deck is a dream come true. A must-play for any Steam Deck owner!', TRUE, 8, 67, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 8 DAY)),
(1055, 30, 5, 'TimeMachine (The Nostalgia Goggles): Return of the Obra Dinn is a breath of fresh, old air. It has the magic of a bygone era where creativity triumphed over cash grabs. No in-game purchases to tarnish the experience—just pure, immersive storytelling. The monochrome style successfully harkens back to classic games, and the intricate puzzles are reminiscent of the adventures I adored in the past. This is how games should be made!', TRUE, 0, 29, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 44 DAY)),
(1003, 30, 4, 'GiftBoxBandit (The Gift Recipient): I didn''t expect much when unwrapping Return of the Obra Dinn, but wow! It''s like stepping into an interactive detective movie. The art style is unique, and the sound design pulls you right into the mysterious vibe. Though I wasn''t sure what I was getting into at first, I ended up playing for hours. A pleasant surprise for sure!', TRUE, 26, 20, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 97 DAY)),
(1022, 30, 4, 'BossBattleBrute (The Souls Veteran): Return of the Obra Dinn isn''t about dodging attacks or mastering combat, but that doesn''t mean it lacks challenge. The difficulty lies in its complex puzzle mechanics and requiring a keen eye for detail. It’s a different kind of battle, one where your mind is the weapon. Any fan of intense challenges will find themselves lost in the pages of this pirate ship narrative.', TRUE, 6, 1, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 336 DAY)),
(1008, 30, 5, 'PreBetaPioneer (The Alpha Tester): As someone who dives into games before they are fully cooked, Return of the Obra Dinn feels like a well-polished artifact from another timeline. It''s rare to find a game with such a cohesive vision and execution without a hitch or bug to be found. The attention to detail is astounding and the investigative gameplay is innovative. It''s a masterclass in game design and a testament to what focused development can achieve.', TRUE, 20, 61, DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 217 DAY)),;
